4420,'',"Meta pane permanently opening automatically and on wrong side of screen?\nI recently updated by install of Ghost from 5.0 I think to 5.3 and this started happening when I edit a post. Notice the meta pane is already open, and cannot be closed. I'm pretty sure it has something to do with the way Ghost is installed since it happens on Chrome, Chrome Canary, Safari, and Firefox. \r\n\r\n![screenshot 2014-11-08 09 22 32](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/863286/4964383/481df560-6729-11e4-940a-7fcb2840caa5.png)\r\n\r\nI've diffed both version of ghost and the new unzipped directory of 5.3. The core folders are exactly the same and I have this expected output from `/content` since I have uploaded images and also modified .hbs (after merging in 5.3) for the Google Analytics code.\r\n\r\n```\r\nme@computer:~# diff -rq ghost/content/ ghost05/content/\r\nOnly in ghost/content/data: ghost.db\r\nOnly in ghost/content/data: ghost-dev.db\r\nOnly in ghost/content/images: 2014\r\nFiles ghost/content/themes/casper/default.hbs and ghost05/content/themes/casper/default.hbs differ\r\n```\r\n\r\nAny thoughts? \r\n"
4419,'','Website is not valid URL\n### Issue Summary\r\nWhen attempting to edit/update the ghost user profile settings, an invalid url message displays, "Website is not a valid URL" - however no website or information has changed on the profile. \r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce:\r\n1. Open blog Ghost and Log in with credentials.\r\n2. Navigate to /ghost/settings/users/user-name.\r\n3. Click save.\r\n4. Observe invalid url displays and failed to load resource displays in\r\nbrowser console.\r\n\r\nI don\'t believe this is similar to #1623, but may be worth referencing, as the error isn\'t directly with URL field, but a similar error message is appearing. \r\n\r\n### Technical Details\r\n\r\n- Ghost(Pro)\r\n- Client OS:10.10 Yosemite / Windows 8.1\r\n- Browser: Chrome / Firefox / IE 11\r\n\r\nPlease see included screenshot with error message and console error\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2014-11-06 at 9 35 09 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6034248/4962597/b8e45924-66e3-11e4-958b-5b067607f827.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n'
4418,'',"Editor preview not shown in production on Chrome\nStrange behavior, I'm not technical enough to decipher: when run in development on my local machine, regardless of browser, ghost works fine.\r\n\r\nWhen on Chrome Version 38.0.2125.111 (64-bit) on Xubuntu 14.04 LTS in production from my web server, while editing a page the live preview pane doesn't show anything. I get a couple errors in the JS console:\r\n\r\n* (2 x) Uncaught NotFoundError: Failed to execute 'insertBefore' on 'Node': The node before which the new node is to be inserted is not a child of this node.\r\n* Uncaught Error: Something you did caused a view to re-render after it rendered but before it was inserted into the DOM.\r\n* Failed to load resource: net::ERR_CACHE_MISS\r\n\r\nThere are other strange issues too, like after clicking through or cancelling modal notifications the screen goes blank and nothing appears until reload, also clicking on Settings -> Users -> {User} nothing happens.\r\n\r\nCould it have something to do with Cloudflare's SSL setting?\r\n\r\n[My blog](https://steves-blog.com/)\r\n\r\nGhost version 0.53 installed via zip."
