4414,'','Add "save" shortcut to settings screens\nOn a post, `ctrl/cmd + s` saves the post. I don\'t see any reason why the same shouldn\'t be the case for the various settings screens!\r\n\r\n- [ ] Save `settings/user/xx` user screen with ctrl/cmd+s\r\n- [ ] Save `settings/general` screen\r\n\r\nSee the `core/client/utils/editor-shortcuts` for an example of how to make an OS specific shortcuts hash, and `core/client/routes/posts.js`\'s shortcuts + actions hashes for an example of how this should be implemented in the two settings routes.'
4413,'',"Meta Data preview inaccurate \nToday I want to discuss the SEO of posts. Maybe get some input and come to a solution (if there is any). \r\n\r\nTake for example my latest post default (untouched) meta data preview:\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2014-11-07 at 16 33 29](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2955483/4955288/34a5d0d8-6694-11e4-8e33-c96a60216de0.png)\r\n\r\nHowever the real (Google) result is as follows:\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2014-11-07 at 16 33 44](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2955483/4955338/87cad0d8-6694-11e4-89eb-fac2de806dea.png)\r\n\r\nPersonally I'd love to have the preview one. I think we should remove the duplicate title in the excerpt, the date and the 'on [subject]' part. Like the preview suggests.\r\n\r\nIs there any way we can influence the search results?"
4412,'',"[bug] Editors can't see self in user list\n## Issue Summary\r\n\r\nMy editor user can't see anyone in in his users group, including himself?\r\n\r\n## Repro steps\r\n\r\n1. Invite an editor\r\n2. log in as the editor and go to /settings/users\r\n\r\n\r\n### What the owner account sees\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2014-11-07 at 08 37 05](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1207005/4955275/20107f7e-6694-11e4-8ed7-86f07bb94da1.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### What the editor account sees\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2014-11-07 at 08 36 59](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1207005/4955278/26936d2a-6694-11e4-8359-bfa840a65cfc.png)\r\n"
4411,'',"Changing a user's slug seems to change all the user's slugs\nWhen you edit a user's slug and then go to edit another user's slug, the second user's slug appears to be set to the value that you changed the first user's slug to. I don't believe it actually changes the slug in the database, I think it's just showing the wrong pre-filled value.\r\n\r\nI've not tested this with more than two users but I don't see why two users with different roles would be related like this so my guess is that it would effect all the other users. I'm happy to test this further if you'd like me to.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Have at least two active users. In my case, I was logged in as the Owner / Administrator and had a second user setup as an Editor.\r\n2. Edit either user's slug, save and go back.\r\n3. Click onto the other user.\r\n4. The other user's slug is pre-filled with the value you just changed the first user's slug to.\r\n\r\nIf you have any trouble reproducing this, let me know and I'll provide more information.\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.3\r\n* Client OS: Mac OS X 10.10\r\n* Server OS: Ghost.org\r\n* Node Version: No idea. It's a Ghost.org site.\r\n* Browser: Chrome 40.0.2209.0 dev (64-bit), Safari 8.0\r\n* Database: Mysql"
