4407,'','Increase available screen real-estate for post editor\nHere\'s a screenshot of the post editor in v0.5.3:\r\n\r\n![screenshot 2014-11-06 13 04 52](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/439616/4932502/4dfc00b2-658a-11e4-89e5-a041e3d0c135.png)\r\n\r\nOn my 1600x900 resolution screen, the web page is 813px tall, out of which 100px is taken up by the top and bottom bars (in black). That\'s ~12% of vertical space dedicated to non-content. And if you take into account the height of the post title and the vertical padding on the content editor, that increases to 31%!\r\n\r\nI think it would be great to have more vertical real-estate for the post content. For now, this could be as simple as adding a "Fullscreen editing" button (similar to the one on the github comment editor), which could selectively display only the editor + preview panes, or maybe even just the editor when horizontal space is constrained. With a keyboard shortcut it would be nearly perfect. I can definitely help with the design brain-storming, and perhaps with code too once the community agrees on the interaction.'
