4405,'',"Removes hash after the url when clicking Meta Data\nRemoves that hash appended to the URL when clicking Meta Data in post settings.\r\n\r\nCloses #4386\r\n\r\nWhen clicking 'Meta Data' the click event appends a # to the URL. I replaced the a with a button element so that won't happen anymore. The button has a type attribute because it will try and submit the form without it. Added text-align: left to the navlist button because the button centers it's content by default.\r\n\r\n"
4404,'','Adds SIGTERM handling\ncloses #4403\r\n- adds SIGTERM handler to match SIGINT handler'
4403,'',"Ghost doesn't handle SIGTERM\nCurrently Ghost handles SIGINT allowing users to use Ctrl+C to kill the server but it doesn't respond to SIGTERM. This will result in the process manager killing it after a given timeout which won't give it time to finish things up and exit cleanly.\r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce**\r\n1. Start Ghost running\r\n2. Send the Ghost process a SIGTERM\r\n\r\n**Expected Result**\r\nGhost exits cleanly, just as if SIGINT was sent.\r\n\r\n**Actual Result**\r\nGhost does nothing and continues regardless, if a process manager sent the SIGTERM a SIGKILL may be sent after a timeout which will kill the Ghost process without any cleanup being done."
