4392,'',"Four configuration atoms for site URL instead of one\nThis is a bug report for inconsistency within Ghost's configuration for the site URL.\r\n\r\n* Starting Ghost with `url` set to `foo` causes Ghost to start up with `Your blog is now available on foo`. However, this message is misleading because templates will still point to the default URL (http://my-ghost-blog.com/).\r\n* Starting Ghost with `theme.url` set to `foo` causes Ghost to start up with `Your blog is now available on http://my-ghost-blog.com/`, but templates will point to `foo`.\r\n\r\nDisparity between `url` and `theme.url` causes different parts of the application to think the site is hosted on two different URLs concurrently. Since there is presumably no use case for this I propose simplifying the configuration so that the value is set it one place instead of four. The other places this value is defined include `_config.url` and `_config.theme.url` but I have not investigated how they impact the application (if at all)."
