4349,'',"Workaround for outlook, who doesn't like quoted-printable encoding\nFor example, outlook 2013 plus would not interpert the following html\r\n(encoded via quoted-printable encoding):\r\n```\r\n<a href=3D=22http://engineering=\r\n.como.com/ghost/signup/MTQxNTcwNzM5MTYwN3x5dXJ5QG5peC5jby5pbHx3NVBmUUN4RGZr=\r\ncGhKc3FPOElybXNZNWtzR0FMTU9tRFI5UlNyRWQ4SGJZPQ=3D=3D/=22 style=3D=22color: =\r\n#5ba4e5;=22>Click here to activate your account</a>\r\n```\r\nThe workournd forces node-mailer to use base64, which outlook understands\r\nwell."
4347,'',"Ghost and Nginx, connecting through an unix Domain Socket\nI'm having troubles with listening through unix domain sockets with Ghost and Nginx.\r\nI think it might be an issue with Ghost, so I'm posting my settings here to debug this.\r\n\r\n\r\nIn my Ghost `config.js` production settings - I've set \r\n```\r\nserver: {\r\n    socket: '/tmp/my-domain.com.socket'\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd in nginx `sites-enabled/my-domain.com`\r\n```\r\nserver {\r\n     listen 80;\r\n     server_name my-domain.com;\r\n   \r\n     location / {\r\n         proxy_pass http://unix:/tmp/my-domain.com.socket;\r\n         proxy_set_header Host $http_host;\r\n         proxy_set_header User-Agent $http_user_agent;\r\n         proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nEverything looks completely fine to me, yet it doesn't work. I restart nginx, ghost and I still get a gateway error.\r\n\r\n\r\nAny tips? And by the way if I set in `config.js` the Unix domain socket with an unix prefix, it doesn't get created at all. Is this intended ?\r\n\r\n```\r\nserver: {\r\n    socket: 'http://unix:/tmp/my-domain.com.socket'\r\n}\r\n``` \r\n"
