4334,'','String appended to css, js paths with npm start - problem when deploying to Github pages using a tool like buster?\nHi ghost,\r\n\r\nThis is more of a question than anything. I recently came to ghost and would like to use it on my github pages. I pulled down the zip and did npm start followed with buster generate to generate the static files. However, all the js, css paths in index.html have text appended to them which messes up the file location when I deploy to github pages. I guess my question is: is there a workaround for this? How are people who use ghost on their github pages getting around this? I appreciate any insight!\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nMike'
