4292,'',"Adds security validation to packages\nCloses #4291\r\n\r\n* Added `grunt-nsp-packages`, `grunt-david` and `grunt-retire`\r\n* Added `audit` task\r\n\r\nUsage:\r\n\r\n* `grunt audit --force` to check everything. Use the `--force`, Luke, otherwise the first error will terminate the process.\r\n* `grunt retire` to check for both front end javascript (everything inside `bower_components/`) and node modules\r\n* `grunt retire:js` to only check front end js\r\n* `grunt retire:node` to only check node modules\r\n* `grunt david` to check for outdated packages\r\n* `grunt validate-package` to check vulnerable packages\r\n\r\nInterestingly enough retire seems to be better at this, but it may also pick up false positives. I'm unsure whether to use `nsp-packages` for node modules and retire for frontend only, or get rid of `nsp-packages` and use retire for all."
