4267,'',"Feature Request: Markdown in Author Bio, or at least HTML.\n(#4261 was closed when it was not addressed)\r\n\r\nI have a multi-author Ghost Pro blog http://www.livelywork.com. Each author has their own Author page, each with their own Bio field.\r\n\r\nI'd like to be able to have markdown in the 200 char bio, in particular to add each author's twitter account, i.e. for me [@ChristopherA](https://twitter.com/christophera)\r\n\r\nCurrently each Author bio is a plain-text only field. You may not use HTML it in —\xa0if you do it is displayed as plain-text.\r\n\r\nYou can't modify the theme to add links, which many people have done to add links to single author ghost blogs, as this is a multi-author blog.\r\n\r\nIf not Markdown, than at least allowing html.\r\n\r\nThis fix suggested in issue #1517 does not address this issue. I tried substituting {{{bio}}} for {{bio}} in my theme and it didn't work, resulting in just plain text. Then tried using {{{user.bio}}} for {{bio}} results in no text shown at all (blank)."
