4229,'',"port forwarded URL not responding\n#### Config\r\nI use vagrant and install ghost as a npm module on it. I previously added this line to my Vagrantfile:\r\n```config.vm.network :forwarded_port, guest: 3000, host: 3000```\r\nI changed config.js development server port to the port I want to listen to: 3000.\r\n\r\n#### Issue\r\n`curl http://localhost:3000` on the VM side is OK, but asking `http://localhost:3000` on chromium (on my host) makes me ERR_SOCKET_NOT_CONNECTED on the browser (Ghost app does not respond on console). The corresponding curl error is:\r\n```curl: (56) Recv failure: Connexion ré-initialisée par le correspondant```\r\n\r\nNevertheless, my other node app (express app) can be reached by chromium without problem.\r\n\r\nI try to configure the config.js url in several ways, and also try to change the `127.0.0.1` server host value by `localhost`, but got no result. Idem when using port 80, forwarded to port 1337 on my host.\r\n\r\nI don't want to change my Vagrantfile, just Ghost.\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: `npm install ghost` version: 0.5.2\r\n* Client OS: Linux 3.8.0-35-generic (i386) - ubuntu 14.04\r\n* Server OS (VM): Linux 3.11.0-12-generic (i386) - ubuntu 13.10 server\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.15\r\n* Vagrant Version: 1.4.3\r\n* Browser: Chrome 34.0.1847.132\r\n* Vagrantfile forwarded ports: \r\n``` \r\nconfig.vm.network :forwarded_port, guest: 80, host: 1337\r\nconfig.vm.network :forwarded_port, guest: 3000, host: 3000\r\nconfig.vm.network :forwarded_port, guest: 443, host: 3443\r\n```\r\n"
