4171,'','Tag Management UI Markup\nReferences #3926\r\n\r\nStatic markup for the Tag Management screen\r\n\r\nA few notes:\r\n* Clicking the tag title now opens a settings menu on the right hand side, much like the new post settings menu\r\n* The settings menu is also used when adding a new tag, only the delete button isn\'t there and \'Edit Tag\' says \'New Tag\'\r\n* Search will not be included in the first implementation of this\r\n* As with the post settings menu, clicking outside of the menu closes it\r\n* The markup is dependent on child tags being nested _inside_ its parent. This makes them infinitely scalable.\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<div class="tag">\r\n    ...\r\n    <div class="tag">\r\n        ...\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n```'
4170,'',"Typed code blocks will print their language name if the block doesn't start the line\n## Issue Summary\r\n\r\nWhen doing a typed code block where you specify the language of the code, like so:\r\n\r\n```\r\n     ```javascript\r\n\r\n     ```\r\n```\r\nthe language is included as the content if the blocks backticks don't begin the line.\r\n\r\n\r\n# Reproduction\r\nPut this in your editor\r\n\r\n```markdown\r\n    ```javascript\r\n    We have some code here\r\n    ```\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Issue summary updated by @novaugust**\r\n\r\n-------------------------------\r\n\r\n**Original issue text**\r\nSuppose we have markdown:\r\n\r\n```markdown\r\n- This\r\n\r\n    ![I have a image]()\r\n\r\n- is\r\n\r\n- a\r\n\r\n    ```javascript\r\n    We have some code here\r\n    ```\r\n\r\n- list\r\n```\r\n\r\nCurrently I found 2 issues:\r\n\r\n1. The editor does not recognize the image and does not display an image upload placeholder\r\n2. The editor incorrectly parse the fence code block so it has the text `javascript` in my code\r\n\r\nMaybe the editor has more issues when parsing a markdown list"
