4165,'',"Bug: Tag input doesn't work on mobile\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nThe tag input bar doesn't work on mobile. When entering tags and trying to complete them with a `,` nothing will happen. \r\n\r\nThis seems to be a bug in Webkit and Webkit based engines: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=16735. Also relevant: https://code.google.com/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=118639\r\n\r\nI have created a simple example that reproduces the issue: http://jsbin.com/tetemo/1/edit (open http://jsbin.com/tetemo/1/ on mobile and type something - the keyCode will show as 0 instead of the character you actually typed)\r\n\r\nI will try to figure out a way to fix this.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Open editor on mobile\r\n2. Tap tag bar\r\n3. Enter tag\r\n4. Type a `,` - observe it being added as text\r\n\r\nThis is a bug because a `,` completes a tag on desktop.\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master - latest commit:  \r\n* Client OS:  Android\r\n* Browser: Chrome"
