4088,'',"Bugs: IE 10/11 UI Issues\nI've discovered a few issues with Ghost in IE10 & IE11 (Windows 8 for IE10, and 8.1 for IE11).\r\n\r\nNone of them seem particularly tough, or completely destroy the UX, but they're not working as specced.\r\n\r\n- [x] Flexbox issues in the user list. (IE 10/11)\r\n\t* Not vertically centred\r\n\t* Does get the `-ms-` prefix. May need to adjust Autoprefixer?\r\n- [x] Burger icon for the mobile nav is not vertically centred (IE 10)\r\n\t* Needs `top: -10px;` on IE 10 only to fix, but a re-work to cure\r\n- [x] Mobile nav doesn't open properly on the settings pages (IE10/11) - [Screenshot](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/390392/4349930/f8f267d0-41cd-11e4-82a1-4a17242fcf09.png)\r\n- [x] Ghost logo & version not showing on the about page in IE11"
4087,'halfdan','Long post meta description is punitively killed\n## Issue Description\r\n\r\nIf you type more than 200 characters in the meta description box, everything you typed is killed via a rollback() since the server says there\'s an error.\r\n\r\nThis is bad, because, I put a lot of work into those 201 characters! Don\'t take it away from me!\r\n\r\n## Repro Steps\r\n\r\n1. Open the editor\r\n3. write > 200 characters in the meta description\r\n4. click out\r\nBOOM\r\n\r\n## Suggestions\r\n\r\nValidate on the client! Or shoot, just don\'t rollback. That\'s so mean!\r\n\r\nAlso, if we want the user to get back the original content of the meta description box, perhaps a "Reset" button would be nice? \r\nMeow'
4086,'ErisDS',"Add Gmail-style shortcuts\nRef #3940\r\n- add `j`/`k` for navigating posts down / up\r\n- `c` for opening a new post\r\n-  `o` to open the selected post\r\n- update keymaster dep to allow for multiple key unbinds (`key.unbind('up, j')`)"
4085,'',"Mail: deprecated mail.fromaddress, reformatted mail.from to Title <emailaddress>\nCloses #4018, #4082\r\n\r\n* reformatted code to allow for traversal\r\n* deeper config items should be denoted like this: `object.object.object.property`.\r\n* added tests for testing the deprecation warnings\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n* cleaned up `mail_spec.js`\r\n* deprecated `mail.fromaddress`\r\n* implemented 'Blog title <email@address.com>' format with fallbacks\r\n* added tests to deprecation and from address, made existing ones more robust\r\n* moved domain intuit into its own module: `GhostMailer.getDomain()`\r\n\r\nLeft them as two separate commits on purpose."
4084,'',"Config: Ghost should fallback if config.url or config.server is missing\nIf the `config.url` option is missing altogether, Ghost will still run in the terminal, but it's not accessible via the browser. As an interesting trial, I also removed `config.server` from the file, Ghost is still running, not accessible. There are error messages for the `.url` to be invalid (but not missing). There are not error messages for the server missing.\r\n\r\nQuestions:\r\n\r\n* Should we solve this?\r\n* Should Ghost error and halt?\r\n* Should Ghost assume default hostname and port, and start on that as a fallback?\r\n\r\n## Tech\r\n\r\n* version: Ghost git (latest: 2f986160fd7d58426bca205298d59d65bb9ff9ea)\r\n* Client OS: Mac OSX 10.10 (14A361p) (beta3)\r\n* Server OS: Mac OSX 10.10 (14A361p) (beta3)\r\n* node: 0.10.31\r\n* npm: 1.4.23\r\n* browser: any\r\n* db: sqlite\r\n\r\nThis might be related to #3864."
4083,'',"Hitting tab bar from Title to Compose box creates pop-up that “logs out” user\n### What’s happening\r\nWhen composing a new blog post, any time a **Title** is typed and then the TAB bar is hit to jump from the Title to the Compose box, a pop-up appears informing you that you have been logged out and should save all copy.\r\n\r\nHowever, it appears as though a log out isn't actually happening and no data is lost.\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2014-09-20 at 8 29 04 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/5355322/4346293/66f4fba8-40f7-11e4-86bd-a3f180402619.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce it\r\n1. Compose a title\r\n2. Hit the tab bar to go to the compose box\r\n\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n- Currently on Ghost Pro\r\n- Mac OSX Mavericks\r\n- Occurs on Safari & Chrome (latest versions)"
