3997,'','Bug: Hard to access last character of previous line in the editor\n### Issue Summary\r\nWhile editing a post, if I try to click on the last character of the previous line, the cursor jumps to the beginning of that line. If I try using the left/right arrow keys, it jumps between the second to last character and the beginning of the line.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Start a new post\r\n2. Type more than one line\r\n3. Click on the end of the previous line\r\n4. Press right/left arrow keys\r\n\r\nThis is a bug because...\r\nI expect to easily get to the last character of any line just by pointing my mouse at it and clicking or by using the arrow keys.\r\n![ghost](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2450827/4211403/f71846c2-3887-11e4-8b9e-8f577800842c.gif)\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master - latest commit: stable - a21ce4dd55a0c9f2522a4edb1e97e1cbd98518ff\r\n* Client OS & Server OS at http://localhost:2368/ghost/editor/: x86_64 GNU/Linux, Arch Linux 3.16.2-1-ARCH\r\n* Node Version: v0.10.31\r\n* Browser: Google Chrome Version 39.0.2145.4 dev (64-bit)\r\n* Database: ghost-dev.db (default sqlite)\r\n'
