3983,'','Bug: URL replacement in RSS feed mucks with content\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nIn the RSS feed, relative URL\'s in `src` and `href` attributes are replaced with absolute ones, but this happens even when a string like \' src="/blah" \' is in the textual content of a post. \r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Create a new post.\r\n2. In the body of the post type:\r\n> src="/hello.jpg"\r\n\r\n3. Publish the post, and then go to `http://[your blog url]/rss`.  \r\n\r\nIn the first `item > description`, you\'ll see something like: \r\n```html\r\n<p>src=\'http://[your blog url]/hello.jpg\' </p>\r\n```\r\nInstead of\r\n```html\r\n<p>src=\'/hello.jpg\'</p>\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Comments\r\n\r\nReason: the rss controller is [using a naive regex](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/blob/master/core/server/controllers/frontend.js#L491) to do the URL replacement.\r\n\r\nOne fix approach could use something HTML-aware like [trumpet](https://github.com/substack/node-trumpet) to process the post...\r\n\r\nAnother could be to (a) expose a handlebars helper (or parameter on an existing one) that transforms the post body to be rss-ready, and then (b) use a hbs template for the feed instead of a controller, possibly even making it part of the theme structure.\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master - latest commit:  0a96351274a8243e3bdb2715b69ce1c9e84b6d06\r\n* Client OS: Mac OS Mavericks\r\n* Server OS: Mac OS Mavericks\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.30\r\n* Browser: Chrome 37.0.2062.94\r\n'
3982,'',"Bug: Admin session is not restricted to /ghost/\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nBefore we switched to ember-simple-auth/OAuth the admin session was restricted to the `/ghost/` subdirectory by setting the path in the cookie. ember-simple-auth uses localstorage to save the access_token and refresh_token. This causes some problems when having multiple Ghost instances installed on the same domain but in different subdirectories. The authentication from Ghost instance A will cause a conflict with the one from Ghost instance B (either by not being valid when logged in or by signing you out when logging in to a different instance). \r\n\r\nSee: https://ghost.org/forum/installation/16209-multi-blog-site-with-auth-conflicts/\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Have two instances of Ghost run in a subdirectory\r\n2. Sign in to one of them\r\n3. Navigate to the second (you'll see an 'invalid authentication' + be asked to log in)\r\n4. Log in to the second instance\r\n5. You are now logged out of the first.\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0 - master \r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nI checked ember-simple-auth and there doesn't seem to be a way to restrict authentication to a specific subdirectory. I escalated this issue to ember-simple-auth: https://github.com/simplabs/ember-simple-auth/issues/300"
3981,'',"Bug: Can't checkmark Static Page in Chrome and Can't see checkmark in Firefox until reload\n### Issue Summary\r\nThere is no way to make a post static in Chrome because clicking the box doesn't do anything. Firefox allows static pages to be created, but the checkmark doesn't show up until the page has been refreshed. See included gifs.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Edit a post\r\n2. Click the gear and click the box for Static Page\r\n\r\nThis is a bug because...\r\nI should see a checkmark after clicking the box for Static Page, but I don't. Upon refreshing the page and looking again at the box for Static Page, I do see a checkmark in Firefox, but not in Chrome.\r\n![trystaticpagechrome](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2450827/4180893/95cafc7e-3707-11e4-8849-1531a50ab8f0.gif)\r\n![trystaticpagefirefox](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2450827/4180896/9f1e5a78-3707-11e4-8332-a358d46682b0.gif)\r\n\r\nFor Chrome, the page is not static and still shows up in the lists of posts, so there is no way to create a static page from within Chrome.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master - latest commit:  v0.5.2-1 adb94efe1d3f7827ddde25aea77853add981848f\r\n* Client & Server OS at http://localhost:2368/ghost/: x86_64 GNU/Linux, Arch Linux 3.16.1-1-ARCH\r\n* Node Version: v0.10.31\r\n* Browser: Chrome Version 39.0.2145.4 dev (64-bit), and Firefox Version 32.0 (mistakenly put 33.0 in gif)\r\n* Database: ghost-dev.db (default sqlite)"
3980,'',"High memory consumption\nI noticed that the memory usage of `ghost` is increasing drastically after few hours running and I was wondering if that is normal. Right now, I have to instances eating about ~200mb of memory.\r\n\r\nI currently use `pm2` to manage my processes, but I observed the same issue using `forever`. I run node v0.10.25, which is the version shipping with Ubuntu 14.04.\r\n\r\nHere is the current status of my two instances:\r\n\r\n    # pm2 list\r\n    ┌──────────┬────┬─────────┬─────┬────────┬───────────┬────────┬──────────────┬─────────────┐\r\n    │ App name │ id │ mode    │ PID │ status │ restarted │ uptime │       memory │    watching │\r\n    ├──────────┼────┼─────────┼─────┼────────┼───────────┼────────┼──────────────┼─────────────┤\r\n    │ ghost    │ 0  │ cluster │ 931 │ online │         0 │ 22h    │ 178.066 MB   │ unactivated │\r\n    │ ghost    │ 1  │ cluster │ 933 │ online │         0 │ 22h    │ 219.902 MB   │ unactivated │\r\n    └──────────┴────┴─────────┴─────┴────────┴───────────┴────────┴──────────────┴─────────────┘\r\n     Use `pm2 desc[ribe] <id>` to get more details\r\n\r\n\r\nAm I doing anything wrong here ? I don't think I have anything special in my setup, all my config and everything is exactly as specified in the documentation.\r\n\r\nI will provide any further information if needed !\r\n\r\n**Edit:** After I perform a complete restart, here's the memory usage : \r\n\r\n    # pm2 restart all\r\n    Processing......\r\n    PM2 Process ghost restarted\r\n    PM2 Process ghost restarted\r\n    PM2 Process restarted...\r\n    ┌──────────┬────┬─────────┬──────┬────────┬───────────┬────────┬─────────────┬─────────────┐\r\n    │ App name │ id │ mode    │ PID  │ status │ restarted │ uptime │      memory │    watching │\r\n    ├──────────┼────┼─────────┼──────┼────────┼───────────┼────────┼─────────────┼─────────────┤\r\n    │ ghost    │ 0  │ cluster │ 7521 │ online │         1 │ 1s     │ 34.555 MB   │ unactivated │\r\n    │