3958,'','Cannot sign in after upgrading from 0.4.2 -> 0.5.1\nFirst of all, clicking "log in" now throws up a "Please enter password" warning even though my browser already filled the details in. It seems I have to click the password box (and do nothing) before clicking log in. Perhaps this is a separate issue.\r\n\r\nNevertheless, it is impossible to log in - trying to log in just redirects back to the log in page every time without further warning or error. Studying the net log reveals:\r\n* POST token = 200 OK {"access_token":"REDACTED","expires_in":3600,"token_type":"Bearer"}\r\n* GET ?include=roles&status=all = 401 Unauthorized {"type":"error","message":"Please Sign In","status":"passive"}'
