3844,'','Bug: Import - Validation (isUUID) failed for uuid\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nI\'ve just exported my content directly from my GhostPro blog (which I assume must be running v0.5.0) and I\'ve just tried to import it into a fresh local install of the Ghost stable branch. None of the posts get imported and they all spit a "Validation (isUUID) failed for uuid" error.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Export content from GhostPro (v0.5.0)\r\n2. Import into local Ghost install (v0.5.0)\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: stable (v0.5.0)\r\n* Client OS: OS X\r\n* Server OS: OS X\r\n* Node Version: v0.10.5\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: Sqlite3'
3843,'','bug: Keyboard shortcuts prevent me from entering text properly\nEDIT:  This is a known issue - Sorry for duplicating, Github filters got me :< \r\n\r\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nWhen using a keyboard layout that is not the QWERTY standard one (US/UK) Markdown shortcuts take the precedence over user input meaning it will prevent the user from entering certain characters in the editor.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Have a french belgian layout (lol sorry)\r\n2. Try to enter "@" character using CTRL+ALT+é (that\'s the same as CTRL+ALT+2 or ALT GR + 2 for you non belgian keyboard owners and no, its not in the in the numpad)\r\n3. See the H2 markdown appear "##"\r\n\r\nI also noticed that the CTRL+SHIFT+L does not work\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: Pretty recent :P \r\n* Client OS: Windows 7\r\n* Browser: Chrome 36.0 latest \r\n'
