3823,'',"Apache Basic Auth protected Proxy conflicts with Signup\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nReverse Proxy configuration on Apache with Basic Authentication protection works well. But signup conflicts with Bearer Authentication -> signup page with 401 error.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. https://www.example.com/blog points to Apache Server\r\n2. Apache is configured as a reverse Proxy https://www.example.com/blog -> http://localhost:2386/blog\r\n3. Ghost is listening on http://localhost:2386 and configured with subdir /blog\r\n4. https://www.example.com/blog is protected through Apache Basic Authentication\r\n5. Acces to https://www.example.com/blog asks for basic auth credentials after that blog is visible (ok)\r\n6. Acces to https://www.example.com/blog/ghost shows signup form but login returns 401.\r\n\r\n### Investigation\r\n\r\nTrace down url and headers in file core/server/middleware.index.js with console.log:\r\n\r\n    function decideIsAdmin(req, res, next) {\r\n        console.log(req.url);\r\n        console.log(req.headers);\r\n        res.isAdmin = req.url.lastIndexOf(config.paths.subdir + '/ghost/', 0) === 0;\r\n        next();\r\n    }\r\n\r\n#### Trace without Basic Auth (ok)\r\n      /blog/ghost/api/v0.1/users/me/?include=roles&status=all\r\n      { host: 'www.example.com',\r\n        'user-agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; rv:31.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/31.0',\r\n        accept: 'application/json, text/javascript, */*; q=0.01',\r\n        'accept-language': 'de,en-US;q=0.7,en;q=0.3',\r\n        'accept-encoding': 'gzip, deflate',\r\n        authorization: 'Bearer nDLUH3doktlsVoWJdm6zZuoD5RHZLwo50Mo8MRO352cN9gVb8q7Gurppxc4v9FlbVubV1P3geyRnm1FqzP5KLaKHqPeOxIbd5CVZKpsLUKBxEtKTr7vJLuH3fy2qISBeaTjEi4Y7QlLC2PKjvBbXtWcRYEWI9WZyfQV4zTnX5f9wtXe3epa3ljo50gngKyBKQADrl3KjzQOIvJGy8Sy1Ms9KI1L1T27b20vlOqVDZb1p1epVbOZW0ytRCtuiG6X',\r\n        'x-requested-with': 'XMLHttpRequest',\r\n        referer: 'https://www.example.com/blog/ghost/signin/',\r\n        'x-forwarded-for': '91.198.198.00',\r\n        'x-forwarded-host': 'www.example.com',\r\n        'x-forwarded-server': 'www.example.com',\r\n        connection: 'Keep-Alive' }\r\n\r\n#### Trace with Basic Auth (nok)\r\n\r\n      /blog/ghost/api/v0.1/users/me/?include=roles&status=all\r\n      { host: 'www.example.com',\r\n        'user-agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; rv:31.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/31.0',\r\n        accept: 'application/json, text/javascript, */*; q=0.01',\r\n        'accept-language': 'de,en-US;q=0.7,en;q=0.3',\r\n        'accept-encoding': 'gzip, deflate',\r\n        authorization: 'Basic xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx',\r\n        'x-requested-with': 'XMLHttpRequest',\r\n        referer: 'https://www.example.com/blog/ghost/signin/',\r\n        'x-forwarded-for': '91.198.198.00',\r\n        'x-forwarded-host': 'www.example.com',\r\n        'x-forwarded-server': 'www.example.com',\r\n        connection: 'Keep-Alive' }\r\n"
3822,'','[Feature] New Post Settings Menu\nThe new PSM design is being constructed here: https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost-UI/issues/99, markup is [here](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost-UI/blob/f7c1dee7880877204b901a4729d05d39878788ab/docs/psm.html).\r\n\r\nIt looks like this:\r\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/120485/3943035/cadcadc0-2584-11e4-8a47-5abe1402cda5.png)\r\n\r\nAnd works like this:\r\n\r\n![](http://f.cl.ly/items/0Q3y1C3w3o461k02473F/psm.gif)\r\n\r\nThe new menu is more complex that the old version, as it has extensible sub-screens. There will likely be a number of child issues to implement the advanced functionality in Ember, as well as to implement each of the new features:\r\n\r\n- [x] Reimplement current PSM in new form #3936\r\n- [ ] Add sub menu functionality #3937\r\n- [ ] Post image upload #3885\r\n- [ ] Meta data screen #3939\r\n- [ ] DRY up closing of post rendering (https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/pull/3965#issuecomment-55117703)\r\n\r\nThese sub issues are ready to start '
