3814,'','Object #<Object> has no method \'exists\'\nI went to configure mail settings for my self-hosted Ghost instance and upon restarting the service Ghost won\'t start. When trying to manually restart it myself the following is what I get\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ npm start\r\n\r\n> ghost@0.5.0 start /var/www/ghost\r\n> node index\r\n\r\n\r\nnpm ERR! ghost@0.5.0 start: `node index`\r\nnpm ERR! Exit status 1\r\nnpm ERR! \r\nnpm ERR! Failed at the ghost@0.5.0 start script.\r\nnpm ERR! This is most likely a problem with the ghost package,\r\nnpm ERR! not with npm itself.\r\nnpm ERR! Tell the author that this fails on your system:\r\nnpm ERR!     node index\r\nnpm ERR! You can get their info via:\r\nnpm ERR!     npm owner ls ghost\r\nnpm ERR! There is likely additional logging output above.\r\nnpm ERR! System Linux 3.2.0-24-virtual\r\nnpm ERR! command "/usr/bin/node" "/usr/bin/npm" "start"\r\nnpm ERR! cwd /var/www/ghost\r\nnpm ERR! node -v v0.6.12\r\nnpm ERR! npm -v 1.3.21\r\nnpm ERR! code ELIFECYCLE\r\nnpm ERR! \r\nnpm ERR! Additional logging details can be found in:\r\nnpm ERR!     /var/www/ghost/npm-debug.log\r\nnpm ERR! not ok code undefined\r\nnpm ERR! not ok code 1\r\n$ node index\r\n\r\nnode.js:201\r\n        throw e; // process.nextTick error, or \'error\' event on first tick\r\n              ^\r\nTypeError: Object #<Object> has no method \'exists\'\r\n    at loadConfig (/var/www/ghost/core/bootstrap.js:129:8)\r\n    at startGhost (/var/www/ghost/core/index.js:19:5)\r\n    at Object.<anonymous> (/var/www/ghost/index.js:8:1)\r\n    at Module._compile (module.js:441:26)\r\n    at Object..js (module.js:459:10)\r\n    at Module.load (module.js:348:32)\r\n    at Function._load (module.js:308:12)\r\n    at Array.0 (module.js:479:10)\r\n    at EventEmitter._tickCallback (node.js:192:41)\r\n```\r\n\r\nI am not sure why this would happen. I switched my config.js to the example one that is included and changed the URL to be what it should. That made no difference. I reinstalled the 0.5 core and that made no difference. It was working before today after the 0.5 upgrade. '
3813,'',"Markdown tab not working\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nThe markdown tab on the editor doesn't appear to be working. Once you click the preview tab to check your markdown work... you can't get back to your markdown! D: [Video of bug (Dropbox)](https://www.dropbox.com/s/mnkodg71jqzrjxc/tj9.mp4)\r\n\r\n1. Start new post (Small screen size)\r\n2. Write markdown\r\n3. Click preview tab\r\n4. Try and get back to markdown via markdown tab\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master (latest commit: 02ca955a00cc6bb79055ded125106333080c35cb)\r\n* Client OS: Windows 8.1 Pro\r\n* Server OS: Windows 8.1 Pro (local)\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.29\r\n* Browser: Chrome 36.0.1985.143\r\n* Database: SQLite"
