3796,'','GitHub backend as a database connection\nThe idea is to connect a GitHub repository as a database.\r\n\r\n[ ] Read-only access to a public GitHub repository\r\n[ ] Read-only access to a private GitHub repository\r\n[ ] Read-write access to a GitHub repository\r\n\r\n## Use Case\r\n\r\nFor a content-heavy website (with a Ghost blog) I\'m considering writing all content in Markdown. This of course includes the blog based on Ghost. As I\'m a big fan of version control and other publishing platforms also work from GitHub repositories (see list below), I\'d like to see this for Ghost as well.\r\n\r\n## Inspirations\r\n\r\nThese platforms use GitHub as a source: (GaaS? :) )\r\n\r\n- http://gist.io/\r\n- http://www.roughdraft.io/\r\n- https://www.gitbook.io/\r\n- https://pages.github.com/\r\n\r\n(I searched for existing issues with "github backend" and did not find one, feel free to close this if there is a duplicate.)'
