3778,'','Allow for configuration-values that are accessible by the templates\n> This issue sprung from the discussion at [irc](http://107.20.237.151:8081/logs/%23ghost/20140814#am25420).\r\n\r\nOne of the pain-points with templates as they work in Ghost today, is that whenever I want to use someone\'s template (or make a template) that has google analytics, or disqus or whatever, I actually have to change the template-code to make this work.\r\n\r\nI propose adding a key to the config-object (named `template` or something akin) that allows for setting configuration-properties that are accessible in the templates. For instance, say I had in my `config.js`:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nproduction: {\r\n    // todays keys omitted for simplicity\r\n    "template": {\r\n        "disqus": "some-disqus-key"\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd then in my template I could do this:\r\n\r\n```html\r\n{{#if conf.disqus}}\r\n    {{! this only runs if conf.disqus exists and has a value }}\r\n    {{> disqus}}\r\n{{/if}}\r\n```'
