3718,'',"Add {{asset}} helper for client side\nThe server currently has an `{{asset}}` helper that lets us get around not knowing what subdirectory ghost will be put into when we hard-code our images (`/ghost/assets/img/some-image.png` vs `/somesubdirectory/that/the/user/specified/ghost/assets/img/some-image.png`).\r\n\r\nAt the moment, the client is getting around this using the `ghost-paths` util, which just has a function that we use from our JS side of things. It would be great if we could also have a tool to use in templates, so that we don't have to bind everything through a model or controller first!\r\n\r\nI bring this up because it's blocking #3155 , and I'm hoping to shirk some work off onto someone else :D"
