3677,'','sqlite - Cannot import from 0.3.3 to 0.5.0\nTesting coming from #3286\r\n\r\nSummary of Issue \r\n------------------------------- \r\n\r\nExporting Ghost 0.3.3 and importing to 0.5.0 failes\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce \r\n------------------------------- \r\n\r\nI started up a fresh copy of 0.3.3 and did the following\r\n\r\n* created 2 posts with text (nothing special here)\r\n* created 1 draft\r\n* went through general and user settings and made sure everything was set\r\n* went to debug page and exported\r\n* started up a fresh copy of 0.5.0 and went to debug page and tried to import\r\n\r\nObserved result \r\n------------------------------- \r\n\r\n![screen shot 2014-08-07 at 9 56 59 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/7192387/3852976/fb9cbc70-1eb8-11e4-9247-96eafbed92ac.png)\r\n\r\nHere is the log from the import: https://gist.github.com/andyboutte/a86d7a0d9e6d17e66b3a\r\n\r\nHere is a copy of my Ghost 0.3.3 export: https://www.dropbox.com/s/otb7w0euy92gbst/GhostData-0.3.3.json\r\n\r\nAdditional Information \r\n-------------------------------\r\n\r\nClient OS: Mac OS X 10.9.4\r\nServer OS: Mac OS X 10.9.4\r\nNode Version: v0.10.21\r\nGhost Build Number: 0.5.0 rc2\r\nLatest Commit:\r\nGhost Database: SQLite3\r\nBrowser: Chrome 36.0.1985.125'
3676,'ErisDS','Bug: Jquery.js not include in theme\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nWhen I use `{{ghost_foot}}` it\'s returns `<script src="/public/jquery.js?v=a537d2d61d"></script>`, but file not found. When I go to `/core/built/public` I see only `jquery.min.js`. When I renamed it all works fine.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n1. Go and use theme which requires correct `jquery.js` for work. \r\n2. And it\'s not work.\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0 rc2 (latest commit: a65cc15e569643a16e79c88987d3f6fdd2603145)\r\n* Client OS: Mac OS X 10.9.4\r\n* Server OS: CentOS 7 x64\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.30\r\n* Browser: Chrome 36.0.1985.125\r\n* Database: SQLite'
3675,'','Bug: Mobile Admin - User Settings "New User" and "Back" Covered\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nDevice: iPhone 4 and iPhone 5S\r\n\r\nWhen on the /ghost/settings/users page on an iphone, the top buttons are covered by the black bar. So you cannot invite users or hit the back button. If you scroll up you can see them, but they are not clickable.\r\n\r\n![img_1874](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3852851/ea17159e-1eb4-11e4-8604-f3d14afde7e9.PNG)\r\n![img_8993](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3852852/ebe0fc00-1eb4-11e4-97c7-002c33875b18.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Open /ghost/settings/users on an iPhone\r\n2. You will see that it is covered up\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0-rc2\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n* Local'
3674,'',"Bug: Can Leave Settings/General Page After Making Changes w/o Saving\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nWhen you make a change on the settings/general page, and then hit the button to go to the home page without saving, there is no popup and none of the changes were saved. If you make a change and click on the content tab though, and then go back to the settings page without refreshing, the option will still be clicked like it saved, but on refresh, it will go back to its original state.\r\n\r\nHere is an example of this:\r\n\r\n![settings save](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3852765/60e1640c-1eb2-11e4-8cf6-794b64b9a3ff.gif)\r\n\r\nIt should either save automatically, or pop up some alert like on the posts to let you know you are leaving without saving. With a lot of other changes like the static page toggle, and ability to change the slug being automatic, you get in the habit of just clicking and expecting it to change and do not realize that it didn't save until later.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Go to settings/general\r\n2. Make a change and then click on the home button\r\n3. Go back, and the change will not have been saved\r\n\r\nAnd for it to look like it worked:\r\n\r\n1. Go to settings/general\r\n2. Make a change and then go to the content tab\r\n3. Click on the settings tab now and you will see the change is still there\r\n4. Refresh the page, and it will go back to the way it was without having saved the change.\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0-rc2\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n* Local"
3673,'',"Bug: Invite Many of the Same User at Once\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nThis could be related to my last issue #3672, but if you hit enter as it is hanging, you can then click on the send button and create a 2nd user. You can also just sit there pressing enter as many times as you can to create many users all with the same username.\r\n\r\n![invite click](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3852575/9f2f2636-1ead-11e4-80c0-bcffdfa2c3b6.gif)\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Enter in the new user's email address\r\n2. Press enter rapidly and many users will get made until dialog is gone\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0-rc2\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n* Local"
3672,'','Bug: Send User Invite Needs To Close Faster On Pressing Enter\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nWhen inviting a user, if you hit enter, the dialog box just kinda hangs there. It should really close immediately.\r\n\r\n![dialog hanging](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3852540/e9f8e9aa-1eac-11e4-9c0f-8836f7166ebd.gif)\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Invite a new user and hit enter, the box will sit there for a second or two\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0-rc2\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n* Local'
3671,'','Bug: Pagination Can Be Set to 0 and No Pagination Will Happen\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nSimilar to #3641 but in the other direction. You can set pagination to 0, and then it looks like no pagination will happen. It will just load all the posts.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Go to blog.com/ghost/settings/general/\r\n2. Change pagination to 0\r\n3. Save and it will load all the posts on the home page\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0-rc2\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n* Local'
