3646,'','Lock accounts based on IP & Username\ncloses #3545\r\n- Repeated login tries by one user are only counted once, keeping a\r\nsingle user from locking out a whole IP range (implementation according\r\nto @sebgie).'
3645,'','Possible Bug: Permalink Just Appending The Next Number if a Post Exists\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nThis may be how the permalink feature is built to work, but if you have a test post with the link "test" and then try to make a different post "test" it will just make it "test-2". So if you make another post, and try to make the url "test-2", it will make it "test-2-2". Just thought maybe its better to just throw an error and have them choose something? Obv whatever you guys think is best including it the way it is. Not really a big deal at all.\r\n\r\n![permilink just auto chooses a number](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3836050/91878574-1dcb-11e4-928d-2efec6921d57.gif)\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Create a post with the url "test"\r\n2. Try to give another post the url "test" and it will make the change\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0-rc2\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n* Local'
3644,'','Bug: Adding \'/edit\' at End of Post is Case Sensitive\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nThis may be entirely how it is supposed to work, but right now, if you add "/edit" to the end of the post, it will take you to the editor, like it should. But, if you add "/Edit", "/EDIT", etc it will take you to a 404. Just thought it should prob have all of them take you to the same place.\r\n\r\n![slash edit case sensitive](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3836023/f7468eb0-1dca-11e4-8fce-8d08de693795.gif)\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Open any post\r\n2. Add "/EDIT" to the end of the url\r\n3. This will take you to a 404.\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0-rc2\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n* Local'
3643,'','Bug: "Are you sure you want to leave" Not Popping Up on Title Change\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nWhen you change the title information of a post, and then try to change the page, it will let you instead of popping up with the "Are you sure you want to leave this page?" alert. The alert works with the content and the tags, but not with the title.\r\n\r\n![no page alert title change](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3836018/b6b68f08-1dca-11e4-8096-8b59cffd9870.gif)\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Open any post in the editor\r\n2. Change the Title of the post\r\n3. Hit any link and it will take you directly there\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0-rc2\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n* Local'
3642,'',"Bug: Change Author Doesn't Throw an Alert\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nWhen changing who the author is of a post, no alert is shown. I am not 100% sure if it is supposed to, but everything else normally does, so I am guessing it should.\r\n\r\n![no change author alert](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3836005/68d7899a-1dca-11e4-803e-3479cece0ab1.gif)\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Open any post in the editor\r\n2. Toggle who the author is\r\n3. No alert will pop up\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0-rc2\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n* Local"
3641,'','Bug: Pagination Says "Less than 1000" but 1000 Works\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nI know this is suuuper picky, and def not pressing, but when you try to make pagination over 1000 pages, it says to make it "less than 1000", but then 1000 works. So, either needs to be re-worded, or changed to 999\r\n\r\n![less than 1000 pagination](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3835995/3b6a933a-1dca-11e4-8c01-940413e54a41.png)\r\n![less than 1000 pagination 1001](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3835996/3b6b6184-1dca-11e4-8c24-de0e1eed2d7c.png)\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Change Pagination to 1000 posts and it will save\r\n2. Change Pagination to 1001 posts and it will say make less than 1000\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0-rc2\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n* Local'
3640,'',"Bug: Static Page Toggle Doesn't Throw Alert\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nWhen you hit the toggle to make a page static or not, it does not throw an alert either way\r\n\r\n![no static page popup](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3835975/ec2273f6-1dc9-11e4-9a94-161a3c1e74b2.gif)\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Open any post in the editor\r\n2. Toggle Static Page\r\n3. No alert will be shown\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0-rc2\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n* Local"
3639,'','Cannot login after upgrade to 0.5 RC2\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nI upgraded my Ghost installation from 0.4.2 to 0.5 RC2 and after that cannot login anymore.\r\nAt first I get a "Please enter a password" warning even if a password was inserted by autocompletion and when I enter the password again I get a new warning but with no text at all. \r\nWhen I copy an access token from a fresh installation I am logged in and can use it but even if I use the password change feature I cannot login after a logout.\r\nAn import of my exported json file is also not possible because of "Validation (isEmptyOrURL) failed for website".\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Upgrade from 0.4.2 to 0.5 RC2\r\n2. Try to login\r\n3. Get warning/error message\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5 RC2\r\n* Client OS: Windows 7\r\n* Server OS: Debian Wheezy\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.29\r\n* Browser: Firefox 31\r\n* Database: SQLite'
3638,'',"Can't log in after migrating from 0.4 to 0.5RC2.\nTrying to log in causes a '500 Internal server error'. Password reset causes to '504 Gateway Time-out'\r\n\r\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nTrying to log in after upgrading Ghost from 0.4 to 0.5 leads to an Internal server error. Trying to log in causes a '500 Internal server error'. Password reset causes a '504 Gateway Time-out'\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Upgrade Ghost installation from 0.4 release 0.5RC2\r\n2. Try to login.\r\n3. Try to login again, and again. Cry.\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master (tag: 0.5.0-rc2)\r\n* Client OS: Mac OS X 10.9.4\r\n* Server OS: Ubuntu 12.04.3 LTS\r\n* Node Version: v0.10.20\r\n* Browser: Chrome 38.0.2107.3\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n\r\n"
3637,'','Add excerpt as page meta description on posts\n- Meta description now returns something on post views: an excerpt of\r\nwhole words under the recommended 160 characters.\r\n- Added block comments to meta title and description helpers\r\n- Simplified conditional logic in for this.RelativeUrl in both helpers'
3636,'','Tabindex for editing new post vs existing post\nNew post:\r\n\r\nCursor should be automatically active inside the `title` field when the editor loads (this works).\r\n\r\nEditing an existing post:\r\n\r\nThe cursor should not automatically be active in any area. Currently the behaviour is the same as with a new post. The problem with this is that with a long title (longer than the width of the title box) the cursor is automatically placed at the end, effectively showing you the 2nd half of the title and cutting off the first half.\r\n\r\nAlso: there is no UX reason that editing a post indicates the next action I would like to complete is to edit the title.\r\n\r\nThis is not a blocker and can be punted to 0.5.x if required.'
3635,'',"Content management keyboard navigation has no endings\nOn the content management screen, use the up/down arrows to navigate between posts. Go all the way to the top, and press up again.\r\n\r\nExpected behaviour: Nothing happens. You have reached the top of the list.\r\n\r\nActual behaviour: The selection moves to the last post in the list.\r\n\r\nSame thing happens in reverse (pressing down arrow on last post goes to first post).\r\n\r\nThis is not a blocker. If it's anything less than a 2 minute fix, punt to 0.5.x."
3634,'','Bug: Mobile Editor – End of the Post Covered by Tag Footer\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nDevice: iPhone 4\r\n\r\nWhen you scroll down to the bottom of your post, the last little bit is covered by the footer. You can pull it up, but it will bounce back down\r\n\r\n![post_covered1](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3831639/b6923b92-1d95-11e4-8ab3-7678872e8cbd.PNG)\r\n![post_covered2](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3831638/b691a6d2-1d95-11e4-97f8-03bd07ec632f.PNG)\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Open any post\r\n2. Scroll to the bottom and the post will be covered\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0RC\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Browser: Safari\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n* Local'
3633,'','Fix revoke user invite and user.destroy\nfixes #3630\r\n- Extend user adapter in ember to load users with status: all\r\n- Fix user.destroy by loading all users with status: all'
3632,'','Feature Request: Administrator Should Be Able To Transfer Ownership\nI think that an admin should be able to transfer who is the owner. There are not really any special privileges that come along with being the owner compared to the admin, so I think the they should be able to transfer if they want to. Might help if a company or whoever has a bad break off with the owner employee, so they can still transfer ownership and delete that user without needing access to email or their password.'
3631,'',"[Suggestion] Blog Description\nWith 0.5, Ghost is becoming multi-user. So I'm thinking the default blog description shouldn't be tied down to the blog owner. Just an idea I guess."
3630,'','Bug: Unable to Revoke Invited User\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nCannot Revoke an Invited User\r\n\r\n![revoke user](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3829200/5eff81bc-1d7e-11e4-899f-67dc13b3be26.gif)\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1.\tInvite a new user\r\n2.\tTry and revoke\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0RC\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n* Local'
3629,'','Transition to signin with error message on invalid token not 500 error\n\r\ncloses #3548\r\n- Add error to hidenav, removes menubar from error screen.\r\n- Wrap atob() in a try/catch\r\n- Added regex to try and validate if params.token at least looks like base64'
3628,'',"Add open class to popover buttons\nRef#3603\r\n- Popover Buttons now have an `open` class applied to them when their popover is open\r\n- The open class is removed from the popover button at the start of the popover's fadeout\r\n- Consolidated common code into popover-mixin"
3627,'',"Update Notification. To dismiss, or not to dismiss?\nTo date, the update check notification has always been non-dismissable. It doesn't have a close button and it's not meant to ever go away.\r\n\r\nIn 0.5, it does have a close button and can be dismissed, only to pop back up if you refresh or re-log in. \r\n\r\nThe update notification is intended to be annoying. People need to upgrade, not dismiss it! On the other hand, it stops you from being able to navigate on mobile, and being able to dismiss it, even though it's only temporarily, might let people complete a task on their mobile successfully.\r\n\r\nDecision time..."
3626,'',"Mobile Navigation gone awry\nI'm seeing a lot of brokenness in the mobile navigation. Once you get passed #3623 and try to navigate around:\r\n\r\nBroken User Profile Flow:\r\n\r\n1. Open the burger menu\r\n2. Open the user menu\r\n3. Click on your profile\r\n4. The menu doesn't close\r\n5. Tapping the top right corner where the burger is saves stuff even though you can't see the save button\r\n6. Can't seem to get out of the menu\r\n\r\nBroken Settings Flow:\r\n\r\n1. Open the burger menu\r\n2. Click settings\r\n3. Click general\r\n4. No back button or save button, although tapping the top right corner saves and tapping the top left corner goes back.\r\n5. Go to settings/users - no back button\r\n6. Drop down into a user - still no back button\r\n\r\nNote: sometimes if you drag or open a menu, the buttons reappear from wherever they are hiding.\r\n\r\n### Technical details: \r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5 RC2\r\n* Device: iPhone 4S (iOS6)\r\n"
3624,'',"Bug: Mobile Editor - First Load in Admin, Hamburger Doesn't Work\n### Issue Summary\r\nDevice: iPhone 4, iPad 4th gen\r\n\r\nAfter a fresh install of 0.5, when you create an account and log in the first time from mobile, the hamburger will not work. It will just flash. If you refresh the page, it will then work\r\n\r\n![hamburger](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3827360/7e9674b0-1d6d-11e4-9885-f3c907132724.gif)\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Install Fresh 0.5\r\n2. Create owner with mobile device\r\n3. Try and click on the hamburger\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0-rc2\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Browser: Safari\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n* local"
3623,'',"Ghost icon is not clickable\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nThe Ghost icon in the upper left corner is not clickable right after login. If I refresh the browser it works as expected. This is annoying on desktop and prevents opening the 'burger' menu on mobile.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Go to /ghost/signin and sign in\r\n2. click the icon -> nothing happens\r\n3. refresh the browser while authenticated\r\n4. click the icon -> opens /ghost\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: RC2\r\n* Client OS: Mac OS X 10.9 / iOS 7\r\n* Server OS: Vagrant\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.26\r\n* Browser: Chrome 36.0.1985.125 / Safari for iOS\r\n* Database: SQLite"
3622,'',"0.5.0 Release Candidate 2 - Ready for Testing\nThere is now a [second release candidate of 0.5.0](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/releases/tag/0.5.0-rc2) published and ready for testing.\r\n\r\nIf you are able to do some testing, this would be much appreciated :doughnut: :cake:\r\n\r\nIf you find any bugs, please raise them as separate issues according to the [contributing guidelines](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md), thank you :+1: \r\n\r\nIf you complete successful testing, please let us know by adding a comment here detailing what you tested and on what environment, covering relevant things like OS, browser, prod/dev mode, database etc.\r\n\r\nSome important areas for testing:\r\n\r\nAspects of Ghost not often used during development:\r\n- production environment\r\n- MySQL\r\n- Ghost as npm module\r\n- sub directories\r\n- the update process\r\n\r\nImportant things that have changed:\r\n- every single detail of the admin!!\r\n- multi-user features (invites, signup, etc)\r\n- permissions of the various user roles\r\n- editing on mobile\r\n- so much more I'd be here til Christmas listing it\r\n\r\nThanks! :balloon: :balloon: "
3621,'','Fix token refresh\nno issue\r\n- spam prevention causes token refresh to return an error'
3620,'','Cleaner spam prevention error messages\ncloses #3589\r\n\r\n- Full error messages appear in stderr\r\n- Clean error messages for user'
3619,'','API endpoint for configuration\nTo make configuration values available to the client (see #3568) we need another API endpoint to read and browse config values.\r\n\r\n- `GET /ghost/api/v0.1/configuration/`: all available config values\r\n- `GET /ghost/api/v0.1/configuration/<config-name>`: one value, identified by config-name\r\n\r\nResponse format:\r\n```\r\n{\r\n    configuration: [{\r\n        key:<config-name>,\r\n        value:<config-value>\r\n    }]\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe configuration endpoint should only return a subset of available config values:\r\n\r\n- `filestorage` (boolean from `config.env.fileStorage`)\r\n- `apps` (boolean from `config.env.apps`)\r\n- `version` (string, semver from `packages.json`)\r\n- `environment` (string from `NODE_ENV`)\r\n- `database` (string from `config.env.database.client`)\r\n- `mail` (sring from `config.env.mail.transport`)\r\n\r\nEvery authenticated user is allowed to read and browse these values.'
