3612,'',"Persistent notifications go away on refresh\nPersistent notifications are pulled down before authentication. Not sure why this is, but it means that if you refresh the admin, they don't appear until you log in again.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Cause a persistent notification by removing mail config or setting `displayUpdateNotification` to 0.5.0 in the settings table\r\n2. Restart Ghost, then log out and log in\r\n3. You'll see the notification\r\n4. Refresh, it will disappear\r\n5. Log out and back in, it'll appear again"
3611,'','Adding missing body class for author pages\ncloses #3606'
3610,'',"Modifying mail configuration to check for existence of environment variables\nAzure has a cool feature where you can deploy a website straight from source control including a Github fork.  To use this feature with Ghost would require that config.js be checked into the Github source repository.  Checking in security credentials like the username/password of your email provider is bad security practice.\r\n\r\nI'm motivated to get Ghost to the point where you can just fork your repository, drop in some templates (if needed), and publish a website on Azure.  This is a clean approach that will let Ghost users keep up to date with new releases easily and encourages them to 'Use The Source, Luke'.  Azure has an 'easy Ghost deploy' wizard, but it's already out of date and that makes me :-(\r\n\r\nI would like to change Ghost's behavior so it doesn't require config.js to be modified for a simple installation.  First step in this path is to get email working without having to drop the configuration and credentials into a source file.  I would like to modify Ghost so it searches process.environment for these settings.\r\n\r\nMy proposed spec is that if the environment variables EMAIL_SERVICE, EMAIL_USERNAME, and EMAIL_PASSWORD are set that config.development.mail and config.production.mail data structures would be populated using these values.  This would not replace the settings in config.js -- if the mail datastructure was set there it would take precedence.\r\n\r\nLet me know if you are open to this change and if so I will code it up and submit a pull request."
3609,'','Change config.example.js to check for PORT environment variable first\n...then use default, simplifies Ghost configuration for IISNode.\r\n\r\nThis removes a mandatory step for deploying into Azure while maintaining compatibility with other enviornments and following NodeJS best practices for listening ports.'
3608,'','Fix Azure compatibility issue around stdin in Gruntfile.js\nThis is a small fix to an Azure deployment compatibility issue, as discussed in https://github.com/projectkudu/kudu/issues/885.'
3607,'',"Lock accounts based on IP & Username\ncloses #3545\r\n- Adds username as a condition in the rate limiter, thus preventing one\r\nuser to lock out a whole range of users with the same IP.\r\n- Changed default rate limit to 5 (per @sebgie's comment)"
3606,'','Body Class missing on Author Archives\n## Summary\r\n\r\nIrrespective of whether author.hbs template exists, there are no body classes added for Author Archives.\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Visit a author archive page e.g. http://localhost:2368/author/harish-chouhan/\r\n2. View the source code.\r\n\r\n## Additional Information\r\n\r\nI tested this when using a custom theme as well as Casper, and tried with and without the author.hbs template. \r\n\r\n## System Information\r\n\r\nUser Role: Owner / Author\r\nClient OS: Windows 8.1\r\nNode Version: v0.10.28 (x64)\r\nGhost Build Number: 0.5.0 rc1\r\nGhost Database: SQLite3\r\nBrowser: Chrome Version 36.0.1985.125 m'
3605,'','Author loses access to post if owner edits & updates it\nThis is my first time reporting a bug, so would appreciate help in doing it properly.\r\n\r\n## Summary\r\n\r\nWhen a owner of a Ghost blog, edits and saves a post created by a user with Author privileges, the author of the post is changed to the owner and the original author is no longer able to access the post.\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Invite a user with author permission\r\n2. Login as the new user and create & publish a post\r\n3. Logout and login back as Owner\r\n4. Edit the post created earlier and save changes.\r\n5. Logout and Login back with the new user account (with author role) and the post would not be accessible anymore.\r\n\r\n## Additional Information ##\r\n\r\nUser Role: Owner / Author\r\nClient OS: Windows 8.1\r\nNode Version: v0.10.28 (x64)\r\nGhost Build Number: 0.5.0 rc1\r\nGhost Database: SQLite3\r\nBrowser: Chrome Version 36.0.1985.125 m'
3604,'','Swap notification close link for a button\nNo issue\r\n\r\n- Swap out notification <a> close link for <button> (we gain a native hover state)\r\n- Remove element selector from tests, to is only looks for the class now\r\n\r\nNo style changes are needed, but https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost-UI/commit/087868c1c99b84e0c5b9701202418ce7b477b18c was done in tandem'
3603,'','Broken dropdown toggle icon\nI suspect this is ember rather than GUI/CSS ? The dropdown caret should spin around to the downward orientation again when it is clicked again to close the menu.\r\n\r\nOpen menu, click *outside the menu* functions correctly (menu closes, arrow spins down)\r\n\r\nOpen menu, click on the dropdown icon again is broken (menu closes, arrow stays pointed up)\r\n\r\n![fuckmenu](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/120485/3816746/42dc3b7c-1cd1-11e4-8d9e-7b002c19e3b4.gif)\r\n'
3602,'','Add catch handlers to import tests.\n**Only changes tests**\r\n\r\nRefs #3473\r\n* Some tests are checking to make sure errors by using a\r\n  catch handler on the test.  When assertions fail done()\r\n  is never called and results in a mocha timeout, which makes\r\n  it harder to see the cause of the failure.'
