3589,'',"Login throttling error notification is too 'developery'\nThe text in the error notification you get when repeatedly logging in with incorrect details is a bit weird. It says `'Only 5 tries per IP address every 3600 seconds.'`\r\n\r\nIt would be much easier to understand if it said `every hour` or `ever 60 minutes`.\r\n\r\n![cloudrop 4 aug 2014 22-59-01 4 aug 2014 22-59-02](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/390392/3804227/6780377a-1c23-11e4-8d0e-e1f3acc2ec4e.png)\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Log in with incorrect details, at least 5 times\r\n2. Try to log in again (with correct or incorrect details) and see error\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\nText is at [/core/server/middleware/middleware.js#L168](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/blob/59953c661034d99108da87a7a9b8504733c003b0/core/server/middleware/middleware.js#L168)\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master (latest commit: 8bfbf132483b6d63af578ee5dc71ce40343105ba)\r\n* Client OS: iOS 7.1.2\r\n* Server OS: Mac OS X 10.9.4\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.28\r\n* Browser: Chrome iOS Safari\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n"
