3572,'','Ensure keyboard navigation matches custom post sorting.\nNo issue.\n\nSince we are using a custom sort order for our post listing, we need to use that sort order when determining the next post (for up and down keyboard shortcuts).'
3571,'','Show "Make Owner" only if displayed user is admin\ncloses #3570\r\n- Added ‘controller.user.isAdmin’ as an condition for displaying the\r\n“make owner” option'
3570,'',"'Make Owner' for administrators only\nOur current API implementation allows only administrators to assigned the owner role. The option to assign the owner role to an author or editor is shown in the cog atm. The API denies the request as expected, but for better UX it would be good to remove the option.\r\n\r\n@felixrieseberg Is this something for you?"
3569,'','fix most recent post stolen by the last logged in user AND only show active users in post-settings-menu drop-down\n2 bugs in 1\r\n- most recent post stolen by the last logged in user\r\n- only show active users in post-settings-menu drop-down\r\n\r\nfixes #3549 fixes #3528\r\n- instead of grabbing and setting the author after fetching the list of users, get the author info from the models "author" property and set it when that value returns. (3549)\r\n- added filter to the PSM\'s "authors" attribute to only display active users (3528)'
3568,'novaugust','[Feature] "About Ghost" page\nSee tryghost/ghost-ui#23 for design specs.\r\n\r\nIt would be wonderful to have this in with 0.5.1.\r\n\r\n@PaulAdamDavis added the HTMLz in [`core/client/html/about-page.html`](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/blob/master/core/client/html/about-page.html)'
3567,'',"Return to invite new user; invite multiple users in one go\nCloses #3533, Closes #3547, Closes #3531 \r\n- invite-new-user always resets role to author now, allowing for multiple invites on one load\r\n- Added confirm action when hitting return in INUModal's email input\r\n- Don't pass users as the model to invite-new-user-modal\r\n- Move invite-new-user reset to a `finally` clause\r\n- invite-new-user always closes on a confirm"
3566,'','Display error for invalid email on user invite\ncloses #3531\r\n- Created invite validator checking for valid email format\r\n- Included said validator in "invite new user" modal, checking the email\r\nbefore the user record is created'
3565,'','Bug: Create User Page Still Loads on Revoked Invites\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nAfter you have invited a user, even if you revoke the invite, the page still loads like they can sign up. It does not allow them to create their account, but still, it should error out I would think.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Invite new user\r\n2. Revoke that user\r\n3. Click on the link that was sent and it will load the page like they can sign in\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0RC\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Ubuntu 12.04\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n* DigitalOcean and local'
3564,'','Bug: Pressing Enter on Sending New User Invitation Doesn\'t Trigger the Send\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nWhen you are trying to invite a new user and type in their email, if you hit enter, nothing happens. It should trigger the "Send Invitation Now"\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Enter in email to invite new user\r\n2. Hit enter and nothing will happen\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0RC\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Ubuntu 12.04\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n* DigitalOcean and local'
3563,'','Bug: Can Revoke Invite after Accepted to Delete User\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nWhen you invite a new user, and they go and sign up. If you have not refreshed the page, and you click on revoke invite, it will delete that user\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Invite new user\r\n2. Open up new browser with link and sign up\r\n3. Go back to the admin page where user was invited\r\n4. Hit revoke and that that user will be deleted\r\n\r\n![revoke access](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3784788/97ce4750-19bc-11e4-80d2-62e1e6e079b4.gif)\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0RC\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Ubuntu 12.04\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n* DigitalOcean and local'
3562,'','Update Ghost-UI with grunt init\nCloses #3554\r\n\r\n- Adds a shell command to update Ghost-UI'
3561,'','Admin isn\'t shown "make owner" option\ncloses #3558\r\n- Replaced canAssignRoles as "show user" conditional with new\r\n"canMakeOwner"'
3560,'','Descriptive error if user by mail not found.\ncloses #3537\r\n- Replaced generic NotFound error with descriptive NotFoundError.'
3559,'','Fix failure in Post API tests.\nRefs #3473\r\n* Make sure test is checking the post it expects by verifying\r\n  the post id in the results.'
3558,'',"Bug: 'Make Owner' drop down is shown for admins\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nThe 'Make Owner' drop down is shown when logged in as admin.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Log in as admin\r\n2. Navigate to the user management page\r\n3. Select a user\r\n4. Click on the cog -> 'Make Owner' is shown\r\n\r\nThe permission system prevents an admin do make another user the owner of the blog but for a better UX the option shouldn't be available at all.\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master (latest commit: 41493e1ccca68ac8913bdf694fe23a2d88f9dd2c)\r\n* Client OS: Mac OS X 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Vagrant\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.26\r\n* Browser: Chrome 36.0.1985.125\r\n* Database: SQLite"
3557,'','Add missing model to template render.\nCloses #3530, Refs #3474\r\n* Cleanup from #3474 which stopped passing the model into\r\n  the render template call.'
3556,'','Include development assets in release build.\nCloses #3498\r\n\r\n* Verified that the built .zip file is able to run in both production (`npm start --production`) and development (`npm start`) without running any grunt tasks.'
3555,'','[feature request] Give express server back in promise / Improve Ghost API to manage it programatically\nIn order to manage the lifecycle of a Ghost blog I have to get access to the express server behing Ghost.  \r\n\r\nIn [`ghost/core/server/index.js` ](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/blob/master/core/server/index.js#L310) you return:  \r\n```js\r\n  return deferred.promise;\r\n```\r\n\r\na simple `return deferred.resolve(server)` would do the trick if you consider updating `server` with the return of `server.listen(...)`, but then there are some errors thrown.  \r\nThose errors look like: \r\n\r\n```\r\nERROR: SQLITE_IOERR: disk I/O error, sql: update "settings" set "created_at" = ?, "created_by" = ?, "id" = ?, "key" = ?, "type" = ?, "updated_at" = ?, "updated_by" = ?, "uuid" = ?, "value" = ? where "id" = ?, bindings: Fri Aug 01 2014 15:41:53 GMT+0200 (CEST),1,16,installedApps,app,Fri Aug 01 2014 15:42:21 GMT+0200 (CEST),1,0523c10c-6736-43b1-a9f4-e688a7c78956,[],16\r\n```\r\n\r\nDo you plan on improving Ghost\'s API for those who wants to use it programatically ?'
3554,'',"Ghost-UI doesn't update with `grunt init`\nAfter investigating https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost-UI/issues/87, @halfdan & I figured out that Ghost-UI only gets updated when the version number has changed in `bower.json`.\r\n\r\nRunning `bower update ghost-ui` on `grunt init` seems like the most logical way to solve this, which means Ghost-UI can be updated often.\r\n\r\nHowever, specific versions should be applied to releases.\r\n"
3553,'','Change user menu link to a button\nCloses #3546\r\n\r\n- Change user menu popover toggle from an `<a>` to a `<button>`\r\n- Change tests accordingly'
3552,'',"Database doesn't update\nI'm trying to remove some tags myself and change some slugs. I have downloaded the file `/content/data/ghost.db` from my production server and modify some value with the help of Liya.\r\n\r\nThe problem is that when I upload the modified file on my server, things stays the same. Is there a cache somewhere? How can I see my modifications appear?\r\n\r\nThank you for your help."
3551,'','Proper messaging on password reset\nfixes #3540\r\n- Show proper message when reusing token\r\n- Show message after resetting password'
3550,'','Properly show message when resetting password.\nfixes #3542\r\n- Make notification a delayed notification'
3549,'','Bug: Posts are stolen by the editor\n### Issue Summary\r\nA draft from a user is automatically stolen and switched to the editor upon editor signin. \r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Sign in as an author. Write a post and save as a draft. Check it displays in the content list as written by author.\r\n2. Sign out and sign in as editor. Note the new post from the author, but it is displayed as written by editor, even without any editing or even any action whatsoever.\r\n3. Sign out and sign back in as author. Note the post has disappeared as it belongs to the editor now.\r\n\r\nThe post should not automatically be attributed to the editor without at least the editor editing it, and in my opinion this should only be an explicit change through the post options menu.\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: Ghost 0.5.0 RC1 from github zip file\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9.4\r\n* Server OS: Mac 10.9.4\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.29\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: Sqlite\r\n\r\n![stealingposts](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/321603/3776539/18b15f22-1956-11e4-97d1-5d4911768264.gif)\r\n'
3548,'','Bug: Invalid signup token shows weird 500 screen.\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nUsing an invalid signup token gets you to a strange 500 screen.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Invite user\r\n2. Use signup token but make it invalid (remove characters)\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2014-08-01 at 10 15 39](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/176576/3776451/b40e6994-1954-11e4-9e38-6cf2851a5af5.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master\r\n* Client OS: MacOS\r\n* Server OS: Linux\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.25\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite3'
3547,'','Bug: Inviting multiple users in a row fails\n### Issue Summary\r\nInviting a first user, and then a second fails with no feedback.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Go to settings/users, and invite a user.\r\n2. Notification of successful email is displayed, and user appears on screen in invited user list.\r\n3. Invite a second user. Nothing happens. No error, no success notification, no user in user list.\r\n\r\nAs a side note, it appears navigating elsewhere in the admin and then back to /settings/users to invite does not make any difference. Refreshing the page however does allow another invite to be sent.\r\n\r\nI would expect successive invitations to succeed.\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0 RC1 from zip file on github\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9.4\r\n* Server OS: Mac 10.9.4\r\n* Node Version: v0.10.29\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite\r\n\r\n![multipleusers](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/321603/3776387/9a5dbd48-1953-11e4-9b00-b1b15f968cde.gif)\r\n'
3546,'PaulAdamDavis',"UI: CSS transition + cursor pointer missing for profile missing.\nHello,\r\n\r\n**CSS Transition** \r\n\r\nI'm not 100% sure about the CSS transition when clicking on the top right for the profile drop down. It feels 'slow' to me.\r\n\r\n    animation: fade-in 1s;\r\n\r\nPerhaps it would be a good idea to reduce it down to 0.6 or 0.5? \r\n\r\n**Profile - cursor pointer missing**\r\n\r\nWhen clicking on the profile name in the top right corner. There isn't a pointer icon, just a text selector.\r\n\r\n    .navbar nav li a\r\n       cursor: pointer\r\n\r\nTested on OS X Mavericks 10.9.4\r\nBrowser: Safari Version 7.0.5 (9537.77.4) and Chrome Version 36.0.1985.125"
3544,'sebgie','repeated succesfful login / logout locks you out\nSummary of Issue \r\n------------------------------- \r\n\r\nSuccessfully logging in and out will lock you out\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce \r\n------------------------------- \r\n\r\n* Log in and out 6 times\r\n* trying to log in the 7th time will lock you out\r\n\r\n\r\nObserved result \r\n------------------------------- \r\n\r\n```Only 5 tries per IP address every 3600 seconds.```\r\n\r\n\r\nAdditional Information \r\n-------------------------------\r\n\r\nClient OS: Mac OS X 10.9.4\r\nServer OS: Mac OS X 10.9.4\r\nNode Version: v0.10.21\r\nGhost Build Number: 0.5.0 rc1\r\nLatest Commit:\r\nGhost Database: SQLite3\r\nBrowser: Chrome 36.0.1985.125'
3543,'',"Missing inline code shortcut\nIn 0.5 we switched Ctrl/⌘ + K to be a link as it is in most other applications. As a result, the code shortcut was removed as it used to be:\r\n\r\nCtrl + Shift + K on windows, or ⌘ + K on mac.\r\n\r\nI think the code shortcut needs to be:\r\n\r\nCtrl + Shift + K on windows, and ⌘ + Shift + K on mac. (see https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/wiki/Keyboard-Shortcuts)\r\n\r\nThe code for it is n place in utils/codemirror-shortcuts.js as the style 'code', it just needs wiring up in the utils/editor-shortcuts.js file if everyone is happy with the shortcut cc @JohnONolan "
