3528,'','Bug: Revoke Access From Author, Posts Get Deleted\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nI think this issue could be one of two things:\r\n\r\nWhen you invite someone to be an author, you can then change a post to be under their name. If you then go and revoke their invitation, that post gets completely deleted. So, either they need to accept the invite before they are allowed to have posts moved under them, or all posts are getting deleted when a user is removed. (I have not tested with this with an accepted user yet)\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Invite a new author user\r\n2. Change a post to be under their name\r\n3. Revoke the invitation\r\n4. Go back to content and you will see an error and the post will be gone\r\n\r\n![user delete post](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/3775362/46c36f26-1943-11e4-8f8a-a237135d36fb.gif)\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.5.0RC\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n* Database: SQLite'
