3460,'',"Incorrect / Too many calls to User API \nAs I navigate around the admin with the console open, each screen seems to be making at least one call to:\r\n`http://localhost:2368/ghost/api/v0.1/users/?include=roles`\r\n\r\nI'm going to guess that this ought to be a call to `users/me?include=roles` and that, similarly to the problem we had with Ember data and posts, we've got a bug somewhere due to ember data not liking slug parameters and query parameters in the same url/\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. log in to /ghost in chrome\r\n2. Open the console on the network tab limited to XHR\r\n3. Navigate around the admin and see all of the ?include=roles calls\r\n\r\nI think there are 2 potential problems here. 1 that the URL is incorrect and 2 that the call is being made so frequently.\r\n\r\n### Technical details: \r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master (latest commit:  99cc855)"
