3419,'',"[Thought] Emblem.js instead of raw Handlebars?\nMaybe it would be worth looking into using [Emblem.js](http://emblemjs.com/) or allow an option to switch between raw .hbs and .emblem for theme development? \r\n\r\nIt might be a completely bonkers idea, but considering that Ghost uses Markdown instead of having to write raw HTML, why isn't the experience when crafting Ghost themes not reflected in the same clean way?\r\n\r\nIt IS possible to come very close to a clean solution using Slim, but there are strange quirks and the Handlebars support is a bit weird.\r\n\r\nI am aware that this might require a ridiculous amount of change unless someone comes along and creates either Grunt or Gulp plugins that don't just output raw Javascript.\r\n\r\nOr, to dream a little further, Ghost could have its very own templating language with `.ghost` files that extends Emblem.js, but has some secret Ghost sauce baked in.\r\n\r\nAgain, I know this could be a stupid idea and I apologize beforehand, so please don't bring out the pitchforks. :-)"
