3213,'',"Preparation for lazy loading of models\nThese commits work towards #2170.  They're a step towards that issue's completion as it's a large and complex change  So I'm going to break it up into atomic pieces that can be merged in as we go.\r\n\r\nThe two commit messages tell the full story:\r\n\r\n* Move creation of knex instance to config module\r\n\r\n* Only reference model properties through the models module.\r\nThis frees us up to enforce one single point of access, thus paving\r\nthe way towards allowing us to initialize the models at are request,\r\nand not when it's require().\r\n\r\nThis is in two commits for now for easy reviewing.  \r\n\r\nIf needed I can and will squash them into one commit when approved."
