3187,'',"HTTP API endpoints for retrieving posts via ids and slugs\nCurrently a post can have a slug that is just an integer.  The way the HTTP API is set up, there's no way to disambiguate between a request to find a post via its id or its slug.  For example, `GET /ghost/api/v0.1/posts/15` could be a request for the post with an id of 15 or a post with the slug '15'.\r\n\r\nSome possible solutions:\r\n\r\n* Prohibit slugs from being the same format as ids (i.e, string representations of integers).\r\n\r\n* Only allow retrieval of posts using ids when using the HTTP API.\r\n\r\n* Change the HTTP API endpoints to explicitly specify the type of lookup (id or slug) as part of the path (or maybe even query?).\r\n\r\n* Collapse the two endpoints into one and do a either a first match lookup prioritizing either the id or the slug, or possibly returning all posts that have matching ids and slugs.\r\n\r\n* Something else?\r\n\r\nThe routes in question are here:  https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/blob/master/core/server/routes/api.js#L12"
