3097,'','Users API: advanced browsing 2\nBased on #3086 it has become apparent that it needs to be possible to further filter the results of users.browse. \r\n\r\nOn the admin settings/users screen, an editor can only edit authors, so it is preferable if they only saw the authors in the list. \r\n\r\nThis means we need to be able to request browse to restrict the results by (preferably) who the current user can edit -  `permissions=edit`\r\n\r\nEither way, this is not absolutely critical to delivery of MU, so it is a separate issue to be done at the end if we can.'
3096,'ErisDS','User API Permissions: Restrict based on role\nIn #2264 the permissions for the user API were defined as: \r\n\r\nJSON API                 | Admin | Editor | Author           | NoAuth\r\n-------------------------|-------|--------|------------------|------------------------\r\nusers.browse             | y     | y      | y                | \r\nusers.read               | y     | y      | y                | y\r\nusers.edit               | y     | y      | y (user == self) | \r\nusers.add                | y     | y      |                  | \r\n\r\nThis is not quite correct, and should be:\r\n\r\nJSON API                 | Admin | Editor | Author           | NoAuth\r\n-------------------------|-------|--------|------------------|------------------------\r\nusers.browse             | y     | y   | y     | \r\nusers.read               | y     | y    | y    | y\r\nusers.edit               | y     | y (user == author)     | y (user == self) | \r\nusers.add                | y     | y (user == author)    |                  | \r\n\r\nThis is related to #3080 and #3083'
3095,'',"Mobile editor Markdown & Preview tabs not clickable\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nSomewhere in the Ember rewrite, the ability to **click** the Markdown & Preview tabs in the editor has been lost. They are still tapable on touch screens, but clicking with a mouse does nothing.\r\n\r\nJust to reiterate: Tap on mobile works, click on desktop doesn't.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n1. Open Ghost admin on a desktop browser\r\n2. Resize the window to below 1000px\r\n3. Click the 'Preview' tab\r\n\r\n**Expected Result:**\r\nPreview tab is clicked and you see the rendered markdown\r\n\r\n**Actual Result:**\r\nNothing. No errors, no nothing.\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master (latest commit: 4bc166e2525d21a6ba387f310464afa96416c011)"
3094,'','Ghost editor turns ![foo] into {<1>}![foo] and breaks editing afterwards\nRunning current master.\r\nLooks like the editor turns ![foo] into {<1>}![foo]. After reopening the post this even breaks the editor so you can\'t remove/change the post anymore.\r\n\r\nHow to reproduce:\r\n- Create a new post\r\n- Type: ![foo\r\n- Once you entered ] ghost turns it in: {<1>}![foo] and the preview shows `![foo\r\n- Save draft\r\n- Go to content and open draft again\r\n-> Save/publish is missing and console shows: "Uncaught ReferenceError: Ember is not defined"'
