2992,'',"[Ember.js] Settings: settings-content doesn't get an ID\nIn the old admin, whenever a pane is selected the element with the class `settings-content` gets and ID for the pane.\r\n\r\nIf the general pane is active, then the element gets the id `general`, etc.\r\n\r\nThis is used in the ember tests, but I'm not sure if it's otherwise required for anything - so this probably isn't massively high priority.\r\n\r\n@PaulAdamDavis Can you confirm whether this is needed for anything in Ghost-UI?"
