2969,'',"Update when.js dependency to version 3.2.3\nI think it's worth updating to the latest version (3.2.3) of the when.js promise library.  I know there's been some discussion (#968) of switching to Bluebird but in the interim it would be nice to take advantage of the work that's gone into newer versions of `when`.\r\n\r\nLots of improvements in 3.0+ in terms of performance, memory usage, and logging (unhandled rejections).\r\n(https://github.com/cujojs/when/releases)\r\n\r\nConsiderable improvements in relation to Bluebird according to Bluebird's own benchmarks from where it was at a few months ago: https://github.com/petkaantonov/bluebird/blob/master/benchmark/stats/latest.md\r\n\r\nI've gone through the upgrading from 2.x to 3.x guide (https://github.com/cujojs/when/blob/master/docs/api.md#upgrading-to-30-from-2x) and made the necessary changes (very few), and I've been using it on my development repo for a few weeks now with no issue (and it really is better at catching unhandled rejections)."
2968,'',"Fix slug create and update logic for posts\nSlug handling for posts is still not quite right.  \r\n\r\n* Unneeded slug API calls being made on the Content and Editor screens.\r\n* The title -> slug observer is running all the time when it should only be used on new (never saved) posts.\r\n* It's possible to end up with a new incremented slug (-number) when the original should be used.\r\n\r\n**Changes:**\r\n\r\n* Remove unnecessary calls to the slug endpoint when loading posts on the Content screen.\r\n* Remove unnecessary calls to the slug endpoint after saving a post in the Editor screen.\r\n* Only run the title to slug observer when the post is being created.\r\n* Improved logic for when to update the slug and and also cases where the existing slug should be used.\r\n"
2967,'','Ported settings/apps logic to Ember.\nCloses #2423\r\n\r\n- Created the apps route to fetch apps from server\r\n- Created controller for a single app\r\n- Modified the template of the apps page to use this controller\r\n- Created the Apps model\r\n- Created AppAdapter to use the FixtureAdapter for Ember Data'
2966,'',"Fix trailing slashes output app-wide\ncloses #2963, closes #2964\r\n- override Ember's `HistoryLocation.formatURL`\r\n- remove overridden `HistoryLocation.setURL`\r\n\r\nall thanks to @jgwhite for the `formatURL` Ember code reference."
2965,'','Adds syntax highlighting to Casper via Prism\nThis commit adds two files to Casper: css/prism.css and javascript/prism.js. This comit also adds corresponding changes to  default.hbs. \r\n\r\nI chose Prism for the syntaxing highlighting because it is a lightweight and modern highlighter. The minified version of prism.js includes all language options that are available on the following page: \r\nhttp://prismjs.com/download.html'
2964,'','[Ember.js] Trailing slashes disappear when navigating directly\nWhen navigating to a URL by typing the full URL into the address bar, including the trailing slash, the trailing slash is removed.\r\n\r\nSo, if you go (by typing it in) to `/ghost/ember/` you end up on `/ghost/ember/1/` and if you go to `/ghost/ember` you end up on `/ghost/ember/1/`, and if you go to `/ghost/ember/1` you end up on `ghost/ember/1/` but if you go to `/ghost/ember/1/` you end up on `/ghost/ember/1`.\r\n\r\nIn a more readable format\r\n\r\nTyped - Landed On - Correct?\r\n`/ghost/ember/` - `/ghost/ember/1/` - CORRECT\r\n`/ghost/ember` - `/ghost/ember/1/` - CORRECT\r\n`/ghost/ember/1` - `/ghost/ember/1/` - CORRECT\r\n`/ghost/ember/1/` - `/ghost/ember/1` - INCORRECT\r\n`/ghost/ember/editor` - `/ghost/ember/editor/` - CORRECT\r\n`/ghost/ember/editor/` - `/ghost/ember/editor` - INCORRECT\r\n\r\nThis is true for all routes, but also:\r\n\r\nIf you logout, you land on `/ghost/ember/signin/`\r\n\r\nBut if you try to go to the signin or signup routes with or without the trailing slash, you always end up without although it flashes up with the slash in the middle of the request, again in a simple format:\r\n\r\n`/ghost/ember/signin` - `/ghost/ember/signin` - INCORRECT\r\n`/ghost/ember/signin/` - `/ghost/ember/signin` - INCORRECT\r\n`/ghost/ember/signup` - `/ghost/ember/signup` - INCORRECT\r\n`/ghost/ember/signup/` - `/ghost/ember/signup` - INCORRECT\r\n\r\n'
