2961,'',"Image uploader breaks when contentPath in config.js is not default\nI set contentPath in config.js to '../../app/content/' and the image uploader stopped working. Searched through the code and it appears this is the line causing the problem:\r\n\r\nlocalfilesystem.js:22: targetDir = this.getTargetDir(config().paths.imagesPath),\r\n\r\nI changed imagesPath to imagesRelPath and it worked.  \r\n\r\nShould this be changed in core?"
2960,'',"Create boundOneWay util function\nCloses #2958\r\n- Created `boundOneWay` util to extract common pattern of having a oneWay property that doesn't break its binding after being set\r\n- Changed `EditorControllerMixin.willPublish`,  `PostSettingsMenuController.publishedAtValue` and `.slugValue` to use the new `boundOneWay` util"
2959,'',"Indirectly couple editor markdown and post's actual markdown\nCloses #2958\r\n- Created `boundOneWay` util to extract common pattern of having a oneWay property that doesn't break its binding after being set\r\n- Changed `EditorControllerMixin.willPublish`,  `PostSettingsMenuController.publishedAtValue` and `.slugValue` to use the new `boundOneWay` util\r\n- Added `markdown` property to `EditorControllerMixin`\r\n- Updated editor's `save` action to set the model's markdown to the editor's markdown."
2958,'','[Ember.js] Make a BoundOneWay utility\nThis idea of "indirect, upstream listening property" should be reusable so that we don\'t have to keep reimplementing it. Essentially, these are properties that are identical to `Ember.computed.oneway(\'upstreamProp\')` save that they don\'t break their binding upon being set, meaning that a change upstream will be mirrored downstream on the property.\r\n'
2957,'darvelo','[Ember.js] Reimplement mobile editor\nFollowing on from #2426/#2895 we need to also make the editor work on mobile again.\r\n\r\nThe mobileCodeMirror shim needs porting across to Ember. For now it can load under the same conditions as it did previously, however there are known bugs with this (see #2570) that can be fixed at the same time if the person doing this has a bright idea.\r\n\r\nIf not - then it should simply load as a replacement editor if the current device is a touchscreen device.'
2956,'ErisDS','[Ember.js] Reimplement filestorage option for uploads\nThere is a config.js option called `fileStorage` which needs to be updated to work in the Ember admin.\r\n\r\nThe `fileStorage` option is a rough version of our plan to eventually allow different methods of storing files. At present, you can store files locally in the file system, or you can turn file storage off completely, which currently only applies to images.\r\n\r\nIn the event that `fileStorage` is set to `false`, the uploader dropzone in the editor, and on the settings pages, should show the URL screen by default, instead of the upload/drop screen, and should disable access to the upload/drop screen.\r\n\r\nThe value of `fileStorage` essentially needs to be prefetched data stored as an HTML data attribute or some such in order for this to work.'
2955,'',"Label 'for' attribute value literal have no delimiter.\nAdded equals delimiter between 'for' and attribute value literal.\r\n\r\nCloses #2954"
2954,'','Label \'for\' attribute value literal have no delimiter\nThere\'s no equal sign marking separation between attribute and value in two occurrences:\r\n\r\nIn /core/client/templates/settings/user.hbs at line 37:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    <label for"user-email">Email</label>\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn /core/clientold/tpl/settings/user-profile.hbs at line 37:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    <label for"user-email">Email</label>\r\n```'
2953,'','Change `posts`, `post`, and `signout` routes to be `AuthenticatedRoute`s\nNo issue.\r\nThe following is a list of routes which are *not* authenticated after this PR\r\n- placeholder routes: `editor` and `content`\r\n- `application`\r\n- password routes: `forgotten`, `reset`, `signin`, `signup`'
2952,'',"Transition user to original destination on login\nCloses #2943\r\n\r\n- `AuthenticatedRoute` now stores the user's original destination on the\r\n  `ApplicationController`.\r\n- The `SignIn` route's `login` action checks if the\r\n  `originalUserDestination` property is set on the\r\n  `ApplicationController`, and if so, retries that transition after a\r\n  successful login.\r\n\r\n\r\nI definitely jshint'd this before PRing. Go me."
2951,'darvelo',"Ember Editor Route can't find posts with low IDs\n## Issue Summary\r\n\r\nWhen you have a large enough number of posts to have them broken into multiple pages in the api, you are unable to go directly to `/ghost/ember/editor/1` as the first post is not returned in [this api call](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/blob/master/core/client/routes/editor/edit.js#L23)\r\n\r\n## Repro\r\n\r\n1. Create enough posts to start paging (>15 I think)\r\n2. Enter `/ghost/ember/editor/1` in your browser and go\r\n3. Redirected to `/ghost/ember` as post 1 was not returned by the api :(\r\n\r\n## Specs\r\n\r\nWin 8, master `df8ba5f439062119922f98ab`"
2950,'',"Markdown links not parsed within embedded HTML\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nLinks in markdown not parsed unless initially introduced outside of the HTML.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Some explanation at [Justified Text](https://ghost.org/forum/using-ghost/2921-justified-text/8/) forum post.\r\n* `<p style='text-align: right;'>[title](http://example.com), author(s), date, [OCLC ref](https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/)</p>`\r\nresults in:\r\n\r\n    <p style='text-align: right;'>[title](http://example.com), author(s), date, [OCLC ref](https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/)</p>\r\n* `[]()<p style='text-align: right;'>[title](http://example.com), author(s), date, [OCLC ref](https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/)</p>`\r\nresults in:\r\n\r\n    []()<p style='text-align: right;'>[title](http://example.com), author(s), date, [OCLC ref](https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/)</p>\r\n\r\nI searched for issues and the nearest possibly relevant ones I found are [#2312](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/issues/2312) and [#2375](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/pull/2375). Sorry if I missed something obvious.\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\nI'm running the Ghost(Pro) hosted trial, so presume it's the latest stable version.\r\n\r\nThanks for reading."
2949,'',"added tiny more details, nothing major (reference #2935)\n* Removed an EOT character that wasn't supposed to be there\r\n* Added tiny detail regarding limits of account for obvious reasons\r\n"
2948,'',"Fix serializing/deserializing Tags on save from the Editor\ncloses #2947\r\n- make a PostSerializer to embed the tags objects in the posts POST/PUT request\r\n- on editor save, clear out tags from the post and data store that have `id: null`\r\n\r\nThere's no easy or obvious way in Ember Data to update the client-generated tags once they return from the server with the id. I tried for hours with a Tag serializer before giving up. Instead, on return from the server, I allow the saved tags to attach themselves to the post, and delete the otherwise identical client-generated tags. The Editor PR will also delete unsaved client-generated tasks on transition away from the editor."
2947,'','[Ember.js] Tags sent from editor along with post are null\nWhen saving a post from the editor, Ember Data tries to send the tags to the server with only their ids. Since they were generated on the client, the ids are all null, so the request ends up as:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  posts: [{\r\n    ...\r\n    tags: [null, null, null]\r\n  }]\r\n}\r\n```'
2946,'','Fixes static pages when permalinks are active.\nfixes #2938\r\n- Fix `page === 1` occurences\r\n- Fix ember logic'
2945,'',"Slug API Should Take an Optional ID parameter\nThere's an issue with the slug api where, asking for a slug that you already own returns that slug but with a '-2' appended, as the server isn't aware that the request is coming from the owner of the slug that it found.\r\n\r\nI'm pretty sure that's a rather opaque sentence, so let me copy and paste my description of this from IRC:\r\n\r\n><novaugust> 1. GenerateSlug('The Title')\r\n><novaugust> 2. Api gets it\r\n><novaugust> 2a) Server slugifies 'The Title' into 'the-title'\r\n><novaugust> 2b) Server checks db for anything that already has 'the-title' as its slug\r\n><novaugust> 2c) Server finds a post that uses 'the-title'. This is actually the post that >generated the request, but the server doesn't know that.\r\n><novaugust> 2d) Server appends a '-2' to unique-ify the slug\r\n><novaugust> 2e) server sends back 'the-title-2'\r\n><novaugust> 3. Post thinks its placeholder should be 'the-title-2', because someone >owns 'the-title'\r\n><rwjblue> IMHO, server needs to get a header or something for identity\r\n\r\n@rjackson is onto something there, eh? ;)\r\nBackground conversation can be found in the logs starting [here](http://107.20.237.151:8081/logs/%23ghost/20140612#pm101259)\r\n"
