2928,'','Fix export of data during database migration\nCloses #2927\r\n-refactor exporter to export tables that exist in the\r\n database instead of keying off of schema.js\r\n-move some shared database utility functions into their\r\n own module'
2927,'','Export fails if run during database migration\n#847 introduced an export prior to the database migration that may occur during a version upgrade.  The `server/data/export` package exports tables based on the current `server/data/schema.js` file.  In the case of an upgrade that introduces a new table, the export will fail on a missing table and produce an unusable export:\r\n\r\n0.4.2 => master shown below:\r\n```\r\nError exporting data: Error: SQLITE_ERROR: no such table: permissions_apps, sql: select * from "permissions_apps", bindings: \r\n```\r\n\r\nproduces:\r\n```\r\n{"meta":{"exported_on":1402345101983,"version":"002"},"data":{}}\r\n```\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce:\r\n\r\n* Create a database while running 0.4.2\r\n\r\n* Checkout the master branch (and `npm install`)\r\n\r\n* Start Ghost\r\n'
2926,'',"Setting the X-Powered-By header to 'Ghost'.\nCloses #2925\r\n- adding X-Powered-By header in core/server/index.js"
