2913,'',"[Ember.js] Editor tab index\nWhen you're mouseless, it's good to have the tab button do logical things.\r\n\r\nOn the editor screen, I want be able to jump from the post's title field to its markdown by hitting tab, but right now I end up in the navbar if I do that.\r\n\r\nSee also #2752 "
2912,'','Removed API dependency from mailer and api/mail\nFixes #2836.\r\n\r\n* Mailer now only handles sending email and initializing settings. Instead of adding new notifications there, it just sets flags on its own object.\r\n* Mailer now checks for the presence of "to". If there is none, it fails. You should really pass a full mail object complete with "to", "subject" and "html", otherwise it\'s partial content.\r\n* Therefore Mail API doesn\'t check for the existence of the "to", and doesn\'t get the email from settings and substitute that\r\n* index.js now has a method that adds the notifications. I figured adding those THERE is probably better than individually in every module. It is, as the comments say, can be made extensible'
2911,'',"Split PostController amongst new Editor/PostSettingsMenu Controllers\ncloses #2910, closes #2899\r\n- create EditorController, PostSettingsMenuController\r\n- remove `posts.post` controllerName dependency on EditorRoute/NewRoute\r\n- `{{render}}` the PostSettingsMenuView with its own controller\r\n- break up properties/methods from PostsPostController into all three controllers\r\n- fix EditorRoute pagination options to now be comparable to PostsRoute\r\n- add NewController to force NewRoute to refresh editor with blank model. Identical to Editor's\r\n- EditorController and NewController are based on a shared mixin\r\n- NewView created, templateName is 'editor'\r\n\r\nKeep in mind NewRoute/NewController still let funky things happen with empty posts and such. Work needs to be done there at some point to drop the unsaved model during a transition."
2910,'',"Create EditorController\nEditorController needs to be created for the editor work that's being done, and also to clean up the controller code a bit."
2909,'','Fixed publish button not updating with model  change\nCloses #2908\r\n- Changes `willPublish` from oneWay property to computed property.'
2908,'','[Ember.js] publish button doesn\'t change state on new post\nThe publish / save draft button doesn\'t change its state when the model changes. This arises from its oneWay binding breaking after it gets set for the first time\r\n\r\n## Repro Steps\r\n\r\n1. Create a new post, fill in its information, and save it as a draft.\r\n2. Publish the post\r\n3. Go back to the post list page (click on content)\r\n4. Open the post you just published to edit.\r\n5. Click on the new post button\r\n\r\nThe publish button will still be in a "publish" state, rather than swapping to the "draft" state.\r\n\r\n## Specs\r\n\r\nos: win 8\r\ncommit: master `fc631665ed8171af`'
2907,'',"Add shadows to PostsListView and the adjacent HTML Preview; Fix preview\ncloses #2906 \r\n- add a utility function to add classnames to targets, retrofitted from clientold to accommodate `Ember.run.bind`\r\n- create a content-preview view that tracks its scrolling\r\n- add a scroll handler to the existing PostsListView\r\n- The `posts/post` template now takes its HTML from the post model instead of using the editor's markdown component\r\n\r\nI've also got this working in the editor, but this will set the stage for that when the editor PR is finished."
2906,'','Add shadows to PostsList and HTML Preview on scroll\nWhen scrolling, shadows should exist under the top bar in the posts list and also in the adjacent HTML preview.'
2905,'',"Fix HTML preview rendering on the main screen\ncloses #2904\r\n- The `posts/post` template now takes its HTML from the post model instead of using the editor's markdown component"
2904,'','Fix HTML preview data bindings\nCurrently the `posts/post` template is using the markdown component to render the HTML preview. While working on #2895 I noticed this was causing it to render image dropzones. The template should instead render the HTML from the model [like it does in clientold](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/blob/master/core/clientold/tpl/preview.hbs#L49).'
2903,'','Clear any existing SIGINT listeners during startup\nNo issue\r\n-remove any existing listeners on the SIGINT event during\r\n the ghost bootstrap process.  handles an issue during testing\r\n where node was warning about too many listeners.'
2902,'','[Ember.js] Slug calls are causing lots of 500 errors\nPretty much anything you do on the content screen or editor currently causes errors:\r\n\r\n![errors](http://puu.sh/9iS6B/b8dc6cc954.png)\r\n\r\nI guess one of the recent changes has a niggle in it :/'
2901,'','Implement the Tag Editor view\ncloses #2425\r\n\r\n- creates custom view for the tag editor'
2900,'','Rebuild Post Settings Menu\nCloses #2845.\r\nRef #1351.\r\n- Refactored `PostSettingsMenuController` to appropriately set and display\r\n  slug and publish date and their placeholders.\r\n- Removed api spam on title change by putting `slugPlaceholder` generation\r\n  inside of an `Ember.run.debounce` call.\r\n- Renamed `gh-blur-text-field` to `gh-blur-input`\r\n- Created `SlugGenerator` class to abstract slug generation.\r\n- Added `timestampVerification` function to `utils/date-formatting`\r\n- `utils/date-formatting` now uses `strict` parsing of dates\r\n- Added more acceptable date formats to accommodate strict parsing\r\n- Moved `isDraft` and `isPublished` computed properties from\r\n  `EditorController` to `PostModel`'
2899,'',"[Bug][Ember.js] New Post from editor screen doesn't clear markdown\n## Issue Summary\r\nClicking on the `New Post` button when in a `/editor/x` route clears out the title, html, and post settings just dandy, but leaves behind the markdown.\r\n\r\n## Repro Steps\r\n\r\n1. Open a post with content for editing\r\n2. Click on New Post\r\n3. Markdown remains :(\r\n\r\n## Specs\r\n\r\nOS: Win8\r\nCommit Ref: `b7aca05d95f50`"
2898,'','Multi blog on single instance\nHello everyone,\r\n\r\nI know this is not right place to post, but I found it best, cause here are all developers working with ghost.  I posted a thread on ghost forum weeks ago, but still none response.\r\n\r\nFreelance developer is what I am looking for, someone who want to customize ghost per my needs. \r\n\r\nWhat I need is multiblog creation on single installation. Something like ghost.org itself, tumblr, wordpress.com or any web 2.0 blog platform. I would like to have simple registration where users can create their blogs on sub-domains with few easy clicks.\r\n\r\nEveryone is welcome, not only professionals. I have limited budget, so anyone who wanna earn, learn and have fun, hit me up on skype:ksifoking for better communication.\r\n\r\nMods, once again, sorry if this is not right place to post.\r\n\r\nPeace,'
2897,'',"Modal Uploader\nfor issue #2547\r\n\r\nonly worked on the general settings so far.\r\n\r\nI add a couple links to images in the fixture data for testing.  The upload modal lets you choose a photo and drag one in.\r\n\r\nThe only thing it doesn't do is save it\r\n\r\n**Edit:**\r\n~~this also depends on https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/pull/2886, since that commit exists here.~~\r\n\r\n"
2895,'',"Reach Editor parity with Ember\ncloses #2426, closes #2781, closes #2913\r\n\r\n**Some issues:**\r\n\r\n* I didn't try to port `mobileCodeMirror.js` .. I think mobile is a different beast and I'm not comfy there yet. Also I'm not sure what our strategy is for that with Ember.\r\n* I didn't understand what was going on with [`fileStorage` in uploadManager.js:137](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/blob/master/core/clientold/assets/lib/editor/uploadManager.js#L137) so I did [gh-markdown.js:25](https://github.com/appleYaks/Ghost/commit/aa1196611882322b7fceb26cc0ccb1b579e01535#diff-1cd2ff4e951d1133c34d516ff81b2182R25) and set it to `false`.\r\n\r\nI did a lot of testing, but I ain't no superman. More heads are better than one, so please let me know where the bugs are at, or how to reproduce them."
2894,'',"Close post settings popover menu after delete post\nNo issue\r\n-inject popover:service into modal component delete post\r\n controller so popover close can be triggered as part of\r\n the delete action\r\n-remove unnecessary 'needs' from the delete post controller"
2893,'',"[Bug][Ember.js] Save post with blank title\nThere's some really strange behavior that happens when trying to `save draft` a post with no title in Ember.\r\n\r\n## Issue Summary\r\n\r\nSaving a post with no title sends a `422` error code from the server, but Ember ignores it and saves the post regardless.\r\n\r\nSeriously, things will get weird weird. Refresh to fix (the problems are local, in Ember)\r\n### Expected behavoir\r\n\r\nEmber should not save a post with an empty title, and show send a `notification` letting the user know they must have a title in there.\r\n\r\n## Reproduction\r\n\r\n### Via new post\r\n\r\n1. Create a new post, or edit an existing one\r\n    1a) If it's an existing post, delete its title\r\n2. Click on save draft without putting anything in the title\r\n3. Click on the **Content** link.\r\n4. Have fun?\r\n\r\n## System specs\r\n\r\n**OS**: Windows 8\r\n**Commit Ref**:  `b7aca05d95f50ad4b464`"
2892,'',"Fix Editor/:postId 404 on draft\ncloses #2857\r\n- in EditorRoute, get model from the datastore if it's there\r\n- if page is refreshed, get model from `/posts` API with `{status: 'all'}`\r\n\r\nThis is @rjackson's fix with minor modifications."
2891,'',"[Proposal] Use Moment objects for Ember Model date fields\nMoment is already a global within the client, and anywhere (to my knowledge) we're working with dates, we're going back and forth into Moments.\r\n\r\nI think it would be a good thing to consolidate the various changes to and from Moment objects into a `DS.Transform`.\r\n\r\nIn essence, this\r\n```javascript\r\ncreated_at: DS.attr('date')\r\n```\r\n\r\nwould become this\r\n```javascript\r\ncreated_at: DS.attr('moment-date')\r\n```"
2890,'','Add notifications for data import success or failure.\nref: #2847\r\n- remove todo alerts\r\n- add notificiations for import'
2889,'',"Changed ember models to use moment for dates\nCloses #2891 \r\n\r\n-Added moment-date `DS.Transform`\r\n-`models/post` and `models/user` both use `DS.attr('moment-date')` in\r\nplace of `date` now."
2888,'',"[Ember.js] DS.attr('date') doesn't parse Ghost API date values\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Have the [ember inspector](https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/ember-inspector/bmdblncegkenkacieihfhpjfppoconhi?hl=en) installed\r\n2. Inspect a post model and look at its `created_at` or other `DS.attr('date')` fields.\r\n\r\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1207005/3190284/bf0261de-eccc-11e3-8c72-78177afd2d38.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nI propose using a `DS.Transform` that serializes all dates into and out of moments on the client side. This will greatly assist #2845 and help consolidate date transformation code. We're already using moment for any real work."
2887,'','Change Backup location\nPrior to every database migration a backup of the current database saved (see #847). The location of the backup is `/core/server/data/<backup-file>`. Since user data is stored in the `/content` folder the location of the backup should be changed to `/content/data/<backup-file>`.'
2886,'','Generic Uploader component\nThis is the beginning of wrapping the existing "uploader.js" here https://github.com/lholmquist/Ghost/blob/master/core/clientold/assets/lib/uploader.js\r\n\r\nin something that the ember code can use.\r\n\r\nit is mostly the same with some differences, such as exporting it as a module\r\n\r\n\r\ni\'m not sure if this should be a true "component" or just be imported into an existing component/controller'
2885,'',"Ghost Admin: Clicking on post containing javascript code breaks post link in admin?\nThis is a tricky one to explain because I don't know if this is a bug. Thought I should mention this.\r\n\r\nI believe it is because I am using http://hivelogic.com/enkoder/ to encrypt my email address.\r\n\r\nTo reproduce this...\r\n\r\n1) Create a new post.\r\n2) Throw in random text. Copy and paste Enkoder's code into the post.\r\n3) Save the post (draft/publish), it should send you back to the main content. You may end up seeing a blank page that you have created with an email link... If not.... step 4!\r\n4) While on the main content, click on the post that you have created with the javascript code in to edit, you should see a blank page with an email link.\r\n\r\nServer: Ubuntu 14.04, Nginx 1.6.0, Ghost 0.4.2.\r\n\r\nAny more information, please let me know.\r\n\r\n(go easy on me... this is my first issue submitted on github!!)"
2884,'','Get single post from API by id and query params; Auto-sort posts list\n Get single post from API by id and query params; Auto-sort posts list\r\n\r\ncloses #2883, closes #2951\r\n- introduce custom findQuery in ApplicationAdapter\r\n- posts/post route and editor/edit route now use custom findQuery to find a single post by id with query params\r\n- create a sorting function in PostsController for out-of-order loading\r\n- refresh updated posts in posts.index to make PostsList highlight latest draft after returning from a save in editor\r\n\r\nThe only problem I had was after updating a draft.. going back to the PostsRoute highlighted the previously last-updated draft, not the most currently updated one. I had to modify PostsIndexRoute to grab a fresh list from the server, but that causes an extra request on first landing on `/ghost/ember/`.\r\n'
2883,'darvelo','[Ember.js] Out-of-order loading of posts\nIf we allow a post to be loaded individually from the API via the EditorRoute or PostsPostRoute, during a refresh/back button, it should be in the correct spot of the posts list as more models are loaded during infinite scroll.'
2882,'',"RejectionError on JSON Import\nWhen I try to import a JSON file I get a response of errors like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nRejectionError: current transaction is aborted, commands ignored until end of transaction block\r\n```\r\n![screen shot 2014-06-04 at 2 31 20 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1186124/3178066/8289bfb0-ec16-11e3-8493-8d2cdebf4a5f.png)\r\n\r\nI am importing this file: https://gist.github.com/jpadilla/7290464\r\n\r\nI can add posts fine, so the database is working in that regard. I am using Postgresql, so I am not sure if I should even file an issue, because I know that isn't really supported."
2881,'','[WIP] inital addition of an upload component\nThis is still a WIP upload component that is related to https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/issues/2547 and https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/issues/2426\r\n\r\nbasic usage in your `.hbs` file:\r\n\r\n    {{gh-file-upload onUploadSuccess="onUploadSuccess" uploadButtonText="Save" autoUpload=false}}\r\n\r\nWhen autoUpload is false, a button is shown.  the default is true\r\n\r\nso far the exposed methods are\r\n\r\n* `onUploadSuccess`\r\n* `onUploadError`\r\n* `onUploadComplete`\r\n* `onUpload`\r\n\r\nThere should probably be a couple more, like a progress event, etc...\r\n\r\n\r\nI just wanted to share what i had so far'
2880,'','Fix error when running Ghost with a socket\nfixes #2879\r\n- Syncronously check/unlink old socket file\r\n\r\n\r\n`httpServer` wasn’t assigned yet because of the aynchronous `fs.unlink`.'
2879,'',"Error running Ghost with socket setup instead of host/port\nAt the moment there is an issue if you want to run Ghost instance that's listening on the socket. \r\n\r\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nThe following error is reported when running Ghost instance configured with socket instead of host/port combination: \r\n\r\nERROR: Cannot call method 'on' of undefined \r\n \r\n TypeError: Cannot call method 'on' of undefined\r\n    at /Users/anndes/Desktop/KOSTIA/common/ghost-0.4.2-master/core/server/index.js:279:20\r\n    at NearFulfilledProxy.when (/Users/anndes/Desktop/KOSTIA/common/ghost-0.4.2-master/node_modules/when/when.js:501:43)\r\n    at Promise._message (/Users/anndes/Desktop/KOSTIA/common/ghost-0.4.2-master/node_modules/when/when.js:426:25)\r\n    at Array.deliver [as 2] (/Users/anndes/Desktop/KOSTIA/common/ghost-0.4.2-master/node_modules/when/when.js:319:7)\r\n    at runHandlers (/Users/anndes/Desktop/KOSTIA/common/ghost-0.4.2-master/node_modules/when/when.js:385:12)\r\n    at Array.87 (/Users/anndes/Desktop/KOSTIA/common/ghost-0.4.2-master/node_modules/when/when.js:352:5)\r\n    at runHandlers (/Users/anndes/Desktop/KOSTIA/common/ghost-0.4.2-master/node_modules/when/when.js:385:12)\r\n    at drainQueue (/Users/anndes/Desktop/KOSTIA/common/ghost-0.4.2-master/node_modules/when/when.js:836:3)\r\n    at process._tickDomainCallback (node.js:459:13)\r\n    at process._tickFromSpinner (node.js:390:15) \r\n\r\nThe issue comes from core/server/index.js file on line 279 (as visible from the stack above). Further investigation of this file shows that httpServer variable is not assigned at correct time when using sockets. That is, the httpServer variable is undefined on line 279, since line 264 asynchronous call is not yet completed to set the variable. \r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Modify config.js file to listen on socket\r\n2. Start Ghost (npm start)\r\n3. The error will display in console\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master (latest)\r\n* Client OS: Mac OS X\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.24\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n"
2878,'','URL (slug name) of new post is set to [object Object] while editing.\nWhen creating new post, if settings of this post is clicked before the draft was saved, the URL field of setting popup displays [object Object]. \r\n\r\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nThis seems to be a minor issue, but could be nice to fix. The problem comes when you create new post and want to edit URL (slug) of the post before saving the draft or publishing. If you click posts settings icon, dialog displays, and URL display [object Object], which is the javascript type rather than the title of the post. \r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Create new post\r\n2. Without saving draft or publishing, click the settings icon to display the dialog\r\n3. Check the value of URL field. \r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master (latest)\r\n* Client OS: Mac OS X\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.24\r\n* Browser: Chrome\r\n\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2014-06-04 at 15 17 13](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1479911/3173247/5e493af0-ebe3-11e3-8649-89e280fd5ef5.png)\r\n'
