2859,'',"Local Install Forgotten Password\nIn ```config.js```, it doesn't seem to be possible to set the development url to ```localhost:2368```. Thus, the email for a password reset will not have a proper url.\r\n\r\nIf anyone else runs into this, you can just change this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nhttp://my-ghost-blog.com/ghost/reset/###### long hash #######\r\n```\r\n\r\nto\r\n\r\n```\r\nlocalhost:2368/ghost/reset/###### long hash #######\r\n```\r\n\r\nand paste it into the browser."
2858,'',"Slug generation permissions bug\n## Issue Summary\r\n\r\nThe server is throwing an error when checking for permissions on slug generation. \r\n\r\n## Repro Steps\r\n\r\n1. Start the server\r\n2. Go to `/ghost/ember/`\r\n3. Check your logs for some 500 errors\r\n\r\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1207005/3142768/6f1c5b5e-e9d2-11e3-9780-81c183dd1359.png)\r\n\r\n## Tech Specs\r\n\r\nOS: Win 8\r\nCommit: master @ `ef6b03fe`\r\n\r\n-------------------------------------------------------\r\nThere's a second error happening on `error.hbs` that is either a result of this, or its own issue (`foreach` helper not recognized). So, that's something that'll need looking into once this is closed."
2857,'',"[Ember.js] Bug -- Editor/:postId 404 on draft\n## Issue Summary\r\nEntering the url `/ghost/ember/editor/*pid*` will 404 when that post is a draft.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Turn your first post to `draft` status.\r\n2. Click on the edit button (so that you're at `/ghost/ember/editor/x/`\r\n3. Refresh the page.\r\nBaby, you just 404'd.\r\n\r\nAt a glance, this is because ember's using this route: `http://localhost:2368/ghost/api/v0.1/posts/` to find posts, without the `?status=all` query param.\r\n\r\n## Technical details:\r\n\r\nGhost Version: master (latest commit: `61dbed0`)\r\nOS: Windows 8\r\nOS: Windows 8\r\nNode Version: 0.10.25\r\nBrowser: Chrome 35\r\nDatabase: MySQL"
2856,'',"[Ember.js] Post Validations \nAt the moment there is some code for validating posts, but it isn't working properly - trying to save a post without a title doesn't work and doesn't provide an error.\r\n\r\nAlso - I think we need to consider a unified approach for validations - maybe using another library like: https://github.com/dockyard/ember-validations, although we probably need to keep using the same validation library we're using on the bank end to ensure consistency. Additionally, there are validations defined in `schema.js` - I'm not sure if there is any way we can reuse this in Ember as we do on the server side.\r\n\r\nThere is validation happening I think on the settings general screen, and that is hooking properly into notifications - but it seems to require hardcoding the validation to happen on save, which IMO should be 'baked in' somehow. I'd like to find a way to define that models must be validated before they can be saved - the ember-validations library does something like this at the controller level according to @rjackson.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, I updated the post model to have default data for some fields which are not allowed to be passed to the serverside as blank - although I'm not sure if this is the best approach. \r\n\r\nNote, there is also an open issue to port over the correct notifications: #2850, this issue is meant to deal with creating a consistent way to do validations."
