2829,'','Changing user email "breaks" login\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nWhen you change the email address for a user, the existing login (rightfully so) is non-existent. However, there is no indication that a user should login using the new email address.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Login\r\n2. Go to Settings > User\r\n3. Change email address\r\n4. Save\r\n5. Logout\r\n6. Login with previous email address "broken", must use new address\r\n\r\nThe behavior is correct, but there needs to be a popup element with an explanation after step 4 (\'Save\' the new address), or the database should save the old address alongside the new one to properly inform a user to use the new email address when they try to login (step 6).\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.4.2\r\n* Client OS: Windows 8.1\r\n* Server OS: OpenShift\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.26\r\n* Browser: Chrome 35.0.1916.114\r\n* Database: SQLite3'
