2820,'',"Fix 403 errors after signup\nCloses #2819\r\n\r\n- Keep around the _csrfSecret on the session after regenerating\r\n\r\nTo figure this out I took a look at the connect csrf middleware and noticed that the `session._csrfSecret` was getting blown up after we regenerate on signup.  I tried to do a `req.csrfToken()` and send that down to the page after signup, then use the updated CSRF value but that didn't seem to work.\r\n\r\nWhy are we regenerating the session after signup?  Is this a security practice I'm not aware of?"
2819,'',"403 Errors from API after Ember Signup\nThis was originally pointed out by @ErisDS in my PR for the signup page but I thought it was caused by not properly sending the `signedUp` action.\r\n\r\nI think what is happening is that when the session is regenerated, the csrf token must be also regenerated and sent down to the page.  I haven't confirmed this yet, and would like someone else to corroborate it at least.\r\n\r\nIf the token does need to be regenerated, we should probably change the `initializers/csrf.js` to hold the value in an Ember.Object so we can update it at a later point.\r\n\r\nI'm going to spend some time trying to regenerate the CSRF and see if it is the culprit."
