2811,'','[Bug Report] Performance issue with sign-in page.\nWhen a large amount of requests are sent to the sign-in page located at `/ghost/` or `/ghost/signin/`, the entire blog will temporally cease to function. This is not due to under powered hardware not being able to process the requests, as sending the same number of requests to any other page will not have the same effect. Oddly enough, the CPU usage by `node index` only increases by a relatively small amount.\r\n\r\nThis could be exploited in a denial of service attack with simple bench-marking tools.\r\n`while true; do ab -n 10000 -c 1000 http://example.net/ghost/; done`\r\nAlso note how the blog will resume normal functionality some time after stopping the attack. The longer the attack, the longer after stopping it will take to recover.\r\n\r\nThis might be related to [issue #1207](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/issues/1207). Upon providing valid login credentials, the blog will cease to do anything else until the login is complete. This is especially apparent when using low power devices such as the Raspberry Pi to host the blog.'
