2773,'',"[Bug] checkObject is too restrictive\nWhen I start Ghost after the refactoring in #2732 I get the following error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nvagrant@vagrant-ubuntu-precise-64:~/code/Ghost$ npm start\r\n\r\n> ghost@0.4.2 start /home/vagrant/code/Ghost\r\n> node index\r\n\r\n\r\nERROR: No root key ('settings') provided. \r\n The app will not be loaded \r\n Check with the app creator, or read the app documentation for more details on app requirements \r\n```\r\n\r\nThis happens because there are situations where settings (apps) are updated with an empty array."
