2736,'',"Postgres test failures and data issue\n#2700 introduced a problem with postgres.  The issue is data corruption being caused by node-postgres converting javascript arrays into postgres arrays (pg uses ```{}``` to bound arrays).\r\n\r\nSpecifically, Ghost has a setting ```installedApps``` with a default value of ```'[]'``` (a string representation of an empty array) which is being converted to ```{}``` and saved.  Before #2700 values sent into ```api.settings.edit``` were run through ```JSON.stringify``` prior to being saved into the database (https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/commit/2795e723e151b018e3b1d6bdc31aebb96994c8a2#diff-12a8dbd78d369667d9a6160c856477dfL219).  I believe this is the correct behavior and should probably be reintroduced.\r\n\r\nYou can see it happening on the travis pg tests.  You can also reproduce it by configuring Ghost to use pg and starting it up a couple of times.  After two or three times it will fail to start because of the corrupted value for ```installedApps```."
