2728,'',"Ghost installation is now crashing in  Azure websites\nGhost is crashing during installation on azure,  you get all the time \r\n\r\n*The resource you are looking for has been removed, had its name changed, or is temporarily unavailable*\r\n\r\nSo, I Tryed to update an already working blog, just adding a single static file but after deployment the ghost blog is broked too with same message. \r\n\r\nhttp://juank.io \r\n\r\nI have installed a couple of blogs in Azure and I never have got this issue.\r\n\r\nLocally on Windows it works fine.\r\n\r\nSwitching On detailed output on azure website the error message says that IIS can't found the ./Index resource\r\n\r\n>HTTP Error 404.0 - Not Found The resource you are looking for has been removed, had its name changed, or is temporarily unavailable.\r\n\r\n**Detailed Error Information:**\r\nModule\r\n   iisnode \r\nNotification\r\n   ExecuteRequestHandler \r\nHandler\r\n   iisnode \r\nError Code\r\n   0x00000002 \r\n\r\nRequested URL\r\n   http://juankio:80/index \r\n\r\nPhysical Path\r\n   D:\\home\\site\\wwwroot\\index \r\n\r\nLogon Method\r\n   Anonymous \r\n\r\nLogon User\r\n   Anonymous \r\n"
2727,'',"Feature request: Use a separate network interface for blog visitors and blog admins/users\nThis is a feature request for the Ghost admin.\r\n\r\n-------------------\r\n\r\nCurrently, the configuration of Ghost only allow 1 network interface to be used for doing 2 distinctive tasks:\r\n- Publishing the blog's articles for the blog's visitors.\r\n- Providing pages for the blog's user to let him manage the blog's content.\r\n\r\nMy request is to make Ghost use a separate network (IP + port) interface for those 2 distinctive tasks.\r\n\r\nAdvantages provided by this feature:\r\n- Better security as the administrator have more control on from where users can manage their content.\r\n- People who get nervous about having the login page exposed to the Internet will feel less nervous.\r\n- Better default ready-to-use configuration for new comers while being safe (see below).\r\n\r\nCurrent default configuration:\r\n```js\r\n        server: {\r\n            // Host to be passed to node's `net.Server#listen()`\r\n            host: '127.0.0.1',\r\n            // Port to be passed to node's `net.Server#listen()`, for iisnode set this to `process.env.PORT`\r\n            port: '2368'\r\n        }\r\n```\r\n\r\nProposed new default configuration:\r\n```js\r\n        contentAdminServer: {\r\n            host: '127.0.0.1', // Can only be accessed from localhost.\r\n            port: '2368'\r\n        },\r\n        contentPublishServer: {\r\n            host: '0.0.0.0', // Can be accessed from anywhere on Internet.\r\n            port: '2369'\r\n        }\r\n```\r\n"
