2717,'','Categories / Tags / Slugs\nWhile I know there have been questions asks in the Ghost Forum, etc about Categories, I was wondering if there are going to be categories ever in Ghost, or is this going to be possible through an "App" (future release of Ghost).  The reason I ask (and please let me know if this is already possible), but I\'m used to post slugs for myself being like so:\r\n\r\n    http://example.org/Linux/long-post-slug1/\r\n    http://example.org/Mac/long-post-slug2/\r\n\r\nAlong with the examples above, I\'d maybe have a couple, if not more tags associated with each post. So, while I do know that right now categories are the same as tags when it comes to Ghost, I didn\'t think there was a way to change the output URL to 1) follow the format of `http://example.org/category/post-slug/` and 2) there is no way to categories an actual post.\r\n\r\nI feel like a category should be used to "file" a certain article, while tags "describe" or allow one to assign "attributes" to a post.\r\n\r\nSo, while this may sound like a reoccuring question, it\'s not; so:\r\n\r\n1. Are there going to be Categories AND Tags available at some point \r\n2. If so, is there going to be a way to make it available to have the format of `http://example.org/category/post-slugs` (or other ways, such as using dates, etc); something that i know Wordpress, Pelican, and a few others allow you to customize\r\n3. If not, is there currently a way, or will there be currently a way to do what I\'m going after with the URL?\r\n\r\nAs a side note, I reviewed the [Roadmap](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/wiki/Roadmap) and  [Planned Features](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/wiki/Planned-Features) items, and nothing mentioned categories or the sorts, so that\'s why I\'m asking.'
