2712,'','Ghost first run failing\nSince the introduction of the canThis permission checks, when Ghost does its "first run" initialization (in production) it will fail to start.\r\n\r\n The issue is that in ```core/server/index.js```, ```models.init()``` inserts the default "Welcome to Ghost" post and the post model\'s ```.save()``` handler calls ```xmlrpc.ping()```, which makes a call into api.settings, which fails because ```permissions.init()``` hasn\'t been called yet.  However, ```permissions.init()``` can\'t be called before ```models.init()```.\r\n\r\nCan be reproduced on master (bb543ede8e57b829b00762903a75880c0007aea9) by starting ghost with no db in production mode.'
