2663,'','Bug: <code> tag in "Blog Description" leads to display of "" />" (without outer quotes) on the top of page\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nAfter inserting a `<code>[self museWithLanguage:@"Objective-C"]</code>`as Blog Description,`" />` (without outer quotes) appears at the top of the page with whitespace spanning the width of the page.\r\nTried with Chroma and Casper themes. (Casper theme is unchanged)\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2014-04-29 at 7 58 53 am](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3445290/2828564/aef39c9e-cf95-11e3-85f1-f76d7a6ef218.png)\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. go to site.com/ghost\r\n2. go to SETTINGS\r\n3. make sure you\'r in GENERAL\r\n4. make "Blog Description" `<code>[self museWithLanguage:@"Objective-C"]</code>`\r\n5. SAVE\r\n5. go to site.com\r\n6. `" />` (without outer quotes) appears at the top of the page with whitespace spanning the width of the page.\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master - latest commit:  INSERT COMMIT REF\r\n* Client OS: OS X 10.9.2\r\n* Server OS: Amazon Linux AMI release 2014.03\r\n* Node Version: v0.10.26\r\n* Browser: Chrome/33.0.1750.152'
