2635,'','POST / Add returns location header\nWhenever an object is created via the API, the response should include a location header for the newly created resource.\r\n\r\nFor example, if we send a POST request to `/ghost/api/v0.1/posts`, we should get back a header like:\r\n\r\n`Location: /ghost/api/v0.1/posts/2/`\r\n\r\nDoing a GET request on the location provided would return us the object created.\r\n\r\nThis should be part of `api/index.js` as it is a piece of additional processing which should be handled by the `requestHandler` similarly to the cache invalidation headers.\r\n\r\nAll of the API route tests should add tests to verify that the correct header is added to the response.'
