2577,'','Ghost Auto-Preview does not work in editor\nHello again.\r\nI was just publishing my first post after upgrading to 0.4.2. I found that now I need to click on the preview pane for it to update. Is this because of the new touchscreen support? I would prefer to not have to click a million times** to make sure my post is perfect. Would this be considered a bug? Is there a fix? Thank you! (PS: Your blogging platform is almost absolutely perfect besides this issue.)\r\n\r\n** That was really a hyperbole.'
2576,'',"Just a poke for vim style editor support.\nI came across these projects today...\r\n\r\njs port: https://github.com/itsjoesullivan/js-vim\r\nweb embed: https://github.com/itsjoesullivan/js-vim-embed/\r\n\r\nLooks that guy took things pretty far earlier this year, but then stopped (as these things go).  \r\n\r\n\r\nI personally would really like vim style editing for ghost or any other js based split screen markdown writing tool.  Markdown is objectively useful for anyone looking to write and format quickly, vim also matches this criteria. That said, I make an attempt to plant a seed here.  It would not need to be full featured, just targeted at markdown efficiencies.\r\n\r\nI'll likely keep exploring this myself, but I think the effort made there is worth a look.  Even writers can benefit from being mouse free if they take the time to form new habits.\r\n\r\nKeep up the good work!\r\n"
2575,'','Running Ghost under nobody:nogroup results in inaccessible control panel\nNow obviously, not a typical use case for Ghost, but if I start Ghost via this Upstart script:\r\n\r\n``` upstart\r\nstart on startup\r\n\r\nsetuid nobody\r\nsetgid nogroup\r\n\r\nscript\r\n    cd /path/to/ghost/install\r\n    npm start\r\nend script\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe backend control panel is inaccessible (504 Gateway Timeout), maybe because it is attempting to write to the file system and the user/group is set to nobody? Feel free to close if Ghost is not meant to be started as "nobody", though it\'d be neat to support from a security standpoint.'
