2551,'',"[API] Added email sending endpoint to the API.\ncloses #2550\r\n\r\n- Added new API module named 'mail'\r\n- Added routes for the mail endpoint\r\n- Added 'send a test email' button to the debug settigns page\r\n- Added handler to this button which sends and AJAX request to the mail API endpoint"
2550,'',"API endpoint and ugly debug button to send a test email\nAs we move towards having apps that may want to use more advanced mail functionality, it'd probably be useful to be able to send a test email.\r\n\r\nThe response from trying to send an email should turn up if there are any catchable errors, and verifying receipt of the email confirms that mail does in fact work.\r\n\r\nThe test email should contain some nice friendly text. The welcome email is a good place to get inspiration, possibly something like:\r\n\r\n> **Hello there!**\r\n> Excellent! You've successfully setup your email config for your Ghost blog over on {{url}}.\r\n> If you hadn't, you wouldn't be reading this email, but you are, so it looks like all is well :)\r\n> Happy emailing!\r\n> xoxo\r\n> Team Ghost\r\n> <https://ghost.org>\r\n\r\nThe endpoint should probably be something like\r\n\r\nPOST: `/ghost/api/v0.1/mail/test/`\r\n\r\nAnd the button in the ugly debug tools an be green or blue I suppose, they're ugly debug tools :+1: "
2549,'','Use current user in models\ncloses #2058\r\n- fixed apiContext as suggested in the issue\r\n- added user to options object for models\r\n- added api.users.register() for public registration\r\n- changed models to use options.user for created_by, updated_by,\r\nauthor_id and published_by\r\n- added override to session model to avoid created_by and updated_by\r\nvalues\r\n- added user (id: 1) to tests\r\n- added user (id: 1) for registration\r\n- added user (id: 1) for import, fixtures and default settings\r\n- added user (id: 1) for user update\r\n- added user (id: 1) for settings update (dbHash, installedApps, update\r\ncheck)\r\n- updated bookshelf to version 0.6.8'
