2539,'',"Bug: Tag Changes to Old Location if Removed and Entered Again in Same Update\n<h4>Issue Summary:</h4>\r\n\r\nIf you have a post with tags, such as 'Popular' and 'Free', and then decide you want to add a tag in between those because you want 'Free' to be last (for using the @last theme feature), you have to first remove 'Free' tag, add the new tag, update post, then add in 'Free' and update post again, otherwise the 'Free' tag will automatically switch back to the middle location where it was originally. Causes the need for multiple updates instead of just one.\r\n\r\nVideo of this happening:\r\n![tag order bug](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4715098/2584067/900a41d8-b9d9-11e3-89f2-735e456196fb.gif)\r\n\r\n<h4>Steps to Reproduce:</h4>\r\n\r\n1. Create any new post or open an existing post\r\n2. Add 2 tags such as 'Popular' and 'Free'\r\n3. Remove one tag, add a new tag such as '1' and then add the tag you just removed and update the post\r\n4. The tag you added last will switch back to the place it was originally\r\n\r\nTo get around this, you remove the tag, add the new one in, and hit update, then add the old tag you removed in again, and hit update.\r\n\r\n<h4>Technical Details</h4>\r\nGhost Version: 0.4.2\r\nClient OS: Mac OSX 10.9.2\r\nServer OS: Mac OSX 10.9.2\r\nNode Version: v0.10.18\r\nBrowser: Chrome v33.0.1750.152"
