2524,'','Included Jquery is not Minified\n### Issue Summary\r\nI just updated to the latest stable release of Ghost and found a small issue.\r\n\r\nThe automatically inserted Jquery by the `ghost_foot` helper uses a development non-minified version of Jquery. \r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce:\r\n\r\n* Use the 0.4.2 stable release.\r\n* Use a theme that includes the {{ghost_foot}} directive. \r\n* Run Ghost and open browser to the index page. \r\n\r\n### Observed result\r\n\r\n* `/public/jquery.js` is not minified. \r\n\r\n### Desired result\r\n\r\n* Jquery should be the production and minified version. \r\n* Jquery should follow convention and be named `jquery.min.js`\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\nGhost: v0.4.2\r\nNode.js: v0.10.26\r\nBrowser: Chrome v33.0.1750.154 m\r\nClient: Windows 8.1\r\nServer: Ubuntu 12.04.4 LTS'
2523,'','Bug: Bower installing to "app/components" instead of "bower_components"\n### Issue Summary\r\nBower is installing components to `app/components` instead of `bower_components`.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. `git clone git@github.com:TryGhost/Ghost.git`\r\n2. [Follow Quickstart instructions](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/tree/8ae55ff8cf05ca01dac650a72a1bd39641cc782b#quickstart)\r\n3. Have a drunk global Bower configuration?\r\n\r\nI\'m not sure why this is happening, I thought Bower installs to `bower_components` by default (and I don\'t think I\'ve changed anything but I must have). I had a couple coworkers also try to install from `git clone`; one was able to run it locally, the other had the same problem.\r\n\r\n*Edit*: Of course I dug around for 3 hours only to find #2386 within 5 minutes of posting this. \r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master - latest commit:  8ae55ff\r\n* Client OS: OSX 10.9.2\r\n* Server OS: local\r\n* Node Version: v0.10.12, v0.10.25, v0.11.11\r\n* Browser: Chrome v33.0.1750.152'
