2485,'',"Image file names get sanitised with underscores, hyphens might be better\nIt has been suggested to me by one of our users that search engines will read hyphens in URLs as spaces, meaning that words separated by hyphens in file names and file paths can be read.\r\n\r\nWhen we sanitise file names, we replace all non-word characters with '_', therefore a simple change to '-' may cause a minor improvement in SEO.\r\n\r\nI have no idea whether this is definitely a thing, but a quick Google search seems to verify. It's such a simple change - worth it?"
