2480,'','Empty tags get named post and then post-x\nSummary of Issue \r\n------------------------------- \r\n\r\nWhen creating a tag that consists entirely of characters that will be stripped out for the slug, the slug that Ghost uses is "post" and then "post-x" for any subsequent tags.\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce \r\n------------------------------- \r\n\r\n* create a new post\r\n* add a tag of: ,./\r\n* publish your post\r\n* now visit your post and click on your tag\r\n\r\nObserved result \r\n------------------------------- \r\n\r\nWhen I first saw this behaviour I was confused why the URL of my tag was "/tag/post/", until I created another tag that had all characters stripped out of the slug and the URL became "/tag/post-2/".\r\n\r\nI would suggest changing the logic to make the URL /tag/tag/ and then /tag/tag-2/, to make it less confusing.\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2014-03-22 at 11 49 56 pm](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/4643742/2492802/7ad5ba1a-b257-11e3-8ec8-1779bb96c73c.png)\r\n\r\nAdditional Information \r\n-------------------------------\r\n\r\nClient OS: Mac OS X 10.9.2\r\nServer OS: Amazon Linux AMI 2013.09.2\r\nNode Version: v0.10.26\r\nGhost Build Number: 0.4.2-rc1\r\nBrowser: Chrome 33.0.1750.152'
