2472,'',"[Ember.js] Implement Notifications for Ember\ncloses #2417\r\n- Adds NotificationsView\r\n- Shows notifications in application.hbs\r\n- Adds notification view\r\n\r\nThis PR implements notifications as per #2417. \r\n\r\nI'm trying to implement something similar to: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/14288980/global-notifications-view-using-ember (componentFor however is deprecated - but the idea should be clear).\r\n\r\nNotifications are implemented as a ComponentView with a custom itemClassType to render individual notifications. \r\n\r\n\r\n![selfie-1](http://i.imgur.com/1VrJgK1.png)\r\n"
2471,'',"Better theme error handling\nWhen a theme is working fine, and I fuck up one of my handlebars tags, no error is shown until Ghost has been restarted.\r\n\r\nEg.\r\n\r\nEnter `{{{@blog.title}}` somewhere - when refreshing the page, nothing happens - until Ghost is restarted - then you get an error message on trying to load the same page. \r\n\r\nI'm not overly picky about how it's done, I appreciate that there are technical constraints - but I'm sure we could improve how this is handled to give the user some feedback about their being some broken code in their theme."
