2468,'',"Bug: Error / warning messages can get muddled\nI have noticed that the errors and warnings shown at the start of Ghost can sometimes get muddled up, so that the related parts are not together. Here's an example:\r\n\r\n![muddled](http://puu.sh/7CHRN.png)\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Add several themes to `content/themes`\r\n1. Make sure some of them have no `package.json`\r\n1. Make sure that one or two have a broken `package.json` file\r\n1. Start ghost and see what happens\r\n\r\n### Technical details: \r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master (latest commit: )\r\n* Client OS: Windows 7\r\n* Server OS: Localhost\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.25"
2467,'','Bug: Javascript assets in /public redirect to subfolders\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nJavascript assets 301 redirect to a subfolder named for the file. E.g.:\r\n\r\n`/public/jquery.js?v=2l2i323li`\r\n\r\nRedirects to:\r\n\r\n`/public/jquery.js/?v=2l2i323li`\r\n\r\nWhich results in a 404 for the script, and all script dependencies fail. This is happening to me with jQuery. \r\n\r\n![image](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/589550/2485154/a20e076a-b115-11e3-9d76-cb387a79fc6f.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Updated to latest ghost via `git pull origin master`\r\n2. Ran `npm update`\r\n3. Ran `grunt prod`\r\n\r\nIssue is now persistent, checking out previous versions (inspected through `git reflog`) no longer resolves the issue.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master - latest commit:  6d1c1b4\r\n* Client OS: OSX Mavericks 10.9.2\r\n* Server OS: Ubunto 12.0.4 LTS\r\n* Node Version: v0.10.21\r\n* Browser: Chrome 33.0.1750.152\r\n'
2466,'','API end points for Apps\nAs it will be possible to register API end points for Apps using the *Routes API*, I would like to propose to have the API end points for Apps registered using the following scheme.\r\n\r\n`GET`, `POST`, `PUT`, `PATCH`, `DELETE` `/ghost/api/v0.1/apps/<app-name>/object/`\r\n\r\nExample Kudos App:\r\n\r\n**Add new Kudos counter for post with id: 1**\r\n```\r\nPost /ghost/api/v0.1/apps/kudos-app/kudos/\r\n\r\n{\r\n\tkudos = [{\r\n\t\tpost: 1,\r\n\t\tcount: 0\r\n\t}]\r\n}\r\n```\r\n**Get Kudos for post with id: 1**\r\n```\r\nGET /ghost/api/v0.1/apps/kudos-app/kudos/1\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Increment Kudos counter by one**\r\nI think that the correct way to increment a counter would be PATCH with an increment operation. At the moment only  replace operations are supported by JSON API so this would not comply with the specification. I have opened a proposal to add `increment` operations to JSON API (https://github.com/json-api/json-api/issues/214).\r\n\r\n```\r\nPATCH /ghost/api/v0.1/apps/kudos-app/kudos/1\r\n\r\n[\r\n  { "op": "increment", "path": "/kudos/0/count", "value": 1 }\r\n]\r\n```'
