2460,'',"Bug: Importing large content fails if a post w/ a '$' in a tag already exists.\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nWhen importing our site data (255 posts, tags such as ('$1', '5', 'Popular')), the import fails when a post already exists with a tag that has a '$' in it. If I create a new Ghost instance, and straight import, it works. If i create a new Ghost instance, create a new post with the tag '$1', then try and import, it does not work.\r\n\r\nThis bug may be content specific, because with other example content I have made it imports just fine. I am happy to email my content to the Ghost team, just do not want public.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nThis import works:\r\n1. Install a brand new Instance of Ghost\r\n2. Log in and create a test post with a post tag of '1'\r\n3. Head to /debug and import content\r\n4. Content will import just fine\r\n\r\nGif of import working:\r\n![ghost_import_bug_works](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/4715098/2477988/a1c8b87e-b078-11e3-80ba-1cc76bb07b91.gif)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThis import does NOT work:\r\n1. Install a brand new Instance of ghost\r\n2. Log in and create a test post with a post tag of '$1'\r\n3. Head to /debug and import content \r\n4. Ghost will sit for 5 minutes, and then throw an error\r\n\r\nGif of import NOT working:\r\n![ghost_import_bug_broken](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/4715098/2477992/ab9d4d92-b078-11e3-8797-27ae45d93f16.gif)\r\n(After 5 minutes of waiting)\r\n![ghost_import_bug_broken_5minlater](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/4715098/2477995/b3b976ae-b078-11e3-80b7-16f29f9fae0e.gif)\r\n\r\nThis is a bug because the import fails to add any data when the post with the '$1' tag exists.\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.4.2-rc1 (installed via npm and direct download, both have problem)\r\n* Client OS: Mac OSX 10.9.2\r\n* Server OS: Mac OSX 10.9.2\r\n* Node Version: v0.10.22\r\n* Browser: Chrome v33.0.1750.152"
2458,'','0.4.2 Release Candidate 1 Ready for Testing\nThere is now a release candidate of 0.4.2, called [0.4.2-rc1](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/releases/tag/0.4.2-rc1), which has been published ready for testing.\r\n\r\nIf you are able to do some testing, this would be much appreciated.\r\n\r\nIf you find any **bugs**, please raise them as separate issues according to the [contributing guidelines](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#bugs) \r\n\r\nIf you complete **successful** testing, please let us know by adding a comment here detailing what you tested and on what environment, covering relevant things like OS, browser, prod/dev mode, database etc.\r\n\r\nSome important areas for testing:\r\n\r\n- using production environment \r\n- using MySQL\r\n- sub directories\r\n- the update process & update notifications\r\n- editing on mobile\r\n- using the npm module (now published!)\r\n- probably a lot more!\r\n\r\nThe final release is scheduled for 25th March if all goes well\r\n\r\nThanks!'
