2420,'','Link to rich text in the editor\nThe markdown editor could be improved if you could add a new tag to it for the embedding purposes. For example the user enters:\r\n\r\n> ^http://example.com^\r\n\r\nThen you could use a library such as olly.js (https://github.com/abeisgreat/Olly.js) and convert that link to a reach media text. For example if they enter the link to a youtube video it automatically embeds the youtube player and removes the link.\r\n\r\nThis will make writing a lot more easier as the library that I suggested before covers a wide range of different websites such as soundcloud, spotify, youtube, vimeo and etc.'
