2400,'',"Broken modal background overlays\n2x inconsistent behaviour in modals. This is in both 0.4.1 and latest master.\r\n\r\n## 1. Background overlay loads on first click, but not second. (Master)\r\n\r\n![bg1](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/120485/2428752/b97da898-ac5a-11e3-9867-d2061674e19b.gif)\r\n\r\n## 2. Background overlay doesn't load at all (0.4.1)\r\n\r\n![bg2](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/120485/2428755/d347f44a-ac5a-11e3-8a38-aa12114edc93.gif)\r\n"
2399,'',"[Discussion] created_by/updated_by without a user\nMost rows of our database scheme have a field for create_by and updated_by values. At the moment these values are always referring to the admin user with `id: 1`. When permissions are in place these values are going to impact the behavior of Ghost. I open this issue to discuss what the values of created_by and updated_by should be for changes Ghost does without an active user? I'm looking at the following cases:\r\n\r\n- initialization of fixtures\r\n- dbHash"
2398,'','CodeMirror Refactor & Upgrade\nThis is step 1 of a refactor towards fixing: #2385, #2108\r\n\r\nThese issues require that CodeMirror be upgraded to a version with a different API & that the code be much more modular so that we can swap out CodeMirror for a standard TextArea for mobile.\r\n\r\nAt the same time this refactor is improving our CodeClimate score: https://codeclimate.com/github/ErisDS/Ghost/compare/cm-refactor\r\naaand, I think it will make reimplementing the editor in Ember.js easier.\r\n\r\nIt is a [WIP] and is not intended to be merged yet.\r\n\r\nStill to come:\r\n\r\n- better, more consistent structuring of each module\r\n- lots of commenting to help decipher the code\r\n- swap `setLine` and `removeLine` for `replacerange` anywhere they appear\r\n'
