2373,'',"[Ember.js] Naming convention for components & helpers\nTurns out Ember components need to have a `-` in them. This makes for unfortunate / ugly naming if you try to force it in, so it would be better to pick a prefix convention like `gh-component` or `ghost-component`. \r\n\r\n~~One for @JohnONolan to confirm whether there is anything particular that fits with branding, otherwise, lets just pick one (I think shorter is better) and PR it.~~\r\n\r\n**Update:** we've decided on `gh-` as this matches with what's happening in https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost-UI\r\n\r\nThis is a reasonably simple issue for someone, to go through and rename all the components and helpers and ensure all uses of them are updated to reflect this."
