2344,'',"Blank admin signup\nHi,\r\n\r\nI'm trying to use Ghost on my server (FreeBSD 9.2) with the last version of nodejs and Ghost. \r\nEverything was good when I did the installation but when I go to .../ghost/signup/ I have a page with nothing (even if I have content on my home page and welcome-to-ghost/ works great).\r\nWhat should I do ?\r\n\r\nHave a nice day\r\nSincerely "
2343,'','Verbose error message on session expiry\nRelated to #2092 - a smaller interim step.\r\n\r\nCurrently if you leave the editor open for 12 hours and then try to save, you get a red notification saying `"Your post could not be saved as a draft. Unknown Error"`\r\n\r\nI would like it very much if we could avoid "Unknown Error" from ever appearing in any UI.\r\n\r\nBetter (interim): "Your session has expired, please back up your work and log in again."\r\n\r\nthoughts?'
2342,'','Nocache404\nRemove the caching of 404 pages instead of caching them for an hour.'
2341,'ErisDS','Rss support for tags\ncloses #2260\r\n- added routes for /tag/:slug/rss and /tag/:slug/rss/page/:page\r\n- added support for tag in the rss controller\r\n- added route tests for each extra case'
2340,'',"Add Spell Checking in the Blog Editor\nAs a blog author, I want to use the online editor as the sole tool to create my content. However, I tend to make spelling mistakes as I type...and sometimes my brain just gets things wrong too. The current editor has no feedback on misspelled words so it's easy to miss them and publish content with errors. I can get around this by proofing 3-4 times and using an external document editing tool, but I'd rather not have to do that.\r\n\r\nPeople have become accustomed to spell checking as a base line feature in any document editing software. Seeing that it was absent was immediately off putting for me and is a *constant* source of pain for me (a paying customer). When people ask me about the ghost product I can list a lot of positives, but in trying to be honest, I have to list this as a major shortcoming right now."
