2316,'',"Bug: Settings content pane gets rendered twice on initial load\n### Issue Summary\r\nIf you go to `ghost/settings`, the content pane gets rendered twice. This happens only on the initial page load.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. In [L58](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/blob/master/core/client/views/settings.js#L58) of `client/views/settings.js` add a `console.log` statement.\r\n2. Go to `ghost/settings` and see console output.\r\n\r\nYou'll find the message printed twice.\r\n\r\nThis is a bug because the page should not be rendered again once it has already been rendered.\r\n\r\n###Solution\r\n\r\n[L64](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/blob/master/core/client/views/settings.js#L64) should have `this.pane.id` instead of `this.pane.el.id`. \r\n`this.pane.el.id` is always returning an empty string whereas `this.pane.id` returns the `id` of the current pane.\r\n\r\nI'll be filing a PR with this solution in a while.\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master:  d996ff68e7c5b01999a9304f731b183ca8eeb14a\r\n* Client OS: ElementaryOS (Based on Ubuntu 12.04)\r\n* Server OS: ElementaryOS (Based on Ubuntu 12.04)\r\n* Node Version: v0.10.16\r\n* Browser: Chrome v32"
2315,'','Publish post as private for getting feedback\nOften you want to be able to get some feedback on a post before publishing it and at this stage the process is building a gist on github then sharing the url to collect feebacks and then modify it in ghost. \r\n\r\nIt will help to be able to publish in private which make the url available but the post not appearing on the home.'
2314,'',"No spell check and can't type on iOS mobile devices.\nThe Ghost editor still has no spell check which makes it really annoying to use. I tend to prefer writing my posts as private [gists](http://gist.github.com) and paste them over when ready. Someone on the forum made a Chrome extension I will look into but I wanted to make sure the lack of spell check was logged as an issue.\r\n\r\nAlso, I can't seem to type on iPhone or iPad mini. I tap the editor section as much as I want and it never places a cursor or brings up a keyboard. It works fine from Chrome or Firefox on my Macbook Pro.\r\n\r\nNote: I'm using the latest source as of this writing."
