2305,'','Validation failure error message when checking \'Static Page\' checkbox\nChecking the \'Static page\' checkbox while editing a post causes this error message to pop up: "Validation [\'isIn\'] of field [\'page\'] failed.".\r\n\r\nI believe this is due to validation that has been added in this commit: https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/commit/ac7f4f05c43196cc1117e0dc44bbafabefabad0f\r\n\r\nSpecifically, in the file core/server/data/schema.js, on line 11, it adds the following validation for the \'page\' attribute of posts:\r\n```\r\n {\'isIn\': [\'true\', \'false\']}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI checked the postData being sent int from the HTTP PUT request sent when the checkbox is clicked, and it contains the attribute " \'page\': true ".\r\n\r\nThat validation bit I posted above should probably be this instead:\r\n```\r\n{\'isIn\': [\'0\', \'1\']}\r\n```\r\nThere may be a better way of fixing this, but this seems to fix this particular issue. I was concerned that the validator would complain that "true" is not the same as \'1\', but... it seems to work regardless. Perhaps this has something to do with the fact that it is stored in the database as an int, or maybe there is some implicit casting happening, I\'m not sure. The validator.js library being used doesn\'t seem to have a \'isBool\' validator.'
2304,'','Bug: apostrophe in image alt tag causes word count to be incorrect\nUsing this syntax for important an image:\r\n\r\n```markdown\r\n![Some of my old \'base\' drawings](/content/images/2014/Feb/base_drawings.jpg)\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd then attempting to pull in only 50 words on the front page of the blog:\r\n\r\n```hbs\r\n{{content words="50"}}\r\n```\r\n\r\nResults in nearly the entire post showing up on that front page. If I remove the apostrophe I get just the first little bit of the post again.\r\n\r\nI\'m on Ghost 0.4.1'
