2293,'',"Support for markdown reference link syntax as well as inline syntax\nWhilst writing a simple html scraper to generate the required json for importing into Ghost, I've hit a problem. The html -> markdown service I'm using converts html anchor tags into reference style links as described on the [official markdown syntax page](http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/syntax).\r\n\r\nThis syntax appears to work when viewing a [full blog post](http://the-photographic-me-um.ghost.io/llynnau-mymbyr/) but doesn't render correctly in the [blog list page](http://the-photographic-me-um.ghost.io), nor in the editor.\r\n\r\nI'm using ghost.org hosting thus running version 0.4.1."
