2288,'','Fresh Install Mac\nHey all,\r\n\r\nJust grabbed the latest build here from GitHub to have a play around with as I\'ve just got the internet installed at my new home. However, I cannot get it running at all. I am running on the latest OS X, latest build of node.js 0.10.26 and the build of Ghost is c64148f361.\r\n\r\nWhen I ran npm install --production I get everything fine except at the end where I get this...\r\n\r\n````\r\n> sqlite3@2.2.0 install /Users/benhodder/GhostDev/node_modules/sqlite3\r\n> node-pre-gyp install --fallback-to-build\r\n\r\nnode-pre-gyp http GET http://node-sqlite3.s3.amazonaws.com/Release/node_sqlite3-v2.2.0-node-v11-darwin-x64.tar.gz\r\nnode-pre-gyp http 200 http://node-sqlite3.s3.amazonaws.com/Release/node_sqlite3-v2.2.0-node-v11-darwin-x64.tar.gz\r\n[sqlite3] Success: "lib/node_sqlite3.node" is installed\r\nconnect-slashes@1.2.0 node_modules/connect-slashes\r\n\r\ncolors@0.6.2 node_modules/colors\r\n\r\nnode-uuid@1.4.1 node_modules/node-uuid\r\n\r\nnode-polyglot@0.3.0 node_modules/node-polyglot\r\n\r\nsemver@2.2.1 node_modules/semver\r\n\r\nbcryptjs@0.7.10 node_modules/bcryptjs\r\n\r\nvalidator@1.4.0 node_modules/validator\r\n\r\nwhen@2.7.0 node_modules/when\r\n\r\nfs-extra@0.8.1 node_modules/fs-extra\r\n├── jsonfile@1.1.1\r\n├── rimraf@2.2.6\r\n├── ncp@0.4.2\r\n└── mkdirp@0.3.5\r\n\r\ndownsize@0.0.5 node_modules/downsize\r\n└── xregexp@2.0.0\r\n\r\nrss@0.2.1 node_modules/rss\r\n├── xml@0.0.12\r\n└── mime@1.2.11\r\n\r\nshowdown@0.3.1 node_modules/showdown\r\n\r\nlodash@2.4.1 node_modules/lodash\r\n\r\nunidecode@0.1.3 node_modules/unidecode\r\n\r\nbusboy@0.0.12 node_modules/busboy\r\n├── readable-stream@1.1.11 (debuglog@0.0.2, string_decoder@0.10.25-1, core-util-is@1.0.1)\r\n└── dicer@0.1.5 (streamsearch@0.1.2)\r\n\r\nbookshelf@0.6.1 node_modules/bookshelf\r\n├── trigger-then@0.1.1\r\n├── inflection@1.2.7\r\n├── backbone@1.1.2 (underscore@1.6.0)\r\n├── bluebird@0.10.14-0\r\n└── lodash@2.3.0\r\n\r\nexpress-hbs@0.7.9 node_modules/expr