2245,'','Wrong cursor position in Markdown editor for Unicode\nCursor position messed up in markdown editor as seen in the screenshot below.\r\n\r\n![Screenshot](http://i.imgur.com/rpSGxrp.png)\r\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nA summary of the issue and the browser/OS environment in which it occurs. If\r\nsuitable, include the steps required to reproduce the bug.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Copy this into the editor "ทดสอบการกรอก ข้อมูลภาษาไทย ว่าสามารถแสดงผลได้ถูกต้องหรือไม่"\r\n2. Make sure the sentence got wrapped on to multiple line.\r\n3. Move cursor to the second line and try editing. The cursor will most likely be on the whitespace.\r\n\r\n### Expected outcome:\r\nCursor should be in the correct place.\r\n\r\n### Technical details: \r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: trial\r\n* Client OS: Mac OS X 10.9.1\r\n* Browser: Chrome 32.0.1700.107'
2244,'',"Errors when importing data from 0.4.1 to latest\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nI went to my instance on `ghost.io` (I'm presuming this is 0.4.1) and exported data. After exporting data, I imported the data to a local instance of Ghost running on latest.\r\n\r\nUpon a successful import, if you try to navigate around Ghost is throwing up errors all over the place. Most of them appear to be unhandled promise rejections stemming from a `SemVer` compare of `0` vs `0.4.1` that comes from the `showUpdateNotification` function in `update-check.js`.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Export data from another instance\r\n2. Import data into local instance\r\n3. Do **not** restart your local instance\r\n4. Navigate around the admin interface, note the errors being logged\r\n\r\n### Technical details: \r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master (latest commit: 4b643361191e98f6ad5406f257ed91b1f7da058f)\r\n* Client OS: Windows 8.1\r\n* Server OS: Windows 8.1\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.7\r\n* Browser: Chrome 33.0.1750.117 beta-m"
