2212,'','[Proposal] Repository (Re-)Organization\nIn trying to start using ghost full time I have run into issues versioning ghost along side my `content` code cleanly in my own site\'s repository.\r\n\r\nI would like to propose that `core` should be it\'s own repository, containing a lot of the files that currently reside in the root (`Gemfile`, `Gruntfile.js`, `.travis.yml`, etc..).\r\n\r\nThis would provide better segregation of "user code" and "core code" and allow for clean versioning of `core` along side our user code, with the added benifit of a user being able to submodule `core` in their own site\'s repository.\r\n\r\nThis would likely help with #2078 as the `index.js` could just as easily point to the `node_modules` directory.'
