2170,'',"Enhancement: Add initialization to models\n@hswolff suggestion in issue #1655 \r\n\r\n> Actually now that you mention it...one thing I'd love for the models to have is the ability to be instantiated upon invocation and not upon having the module required.\r\n\r\n>What I mean by this is right now there's a bit of a bottleneck. We cannot load any model files before the config.js file has been loaded as Bookshelf is set up directly in the module and not behind a function that allows you to set it up at your own desire.\r\n\r\n>This I believe is one big thing that is in the way of us no longer having to require server in a promise. I've also run into issues related to this when testing.\r\n\r\n>It would be great if core/server/models/base was moved into a function on module.exports (with every other model file following suit) so that when we wanted we'd be able to call initBookshelf() to begin the bootup of the models, as opposed to having to delay requiring the entire module.\r\n\r\n>I'd loove if that was done. :love_hotel:\r\n\r\nI open this issue as a reminder that this needs to be done, but I would like to get #1401 and #2058 done first, because we would do things twice otherwise."
