2157,'',"Ghost Filters are broken\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nCalling `Filters.registerFilter` from an app via the proxy object causes an error:\r\n\r\n> 'ERROR: Cannot read property 'ghost_foot' of undefined'\r\n\r\nFull error message (when trying to register the 'ghost_foot' filter):\r\nhttps://gist.github.com/ErisDS/e55f095150114e1fc6ad\r\n\r\nIt seems that the `this.filterCallbacks` is always undefined, so I guess the way the module is setup to get instantiated isn't working properly. \r\n\r\nThere are also two properties, `this.filterCallbacks` and `this.filters` I think only one is needed. I believe once upon a long before GitHub we may have tried to maintain a list of all the available filters - this may be useful but isn't done at the moment.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Create an App as per [the wiki guide](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/wiki/Apps-Getting-Started-for-Ghost-Devs)\r\n2. Add the following snippet to the `activate` function:\r\n```\r\n    this.app.filters.register('ghost_foot', function () {\r\n        console.log('foot');\r\n    });\r\n```\r\n3. Make sure the app is set in `activeApps` as per [the wiki guide](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/wiki/Apps-Getting-Started-for-Ghost-Devs)\r\n4. Run npm start\r\n\r\n### Technical details: \r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://gist.github.com/ErisDS/e55f095150114e1fc6ad"
