2136,'','Bug: Changing title of already drafted post will not properly generate a new slug\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nAfter saving a post in draft for the first time the slug is generated from the title. Changing the title afterwards and removing the slug will cause Ghost to regenerate the slug, but will yield a slug in the `post-n` format instead of a slug generated from the title. \r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. New Post\r\n2. Enter Title and save as draft\r\n3. Change Title, remove slug \r\n4. New slug is generated in post-n format.\r\n\r\nI would expect the slug to be empty when I remove it while the post is still a draft. The placeholder suggests that the slug will become the slugified version of my title.\r\n\r\n![slug-behaviour](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/176576/2108626/029a59ee-8fe2-11e3-9648-6e516fc7dc7f.gif)\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.4.1 (and current master)\r\n* Browser: Chrome 30'
