2093,'',"Markdown issues with new lines.\nLine breaks are not always working. It's hard to describe what is happening, therefore I made a gif. I would expect the formatted (right) being the same as the input (left).\r\n\r\n![markdown](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/2971735/2058040/302747fa-8b5a-11e3-8a5b-fffecc97876c.gif)\r\n\r\nI narrowed it down and changed a regular expression. I thought I got it working until I did a `grunt validate`. It starts failing at https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/blob/master/core/test/unit/client_showdown_int_spec.js. This is rather strange because if I [reconstruct that output manually in JSfiddle](http://jsfiddle.net/F4ZJP/23/), it perfectly matches the provided regular expression.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTake https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/blob/master/core/test/unit/client_showdown_int_spec.js#L75 for example. It fails with\r\n```\r\n6) Showdown client side converter should not treat pre blocks with pre-text differently:\r\n   AssertionError: expected '<pre>\\nthis is `a\\\\_test` and this\\\\_too and finally_this_is\\n</pre>  ' to match /^<pre>\\nthis is `a\\\\_test` and this\\\\_too and finally_this_is\\n<\\/pre>$/\r\n```\r\n\r\nPutting said input line that in my [modified JSFiddle](http://jsfiddle.net/43cNX/1/), the output of *Haunted Markdown* and *Fixed Haunted Markdown* is exactly the same. Also the [regular expression}(http://regex101.com/r/yP1gS7) matches.\r\n\r\nI hope I didn't write this too complicated.\r\n\r\n"
2091,'',"Load Apps Sandboxed\nAn attempt at #2007\r\n\r\n- Based on suggestions from ~~@gotdibbs, loading with an eval approach~~ @hswolff to use native Module class.\r\n- Load relative modules in child sandboxes\r\n\r\n~~This gets a little hairy because of things like __dirname getting set to the core/server/apps path when we `eval`, but it's a decent start after some hackery.  I feel like the test cases give some faithful things a person might try and be sneaky about.~~\r\n\r\nI know @sebgie mentioned a more white list than black list approach, but I wasn't sure how to do that.  Feedback welcome."
2090,'hswolff','Bug: Page.hbs sometimes not recognised\nIn certain situations the `pages.hbs` file is ignored.\r\n\r\n## Scenarios & Observed results\r\n\r\n> If I switch themes to a different theme, the `page.hbs` file is being called. \r\n> If I copy `page.hbs` from Casper into my theme folder, it does not get called. \r\n> If I rename my theme folder to something else, the `page.hbs` file gets called. \r\n> If I rename my theme folder back to the original name, `page.hbs` does not get called\r\n\r\n## Desired result\r\n\r\nThe `page.hbs` is always referenced if it exists.\r\n\r\n## Forum topics related\r\n* https://ghost.org/forum/bugs-suggestions/5065-v0-4-1-page-hbs-doesn-t-seem-to-do-anything/\r\n\r\n## Additional Information\r\n\r\n**Version**: 0.4.1'
2089,'','Bug: Tag popup is no longer navigational with arrow keys\nWhen the tag popup appears, you can no longer navigate through the tags as before.\r\n\r\n## Scenario\r\n\r\n* Create post\r\n* Start typing a tag that already exists\r\n* Use arrow keys to navigate the suggestion list\r\n\r\n## Observed result\r\n\r\nOnly the top and bottom tag suggestion can be selected.\r\n\r\n## Desired result\r\n\r\nThe user can navigate through the list and select a tag freely using the arrow keys.\r\n\r\n## Forum topics possibly related\r\n* https://ghost.org/forum/bugs-suggestions/5069-possible-bug-0-4-1-up-down-arrow-key-navigation-broken-for-tag-suggestion-popup-menu/\r\n\r\n## Additional Information\r\n\r\n**Browser**: All\r\n**Version**: 0.4.1\r\n**Node Version**: v0.10.21\r\n**OS**: Mac OS X 10.9'
2088,'',"Bug: Login/signup input:focus border misalignment\nAll of the inputs in the authentication process, so sign in, forgot password & sign up, when focused add a `1px` border, making the box `2px` *bigger* in each direction, making it misaligned with other inputs or its container.\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2014-01-31 at 09 00 05](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/390392/2048924/b7dcc31e-8a56-11e3-9ec1-525f1586d1ce.png)\r\n\r\nSee the bottom edge of the inputs here.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Go to the sign in/sign up page\r\n2. Focus on an input\r\n\r\n### Technical details: \r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 4.1 (via ghost.org hosted service)\r\n* Browser: Chrome 32\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nA fix would be to use a solid `box-shadow` which doesn't affect the dimensions, like: \r\n\r\n    box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px #AAA9A2;\r\n\r\nI know it's such a simple thing to send a PR for, but I wanted to check it wasn't done for a specific reason. I'll send a PR if this was a late night oversight."
2087,'','Bug: tag with apostrophe gets truncated upon entry\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nI have a tag (rich\'s cigar store) with an apostrophe whch was created in a previous post, that when added to a new post gets truncated.\r\n\r\n![screen shot 1](http://f.cl.ly/items/1f2M2r2r350B0k0A3b3o/Image%202014.02.03%2015%3A36%3A08.png)\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2](http://f.cl.ly/items/1f2e3s3t0k0N0a2A2u0w/Image%202014.02.03%2015%3A36%3A44.png)\r\n\r\nAfter creating a new post and typing a few characters for a tag I selected the suggested tag from the popup menu using the up/down arrow return key technique.  The tag I actually get is "rich" (everything before the apostrophe).\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Add a post with a tag that has an apostrophe in it.\r\n\r\n2. Create another post.\r\n\r\n3. In the tag field type the first few characters of the tag created in step 1 and select it either with keyboard commands or with the mouse.\r\n\r\nYou should see a truncated version of the original tag.\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.4 and 0.4.1\r\n* Client OS: Mac OS X 10.8.5\r\n* Server OS:  Mac OS X 10.7.5\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.24\r\n* Browser: Chrome'
