2078,'',"Publish Ghost to NPM\nThere are a few outstanding tasks that need to be completed before Ghost can be published as a npm module.\r\n\r\n- [x] 1. Don't require a compilation of assets #2239 \r\n- [ ] 2. Allow for ghost to be installed globally `-g` (possible include a project scaffold) #1001\r\n- [ ] 3. Allow ghost to be mounted as an express middleware component #827\r\n- [x] 4. Extend ghost bootup to take in a config object directly #1818\r\n- [x] 5. Allow configuration of `/content/` directory location #1858\r\n- [x] 6. Allow disabling of logging #2103\r\n- [x] 7. Document all ways to use ghost as a npm module (middleware, your own bootstrap script, globally) #2008\r\n- [x] 8. Conform to standards for npm modules with regard to running `npm test` #1053\r\n- [ ] 9. Tests to ensure all these features remain in a working state.  Including way to know when ghost has started so we know when we can accurately begin running our tests. #2225 \r\n"
