2073,'','Image upload failing when Ghost run in subdirectory\nI have ghost running under /blog/ subdirectory using 0.4.0. So far everything works fine except for setting the blog logo and and cover on the Admin settings page. Uploading an image there essentially hangs the UI.\r\n\r\nLooking on my local file system. I can see that the directory ```content/images/2014/Jan/``` has been created under the web server root, rather than the blog subdirectory. i.e. under ```domain/content/images/2014/Jan/``` instead of ```domain/blog/content/images/2014/Jan/```. The uploaded images have been successfully copied to there too.\r\n\r\nInterestingly, the variables targetDir and targetFilename in localfilesystem.js are relative ("content/images/2014/Jan") but when these are passed to fs.mkdir and fs.copy, the directories used are relative to the domain root, not the blog root.'
