2068,'',"Bug: published date in post settings is not being accepted in the various formats\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nWhen entering a date in one of the supposed accepted formats like `DD/MM/YY`  Ghost returns that the date is invalid. When entering a date with a 4 digit year such as `2014` Ghost gets confused, think you mean '20' and tells you off for setting a date in the future. \r\n\r\nThis shows that only the first format: `DD MMM YY HH:mm` is actually being used.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Create a post and publish it\r\n2. Try to set the date to something in the past, but using the format `DD/MM/YY` or  `DD MMM YYYY` \r\n\r\nWe should support all formats in the list and additionally lets do #1866 while we're here.\r\n\r\n### Technical details: \r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.4.1-rc1"
