2064,'',"Running Ghost using sudo but removing root privileges on port 80\nReference #1638 \r\n\r\nA discussion on this issue noted that it would be a good idea to have a configuration option to remove root privileges if running Ghost on lower port, such as port 80. \r\n\r\nThis is how Apache has worked for many years, and seems not only robust but is behavior most web developers have come to expect. \r\n\r\nRunning Ghost on higher ports and than having to mess with iptables is not necessarily for the faint of heart. A better approach would be for Ghost to provide the option of removing root privileges when running Ghost on port 80.\r\n\r\nHowever, I don't see any follow up to address this possible configuration change, which is why I'm opening this issue. "
