2043,'',"Bug: No line break after link\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nWhen creating a link with Markdown, you cannot insert a line break after the link. If you create the link and hit return, in the markdown display you get the line break, but no line break is shown in either the preview or the live site view.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Make a new post\r\n2. Use markdown to create a link\r\n3. Hit return\r\n4. Type some other words\r\n5. Publish the post\r\n\r\nThis is a bug because surely you should be able to have a link and then a line break?\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2014-01-26 at 19 22 04](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/5874012/2004743/31d39616-86bf-11e3-9fd3-876885cd4d30.png)\r\n\r\n### Technical Details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.4.0\r\n* Client OS: Mac OSX 10.9.1\r\n* Server OS: Apache 2.2.26\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.24\r\n* Browser: Safari 7.0.1\r\n\r\n### Some Notes\r\n\r\nI am aware that the editor will be overhauled in a future release of Ghost, which is great news, so this bug will most likely be squashed then. Also, I wasn't sure if this bug had already been reported, as I can't find where to search so apologises if someone got there first."
2042,'sebgie','Refactor click handlers on upload button.\nInstead of binding and unbinding, bind the data to the outer scope.\r\n\r\nFixes https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/issues/2028.'
2041,'','[request] enable logging of client ip if the server is behind a reverse proxy\nI am currently running a Ghost blog on Runkite (ghost 0.4.0), which uses some kind of reverse proxy to forward the requests from their public IP addresses to the private IP addresses the virtual servers are running on. This means that the access log written by Ghost only contains the IP of the reverse proxy and not the client IP. Since I do not have access to the front end servers, I cannot access the correct logs so client IP addresses are not available.\r\n\r\nThe same will probably happen when the Ghost blog is accessed via Cloudflare or similar CDN services.\r\nIt would be helpful if the logging could be switched to log the X-Forwarded-For IP instead or additionally similar to the CustomLog directive in Apache.\r\n\r\nA sample log looks like this:\r\n\r\n    192.237.247.189 - - [Sun, 26 Jan 2014 16:52:44 GMT] "GET /a-stupid-joke/ HTTP/1.1" 200 4544 "http://alex-ghost.apps.runkite.com/" "Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; rv:27.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/27.0"\r\n\r\nthe IP belongs to Rackspace so its probably to the Runkite infrastructure.\r\n\r\nI\'m not sure if apps will support custom logging, if not this should be a configuration option in the ghost system itself.\r\n\r\n'
2040,'','Bug: Multiple hits on the save/publish button can create multiple posts\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nOn slower connections, where there is time to hit the button multiple times, multiple posts can be created. Accidental double clicks, or multiple clicks because it appears nothing is happening can result in multiple posts being created and/or published.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Ensure your connection is slow enough to give you time between request and response.\r\n2. Open the editor\r\n3. Enter a title\r\n4. Click on the save draft or publish button as many times as you can before the request completes\r\n\r\nThis results in unexpected multiple posts. \r\n\r\nI believe the correct thing to do would be to disable the button until the request completes.\r\n\r\n### Technical details: \r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.4\r\n* Database: MySQL\r\n* Connection: SLOW\r\n'
2039,'','Fix : redirect to correct slug when switching between  param and keep 30...\n...1 instead of losing SEO\r\n\r\nIf I have old post without date indexed, then I tell in configuration I want dates, so when I access the old URL without date, I will be redirected to the one with date.\r\n'
2038,'','Improvement for published posts with no published_at\nThis is not a fix, merely an improvement for 0.4.1.\r\n\r\nI think the real issue stems from the problems documented in #1655 and will require major refactoring work.\r\n\r\nHere we at least make sure that the published date gets set on a future save.\r\n\r\nissue #2015\r\n\r\n- this is another little workaround / improvement to try to reduce the number of people who end up with a published post with no published_at set\r\n- I assume we need to complete #1655 to fix this properly'
2037,'','Fix : redirect to correct slug when switching between  param and keep 30...\n...1 instead of losing SEO\r\n\r\nIf I have old post without date indexed, then I tell in configuration I want dates, so when I access the old URL without date, I will be redirected to the one with date.'
2036,'ErisDS',"bug caused by unidecode's bug\nclose #1986\r\n- remove URL reserved chars after unidecode, because unidecode will produce some URL reserved chars."
2035,'sebgie',"Post settings don't render on change\nThis is an alternative solution to #1908\r\n\r\nfixes #1908\r\n\r\n- each individual update function handles rendering its own item on success or failure, rather than re-rendering the whole group\r\n- also resolved a bug where the published date didn't get reset properly on error"
2034,'','Notice: 0.4.1 is closing TODAY (27th Jan)\nI figured this was a good way to make a quick announcement.\r\n\r\nWe are closing 0.4.1 today, any PRs submitted to the 0.4-maintenance branch after Midnight GMT 27th Jan will not be considered for 0.4.1. \r\n\r\nAny unfixed bugs will have to wait for the next release.'
2033,'','Move NProgress to ajaxStart and ajaxComplete\nAs recommended by @gotdibbs https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/pull/2032#issuecomment-33309330\r\n\r\nIt may be better to move NProgress from wrapping sync calls, to being defined in ajaxStart and ajaxComplete.\r\n\r\nIt would be nice to clean it up so that this was the only place it was used.'
2032,'ErisDS','Have NProgress called for all ajax calls\nfixes #2011\r\n\r\n- rather than trigger NProgress for fetch calls\r\n I’ve moved it to be used for all sync calls\r\n\r\n- issue #2011 was a result of NProgress only being\r\n called during a fetch() call, which when saving\r\n is not used - save() is.  Sync is used by all\r\n ajax calls.'
2031,'','Standard Markdown linebreak support\nAs discussed in #1087, Ghost currently uses its own Markdown flavour that deviates from the spec by converting single line breaks to `<br>` tags.\r\n\r\nWhile I understand that this probably enhances usability for those not familiar with Markdown, it does create interoperability problems for those that use Markdown in lots of places, or use external editors which does hard wrapping.\r\n\r\nSo I hope it would be possible to make this configurable, so Markdown-nerds can still be happy :neckbeard:'
2028,'',"Import button does not work in Firefox\nIf you go to the semi-secret import page in Firefox and try to import a file, the click on the import button is not hijacked by the JavaScript, and the form is instead submitted normally, as a rather pointless GET request to `http://localhost:2368/ghost/debug/?importfile=GhostData.json`. If you don't inspect the URL, it looks like nothing happens.\r\n\r\nI have not been able to nail down the root cause here, but it seems to be related to some of the [magic going on with the click event in debug.js](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/blob/master/core/client/views/debug.js?source=cc#L25)."
2027,'','"Delete Post" dialog usability with button color\nThe current UI for deleting a post exhibits a bad usability, since the coloring and the labeling of the buttons is ambiguous:\r\n\r\n![Bad UX](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/582444/2001906/8726cf5e-85d7-11e3-9c79-237faae43786.png)\r\n\r\n- The user has to read the question in the dialog to be able to tell what they should click. Is it "Yes, cancel" (because green is good?) or "No, cancel"?\r\n- Red is usually associated with deleting something, but here it cancels the action\r\n\r\nPlease change this dialog to something like this:\r\n\r\n![Good UX](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/582444/2001910/c85a83c6-85d7-11e3-80d2-10666923fec3.png)\r\n\r\nSee also: [Should “Yes, delete it” be red, or green?](http://ux.stackexchange.com/questions/49991/should-yes-delete-it-be-red-or-green)'
2026,'',"bug caused by unidecode's bug\nissue #1986\r\nremove URL reserved chars after unidecode, because unidecode will produce\r\nsome URL reserved chars."
2025,'sebgie','Start up safely when the activeTheme is not present\nfixes #2000\r\n\r\n- resolves errors when attempting to start Ghost without the active theme present\r\n- the frontend will render a 500 error page safely\r\n- issues with themes that have an error template are resolved separately in #2018'
2024,'sebgie',"Use absolute path when storing images\ncloses #1983\r\n\r\nImages were uploaded to a relative location, based on the current directory. So if you start Ghost using `node ~/Ghost/index.js`, it would put all images at `~/content/images`.\r\n\r\nThis changes it to use a absolute directory, based on Ghost's root directory (see `server/config/paths.js`)."
2023,'','403 error\nPOST /ghost/api/v0.1/posts/ 403 27ms - 19b\r\ni got this  message\r\nand  i found there is no api directory\r\n\r\nby the way , i wanna know how to make the ghost work in production mode'
2022,'','Markdown: Text Highlighting\n[Roon](http://roon.io) has a cool Markdown feature called "highlight". To use it you would do:\r\n\r\n```markdown\r\nThis is some ==highlighted== text\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd then the *highlighted* part would then become highlighted. This is a good way of pointing out important parts rather than using bold or italic text.\r\n\r\nYou can see an example at [Sam Soffes blog](http://sam.roon.io/coins).\r\n\r\nJust food for thought.'
2021,'','Cannot find themes with more than three dots\nWith the latest version of ghost it is not possibile to use themes with more than three dots in the root folder name. The administration panel will find it but only with two dots. \r\nIf you select the theme the frontend will exit with an status code of 500.'
2020,'','Minor code cleanup of editor keyboard shortcut actions.\nI noticed that markdown-actions.js repeats itself an awful lot. Seeing as just about every `case` in the `replace` function calls `this.elem.getCursor()`, and frequently `this.elem.getLine(cursor.line)`, at least once, it seems like it should be moved up outside of the switch structure.'
2019,'','[Translations: /zh] Add some simplified chinese (zh) translations in _config.yml\nFully Translate quickstart/quickstart.md to simplified chinese (zh)\r\nTranslate a little part of themes/index.md to simplified chinese (zh)\r\nWill finish the translation if the current version gets selected.'
2018,'',"Catch errors when rendering the error template\nfixes #1991\r\n\r\n- if there's an error when rendering the error template, default to sending a plain response detailing both errors."
2017,'','Upgrade express-hbs, and switch to using registerPartial\nfixes #1964, fixes #1975\r\n\r\n - Issues with partial handling which caused #1964  have been part fixed by handlebars, part worked around by express-hbs, we must use `registerPartials` to ensure partials are handled correctly.\r\n - Issue with error handling which caused #1975 has also been fixed in express-hbs, which now catches the error from handlebars and passes it to express so that we can handle the error with an error page.'
2015,'',"Bug: published_at is not always set\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nIt is possible for blog posts to get into a state where their `status` is `published` but `published_at` is null\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nUnknown :-1: \r\n\r\nThis is a bug I've seen reported numerous times on [the forum](https://ghost.org/forum/using-ghost/3609-posts-on-content-gone-missing/2/) and is definitely still occurring in 0.4.\r\n\r\nIn 0.4 I added a fix to make sure that when this happens the content screen [doesn't break](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/issues/1730), but it still happens, and borks the order of posts on the admin and frontend. \r\n\r\nI have a feeling this is caused by the way we use the saving method in bookshelf, and probably requires https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/issues/1655 in order to be fixed, but think it would be good to investigate to see if we can at least find a way to reproduce it.\r\n\r\n### Technical details: \r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.3.3, 0.4\r\n* Potentially MySQL only?"
2014,'','Bug: Creating a code block after a list appends the code to last li element in markdown\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nI see that having a code block right after a list does not format well in markdown.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Create a new blog post\r\n2. Paste the below text in the editor\r\n\r\n* one\r\n* two\r\n\r\n\r\nend of list\r\n\r\n    code\r\n    \r\nend of code\r\n\r\n* another list\r\n* another here\r\n\r\n    code not coming fine\r\n    here\r\n\r\n\r\nObserve that the code block comes fine in the first case but in the next case it is clubbed into the last list element.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: 0.4\r\n* Client OS: Mac 10.9\r\n* Server OS: Ubuntu 12.04\r\n* Node Version: v0.10.20\r\n* Browser: Chrome  31.0.1650.63'
