1938,'','Including theme partials in a way that supports symbolically linked directories\nThe old way was breaking because config.paths().availableThemes[activeTheme] would just be a string.\r\n\r\nBy doing a fs.stat() on the full path (that was already being constructed a line later), all theme directories are supported.\r\n\r\nThis fixes issue #1937 that I just posted, which includes a reproducible case.'
1937,'','Bug: Themes that are symlinked cannot use custom ./partials directories\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nIf a theme is a symbolical link (symlink) then its ./partials directory will not be properly registered.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Copy the casper theme: `cp -rp ./casper ./casper-copy`\r\n2. Make a symlink to the new casper-copy theme: `ln -s ./casper-copy ./casper-ln`\r\n3. Add a partials directory: `mkdir ./casper-copy/partials`\r\n4. Add a partial: `echo "Hello" > ./casper-copy/partials/hello.hbs`\r\n5. Reference the partial in default.hbs right before the closing body tag: `{{> hello}}`\r\n6. Boot\r\n7. Set the theme to casper-copy, save, reboot the server, load a page, verify success\r\n8. Set the theme to casper-ln, save, reboot the server, load a page, verify error: `Error: The partial hello could not be found`\r\n\r\nThis is a bug because symlinked theme directories are really common. You may check out a theme from github and link to it from your Ghost installation.\r\n\r\nIt\'s a minor annoyance but common bug\r\n  https://ghost.org/forum/themes/625-ghost-is-no-longer-detecting-my-partials/\r\n  https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/issues/1747\r\n\r\nAnd it\'s hard to track down and debug without knowing about the problem.\r\n\r\n### Cause\r\n\r\nThe way in which the active theme directory is being checked for a partials directory isn\'t portable and fails on symlinked themes. I have a fix coming as a pull request.\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\n* Ghost Version: master - latest commit:  c82d2eadba0176ce96ec91d57bfa8582cae50f95\r\n* Client OS: Mac OS X Mavericks\r\n* Server OS: Mac OS X Mavericks\r\n* Node Version: 0.10.21\r\n* Browser: N/A'
