1884,'','Separate Posts and Pages menu\nSince static pages have been introduce, both pages and posts appear under the Content menu from the admin interface.\r\n\r\nIt would be awesome if pages and posts were either in separate menus or sortable under the Content menu. \r\n\r\nCurrently you have to dig through the posts to find a previously created static page.\r\n\r\nTested in 0.4.0-pre'
1883,'',"Restored files that were refactored away.\nResolves #1873.\r\n\r\nDuring unzip based deployments of new releases, old files are not removed and node's require loads the old file instead of all the new ones in the new directory. The newly restored files in this commit act as a delegate for all other dependent scripts. They simply load all the new files from the new directory by using the trailing slash to disambiguate."
