1771,'',"Images are storing subdirectories in their paths\nIf using Ghost in a subdirectory, uploaded images are getting the subdirectory being returned as part of their path.\r\n\r\nExpected behaviour:\r\n\r\nGhost should consider paths of images and other resources as starting after the subdirectory, not including the subdirectory in the path. The subdirectory should be added/removed/handled separately.\r\n\r\nTo reproduce:\r\n\r\n- change your url in config.js to contain a subdirectory\r\n- start ghost, visit the editor and upload an image\r\n- note that the path for the image now starts with your subdirectory, instead of starting at `/content/images` which is the image 'mount' path.\r\n\r\nThis is on the latest master 25f3df2"
