1668,'','relative paths in css issue when relative from domain root\n`/core/client/assets/sass/layouts/users.scss` has a reference to a static image relative to root of the domain.\r\n\r\n`background-image: url(/shared/img/user-image.png);`\r\n\r\nHowever if the site is running in a subfolder (config.paths().webroot) then this reference will be wrong as `/shared/` will become `/subFolder/shared/`.\r\n\r\nGiven that relative paths given in CSS are relative to the .css file (not the page). Then the css can define relative paths.\r\n\r\nTherefore `background-image: url(../../shared/img/user-image.png);` will resolve correctly as the compiled version of the sass file is `/ghost/css/screen.css`\r\n\r\nAll images in .sass file will need to be checked and updated.\r\n'
