1620,'',"Added support for embeddable tweets\nAdded support for embeddable tweets\r\n\r\nYou can easily embed any tweet to your posts by simply copy pasting their full url in markdown\r\nE.g. \r\nhttps://twitter.com/xdamman/status/408455694241636352\r\n\r\nThe only issue is that because of the live update of the preview pane, the embeddable tweet needs to be re-rendered every time. This creates a flickering which is not ideal. I mitigated it by setting a min height to the container of the tweet. Not sure how we can avoid that. I'm not familiar enough with your code base yet. Please have a look.\r\n\r\nI'm happy to add support for other types of embeds (youtube, instagram, facebook, ...) if there is interest. \r\n\r\n![screenshot](https://photos-3.dropbox.com/t/0/AAAKYCE5MfAzvxt1AwNL137DlCRKDoZUdQBMKGrT6Zl8zw/12/1702667/png/1024x768/3/1386241200/0/2/Screenshot%202013-12-05%2001.15.23.png/s071uGo_mproSc0NcomVtHvY7NvgbUJ5tNwRxnGJYQ0)"
1619,'','Some non-breaking changes to help create rails engine\nI am currently trying to create a rails engine to use the ghost client without the server (soon to be open sourced) and there are just two minor incompatibilities I would like to fix.\r\n\r\n1. Trailing slashes on the backbone router breaks links\r\n2. Extract the bourbon import into a seperate file, to allow using the bourbon gem.\r\n\r\nThese are just minor, but if they cannot be fixed then it is cool, I will just need to maintain a separate fork.\r\n\r\nCheers\r\nGraham'
1618,'',"Don't advise the specifics of login failure\nAvoid providing additional information to potential hackers, i.e. they now know the username exists and can target the password."
1617,'','Automatic email linking breaks custom mailto links\nAs reported [in the forums](https://ghost.org/forum/using-ghost/2847-not-sure-if-this-is-a-bug/), when you enter a mailto link in the editor:\r\n\r\n```\r\n<a href="mailto:me@example.com?subject=stuff">me@example.com</a>\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is the resulting HTML:\r\n\r\n```\r\n<a href="mailto:<a ref=\'mailto:me@example.com\'>me@example.com</a>?subject=stuff"></a>\r\n<a href="mailto:me@example.com">me@example.com</a>\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis seems to be caused by our automatic linking of email addresses. The same applies to links without a `subject` parameter, but it\'s a good example why we should support this.\r\n\r\n**Update** this also happens for images as per #2131'
1616,'','"Unable to find setting" error on image upload within admin\nUploading a logo or cover image within Admin > Settings > General results in error.\r\n\r\n### Issue Summary\r\n\r\nUpon image upload, an error message is displayed containing the following contents:\r\n\r\n```\r\nUnable to find setting: [object Object],[object Object],[object Object],[object Object],[object Object],[object Object],[object Object],[object Object],[object Object],[object Object]\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn the browser console, the following occurs:\r\n\r\n> Failed to load resource: the server responded with a status of 404 (Not Found) http://ghost/ghost/api/v0.1/settings/?type=blog,theme\r\n\r\nScreenshot:\r\n![screen shot 2013-12-04 at 2 29 32 am](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/45622/1671613/1663b6d8-5cbf-11e3-9fe9-2634d594e6e5.png)\r\n\r\nThe image does actually upload, however, until the node server is restarted it does not display within Ghost.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nUpload an image; does not appear to be related to image type or file size.\r\n\r\n### Technical details:\r\n\r\nGhost Version: master (latest commit: d2d9db30676bd0abd02e8b932fb73d247b39f03c)\r\nClient OS: Mac OS X 10.9\r\nServer OS: Ubuntu 12.04.3 LTS\r\nNode Version: 0.10.21\r\nBrowser: Chrome 33.0.1726.0 dev'
1615,'','Switch from multipart to busboy\nFixes #1227\r\n\r\n- Removed deprecated `multipart` references.\r\n- Setup `busboy` to pass along file streams and do a naive parse of form\r\nvalues.\r\n- Updated logic in file storage and db import to handle file streams\r\ninstead of the temporary files created by `multipart`.'
