1610,'',"Mint analytics URL not handled under Ghost\nNoticed an issue with accessing Mint analytics under Ghost 0.3.3 - you can't access the main directory www.example.com/mint under the stock rewrite rules. I've tried to set a custom rewrite rule under `server.js` to have /mint/ redirect to /mint/index.php, but no luck. The rewrite rule I used was:\r\n\r\n    server.get(/^\\/((mint)\\/?)/, function (req, res) {\r\n        res.redirect('/mint/');\r\n    });\r\n\r\nSafari just throws a redirect loop error, which is probably to be expected given the way the rule is written. I tried `res.redirect('/mint/index.php');`, but it still loops.\r\n\r\nI decided to try and tweak this in nginx, also with no luck. I tried to have nginx treat the /mint/ directory as it's very own website with the following rewrite rule:\r\n\r\n    server {\r\n        listen 82; #IPv4\r\n        server_name www.classicyuppie.com classicyuppie.com;\r\n        root    /var/www/ghost/mint/;\r\n        index.php index.html index.htm;\r\n\r\n        location / {\r\n                try_files $uri $uri/ =404;\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n\r\nStill no luck. Ghost's rewrite rules take over and I get a 404 returned. Perhaps there's a way to exclude certain urls from being excluded from Ghost's rewrite rules. I'm not that savvy when it comes to scripting for .js, so if anyone has a better idea how to go about this, please, let me know."
1609,'',"CasperJS random failures\nCasperJS seems to produce random failures on Travis again. While submitting and testing #1608 I received multiple build failures that eventually go away when running the test suite repeatedly. Similar issues appeared on #1606.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure what causes these new issues. @bastilian and I tried upgrading CasperJS to the latest beta3 which seems to partially help reducing the amount of PAGE FAILURES. I'd like to raise since I'm not sure that CasperJS is the only reason the build is failing."
1608,'','Upgrade downsize to 0.0.4\nrefs #1095\r\n- added new unicode test to excerpt helper\r\n\r\nThis addresses issues (e.g. #1095) with unicode languages and the excerpt/content helper failing to limit the content by words. Downsize 0.0.4 now uses XRegExp (https://github.com/cgiffard/Downsize/pull/3) in order to support matching unicode strings. This allows downsize to work on languages like greek or russian properly.\r\n\r\nSome more thought will have to be put into supporting CJK since the notion of a "word" is different there.'
