1600,'',"backspace in preview.. oops lost work\nso, along with #1598 , this also caused me to lose work.\r\n\r\nIt's not entirely a bug, but, more of a feature request, and users should never lose work!\r\n\r\nWell I generally stare at the preview mode while blogging.  One time, I had written a lot, and then automatically clicked the preview and hit backspace, my brain fooled into thinking that was my editor.  My browser went back and I lost work.\r\n\r\nFor one thing, it would be nice if the page loaded with the article data in place, so if you did go back and forward, default browser functionality would potentially keep your work.  This would probably fix #1598 too, as long as you used the same window.\r\n\r\nSince it seems the article is populated after page load, then you really need to stop users from being able to willy nilly go back, especially since they could have written a lot."
