1598,'','pragma no-cache\nI noticed when editing a post, I would save it, then look at it, then go back and edit it, but it would not be a refreshed version, so I might lose changes I made if I editted it and saved it again.\r\n\r\nAll admin pages should be pragma no-cache so it re-gets all the data.'
1597,'',"db migrate versioning\nI just looked at the db migrations.. Does it check 1 date and make sure it's on the newest one?\r\n\r\nIf so, what if 2 people both add migrations\r\n\r\ndb version 10\r\nperson 1 adds migration 15\r\nperson 2 adds migration 13\r\n\r\nThey both commit and merge\r\n\r\nperson 1 won't get person 2's changes since his version will already be at 15.\r\n\r\nI think rails had this problem, that's why now they have a record for each migration, and it checks whether or not a record exists for each file.\r\n\r\nin this case, \r\nwe'd have\r\n10\r\n13\r\n15\r\nin the `migrations` database table.\r\nso when person 1 updates, his db see's he doesn't have 13 and everyone gets synced."
1596,'',"Use random text for post headings' id attribution?\nI've just noticed that Ghost will generate a id attribution for each post heading with its content. But if people write headings in Chinese (or probably Japanese, Korean) Ghost will generate an empty id that means the anchors are no longer working. Ghost will also generate exactly same id for each heading if they have same English characters but the rest are different.\r\n\r\nSo, how about generate post headings' id with a random text? I'm currently building a theme which can generate a TOC for post. It will be handy if you could add support for this.\r\n\r\nCheers"
1595,'','Weird behavior when pressing delete in the preview\nPressing delete while some text is marked deletes both the title and the preview content. It seems to only occur after saving a draft for the first time.\r\n\r\nI was not able to reproduce it in Firefox and Epiphany/Webkit, only Chrome seems to be affected.\r\n\r\nTo reproduce ([taken from here](https://ghost.org/forum/bugs-suggestions/2957-saved-drafts-disappearing/6/)): \r\n\r\n> 1. create a new post and "save draft."\r\n> 2. Click in right pane (imagine you thought you were going to edit there so grab some text) and hit delete.\r\n> 3. everything in right pane disappears. Title is gone. markdown remains in left pane.\r\n > 4. refresh browser. Now all markdown is gone. If you exit and log back in your post will be empty.\r\n\r\n@halfdan also made a gif:\r\n\r\n![](http://i.imgur.com/OeA784e.gif)\r\n'
