1569,'',"Restore support for using ghost as a npm module fixes #1326\nThis resolves the issues we faced when I first implemented supporting ghost as a module.\r\n\r\nThis pushes all packages to delegate to `./core/server/config` when they need to access the config.js environment object.\r\n\r\nThe only weird thing exists in `./core/server/config/index.js` where I have an || statement that uses a require statement to fetch the config.js file.  This was required because it seems that grunt runs each task in their own process.  So when `grunt loadConfig` is executed, it creates the `config.js` if it needs to.  However when the mocha tests are then run the cached config object no longer exists.  Hence the need for the odd require statement.  I added a comment there to explain why it's there as well.\r\n\r\nAside from that everything else in this should be straightforward. \r\n\r\nLooking forward to feedback :)."
1568,'',"SQLITE_CANTOPEN: unable to open database file\nI'm getting this error but I have no permission problem.\r\n\r\nIt was working fine before, this started happening after I get the latest version:\r\n\r\n```\r\n> ghost@0.3.3 start /home/ubuntu/blog\r\n> node index\r\n\r\nERROR: There is a problem with the database\r\nSQLITE_CANTOPEN: unable to open database file, sql: select * from sqlite_master where type = 'table' and name = ?, bindings: settings\r\n```\r\n\r\nHere are my findings\r\n\r\n- I've tried to upgrade installed sqlite3 bindings to `sqlite3@2.1.19` didn't change a thing.\r\n- Since it doesn't event create a database in content/data folder, I've tried to copy a database already created on mac os x. Same error happened.\r\n- I made sure all permissions are correct and files/folder owned by correct users, I even tried setting `777` to all, no luck\r\n- I'm using an EC2 instance, ubuntu machine\r\n- I have `node@0.10.7`\r\n- It does not happen on mac os x and works fine there"
