1564,'',"Bumping to knex 0.5 and bookshelf 0.6\nSo this looks like it's broken because it logs some new errors in the import tests about the slug not being unique - @sebgie I'm not sure if this is related at all to what you were doing with the transactions...\r\n\r\nIf anyone seems to know what might be causing these issues, I'll see if I can help debug... I was having a little trouble following the test code at first glance.\r\n\r\nI figured it'd be good to move up to the latest soon to see if any of the latest tweaks for PostgreSQL have helped, and make it easier to upgrade for new fixes there, re: #1555.\r\n\r\nThere's also a really, really bare bones [migration api](http://knexjs.org/#Migrate) if anyone is interested."
1563,'jgable','Enhancement: Invalidate cache header only for published posts\nWith the current implementation `X-Cache-Invalidate` headers are sent with every `POST`, `PUT`, `DELETE` response from `/ghost/api/posts`. Only posts with status = published should invalidate the cache.\r\n\r\nTricky part is that a change from published to draft and from draft to published needs to be detected to implement a working solution.\r\n\r\n'
1562,'','[WIP] added has_any_tag and has_all_tags core filters to Theme API\nContinuation of #1539 pull request (has_tag (single tag) )\r\n\r\n* Added has_all_tags (AND) helper to core Helpers.\r\n* Added has_any_tag (OR) helper to core Helpers.\r\n* Added unit tests to check works as expected.\r\n\r\nThis patch adds functionality to support the following use cases:\r\n\r\n* has_all_tags:\r\n\r\n ```html\r\n        <section class="post-excerpt">\r\n          {{#has_all_tags "summer of code" "snippet"}}\r\n                <p class="code-snippet">{{content}}</p>\r\n          {{ else }}\r\n            <p>{{excerpt}}&hellip;</p>\r\n          {{/has_all_tags}}\r\n        </section>\r\n```\r\n\r\n* has_any_tag\r\n\r\n ```html\r\n        <section class="post-excerpt">\r\n          {{#has_any_tag "snippet" "code" "programming" }}\r\n                <p class="code-snippet">{{content}}</p>\r\n          {{ else }}\r\n            <p>{{excerpt}}&hellip;</p>\r\n          {{/has_any_tag}}\r\n        </section>\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis could be pretty useful to filter post types using tags.\r\n'
1561,'',"Update the default fixture to make it clearer\nAfter having a few users mis-read / mis-understand the default fixture, I think it might need some tweaking. \r\n\r\nThe following line is what confuses most people, as they are reading from the blog and not the editor. They find themselves looking for a 'left hand panel' - which doesn't exist.\r\n> In the left hand panel of Ghost, you simply write as you normally would.\r\n\r\nHere are my suggestions (feel free to add your own to this list);\r\n\r\n* Alter the perspective of the post to the user reading from the blog, not the content page.\r\n* Instruct users on how to access the admin dashboard `/ghost/` (if the perspective isn't changed).\r\n    * From here explain how to get to the 'new post' page or how to edit the post.\r\n\r\nThese are only suggestions, I think it would be beneficial to discuss some alterations to get a wider view."
1560,'matthojo','[Docs] Adding basic documentation for configuring nginx\nThis adds information for a basic nginx setup as a proxy with Ghost running in the background.\r\n\r\nThis closes #1324 (partially)\r\n\r\nFor adding a how to on setting up Apache and maybe other web servers it should be considered to "restructure" the documents, since it is very long already, i think.\r\n\r\nI also cleaned up the above sections a bit and added information to avoid minor pitfalls.'
