1524,'','Set RSS link title to blog title\nAs reported [here](https://ghost.org/forum/bugs-suggestions/2987-rss-fetched-title-in-feedly/), the title of the link element that links to the RSS feed is just `RSS`. Some programs like Feedly are actually using it; this commit sets it to the correct value, which is the blog title. Also updated the unit test.'
1523,'','Install in sub-directory support.\nThis changes Ghost core to allow hosting Ghost in a sub-directory. \r\n\r\nAdditional work is needed:\r\n\r\n  * Create new theme helper(s) to generate URLs for stylesheets/scripts (e.g. for https://github.com/TryGhost/Casper/blob/master/default.hbs#L17)\r\n  * Change client-side JavaScript to properly send requests to `/<subdir>/api/*` and generate the admin menu with subdir.\r\n  * Adjust tests to work with subdirectories (some work already done here)\r\n\r\nThe theme helpers require #1390.\r\n\r\nrefs #527'
