1490,'','Bug in @first in foreach posts loop on only paginated index pages\n**Bug:**\r\n\r\n* I modified the default Casper theme\'s index.hbs template so that the first post listed on index page have a longer excerpt character size than the remaining listed posts. This worked fine it seem when all posts 6-10 of them were listed all on one single index page (page 1).\r\n* But I just noticed now that the index has paginated to 2 pages, the 1st index page no longer has that custom @first longer excerpt size but page 2\'s first post does!\r\n\r\nYou can see the problem on my Ghost blog\r\n\r\n* page 1 index http://ghost.centminmod.com\r\n* page 2 index http://ghost.centminmod.com/page/2/\r\n\r\nNotice how page 2\'s first post is only post out of both indexes page 1 and page 2 to have the longer excerpt.\r\n\r\n**System setup:**\r\n\r\n* DigitalOcean 512MB VPS \r\n* CentOS 6.4 64bit based\r\n* Centmin Mod Nginx stack - full Ghost blog install outline is at http://ghost.centminmod.com/ghost-node-js-install-on-centmin-mod-nginx-stack/\r\n* Nginx 1.5.6 with proxy_cache setup currently at 120 minute cache TTL\r\n* Node.js 0.10.21\r\n* NPN 1.3.11\r\n* PM2 0.6.3 my init.d startup script http://ghost.centminmod.com/ghost-blog-node-js-init-startup-script/\r\n* Using sqlite3 db\r\n\r\nThe relevant index.hbs custom foreach post loop is posted here https://gist.github.com/centminmod/7486490\r\n\r\n```\r\n<main class="content" role="main">\r\n    {{! Each post will be output using this markup }}\r\n    {{#foreach posts}}\r\n        {{#if @first}}\r\n    <article class="{{post_class}}" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/BlogPosting">\r\n        <header class="post-header">\r\n            <span class="post-meta"><time datetime="{{date format=\'YYYY-MM-DD\'}}" itemprop="datePublished">{{date format="DD MMM YY"}}</time> {{#if tags}}| {{tags}}{{/if}} | <a href="{{url absolute="true"}}#disqus_thread" data-disqus-identifier="{{id}}">Comments</a></span>\r\n            <h2 class="post-title"><a href="{{url}}" itemprop="url"><span itemprop="name headline">{{{title}}}</span></a></h2>\r\n        </header>\r\n        <section class="post-excerpt" itemprop="articleBody">\r\n            <p>{{excerpt characters="28"}}&hellip;<span class="read-more"> <a href="{{url}}">Read More</a></p>\r\n        </section>\r\n    </article>\r\n \r\n        {{else}}\r\n \r\n    <article class="{{post_class}}" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/BlogPosting">\r\n        <header class="post-header">\r\n            <span class="post-meta"><time datetime="{{date format=\'YYYY-MM-DD\'}}" itemprop="datePublished">{{date format="DD MMM YY"}}</time> {{#if tags}}| {{tags}}{{/if}} | <a href="{{url absolute="true"}}#disqus_thread" data-disqus-identifier="{{id}}">Comments</a></span>\r\n            <h2 class="post-title"><a href="{{url}}" itemprop="url"><span itemprop="name headline">{{{title}}}</span></a></h2>\r\n        </header>\r\n        <section class="post-excerpt" itemprop="articleBody">\r\n            <p>{{excerpt characters="18"}}&hellip;<span class="read-more"> <a href="{{url}}">Read More</a></p>\r\n        </section>\r\n    </article>\r\n        {{/if}}\r\n    {{/foreach}}\r\n    {{!! After all the posts, we have the previous/next pagination links }}\r\n    {{pagination}}\r\n</main>\r\n```\r\n'
