1475,'','Tag submission shortcut causing problems on non-english languages\nI have received a report that on some languages e.g. cyrillic. The tag \'submission\' short cut of `,` is causing problems. This is due to certain characters being placed on the `,` key.\r\n\r\nFor example the word "Общее" has the letter `б` which is placed on the same key as `,`.\r\n\r\nPerhaps we should remove the comma shortcut or make it more accurate to `,`, rather than a keycode.'
1473,'',"API / data restrictions for apps / internal on settings model\nGhost's data API is accessible internally via api(), over HTTP, and will also be made available to apps.\r\n\r\nThe API provides CRUD functionality for all of our data models.\r\n\r\nHowever, there are some restrictions which should be in place. Essentially, it should never be possible for an app to add a setting, delete a setting or to modify a setting marked `core`. \r\n\r\nApps should get their own app_settings table which they can modify to their heart's content, but the settings table shouldn't really be interfered with.\r\n\r\nI think the most sensible way to do this, is to only permit these operations if using the api internally, so the features are not available if you are using HTTP or you are an app. "
1472,'','Account redirects\nIn addition to #1312 and instead of #1439\r\n\r\nThe `signup`, `signin` and `signout` pages should all live at `/ghost/sign**/`\r\n\r\nThe non-ghost urls should all redirect to the ghost urls\r\n\r\n* `/signup/`  -> `/ghost/signup/` \r\n* `/signin/`   -> `/ghost/signin/` \r\n* `/signout/` -> `/ghost/signout/` \r\n\r\n'
1471,'jgable','Improved password reset tool\nWe need to improve the robustness of the password reset tool.\r\n\r\n* When someone hits the password reset button, ghost should generate a URL with a token which will take the user to a password reset form. That URL should then be emailed to the user.\r\n* If the email fails in anyway, we should show a useful message pointing the user to the mail configuration documentation.\r\n* The token should only be valid for 24 hours\r\n* The password reset form should allow a user to choose their own new password. It should be entered twice.\r\n* The password should be reset to the new password on successful completion of this form.\r\n* The reset password form should look much the same as the current forgotten password form, \r\n* The reset password form should live at /ghost/reset/\r\n* /ghost/reset/ should redirect to /ghost/forgotten/ if someone tries to access it without a valid token, if the token has expired this should be clearly messaged.'
1470,'ErisDS','Cache Control Headers\nRequires #1405 \r\n\r\nOnce we have asset management in place we can fully set cache control headers for Ghost.\r\n\r\nWe need to set proper cache headers for\r\n\r\n* /ghost/ admin routes \r\n* /ghost/api routes \r\n* frontend routes\r\n* managed assets\r\n* unmanaged assets (i.e. from themes not using the helper)\r\n* error pages\r\n* redirects\r\n\r\nI had a first stab at doing this here: 3f4a9e00ac\r\n\r\nMy idea was to create profiles which could be applied:\r\n\r\n* **Private** `no-cache, private, no-store, must-revalidate, max-stale=0, post-check=0, pre-check=0` - used for admin & api routes + error pages\r\n*  **Public** `public, max-age=0, must-revalidate` - used for frontend routes, unmanaged assets and probably for redirects\r\n* **Asset** `public, max-age=one-year, must-revalidate` - used for all managed assets\r\n\r\nWe can start to add a lot of this to non-assets without the asset management. '
1469,'','Ghost installation locking out user\nI\'m opening this issue due to several forum topics stating that installations are \'locking\' out their users, due to the users emails "no longer existing".\r\n\r\nThis seems to only be mainly on the Digital Ocean service at the moment, however I\'m raising the issue on here first _just incase_ it is a genuine Ghost bug.\r\n\r\n**Scenario**\r\n\r\n* Create blog\r\n* Signup\r\n* Play with Ghost\r\n* Go to login with Ghost again once logged out\r\n* "No user with this email exists"\r\n* Go to signup\r\n* "You can only have one user"\r\n\r\n**Solution found**\r\n* Fresh installation (I cannot fathom this explanation unless it\'s related to a database change)\r\n\r\n**Forum topics possibly related**\r\n* https://ghost.org/forum/using-ghost/2209-can-t-log-back-into-blog\r\n* https://ghost.org/forum/installation/2713-can-t-log-in-to-my-ghost-blog/\r\n* https://ghost.org/forum/installation/2397-error-there-is-no-user-with-that-email-address-and-a-user-is-already-registered-only-one-user-for-now/\r\n\r\n**Possible causes (a.k.a guesses)**\r\n* Custom themes interfering somehow?\r\n* Host configuration \r\n\r\nI\'ll update this with any more information as it comes in.'
