1460,'','Added server.js file to root so that Azure will build properly on deploy\nWhen deploying Ghost to Azure the build fails because Azure expects there to be a server.js (or app.js) file in the Express app root. This small change allows Azure to build the site properly on first deploy.\r\n\r\nIn addition (sorry I meant to put this into another PR) I added a route for historical Wordpress-style URLs. This simply allows for their presence and routes to the slugged post - this is nice for backwards compatibility of imported blogs (like mine).'
1459,'','Pry apart the site into separate modules, lean more on NPM\nHi guys! I just pushed my blog to Ghost:\r\n\r\nhttp://www.wekeroad.com\r\n\r\nAnd I love what you\'ve done. One thing that I think would make life easier for the core team and others like me who want to contribute would be to get a bit more idiomatic with Ghost\'s internals. Specifically - following the mantra "do one thing well".\r\n\r\nTo that end, I would love to contribute to this and open a PR for tracking, but I wanted to check with the team first. My specific ideas are separating the modules along these lines:\r\n\r\n - ghost-core (all the main logic and data maneuvering)\r\n - ghost-admin (the admin views, routes, client code etc - note that this isn\'t a full express site, just the hooks)\r\n - ghost-rest (the JSON api)\r\n - ghost-caspar (the Caspar theme)\r\n - ghost-express (the web site which pulls in all of these modules)\r\n\r\nOne nice benefit of doing this is that it makes theming a lot more extensible and puts the installation and management of themes into NPM which can manage *everything* for you instead of leaning on git submodules (which can be rather opaque).\r\n\r\nAnother nice thing is that it unbolts HBS from ... well everything. If a theme wants to use HBS then... hurrah. Otherwise it could use Jade or EJS etc.\r\n\r\nIf I don\'t want a REST api, I don\'t need to add the package and hook it up in the app.\r\n\r\nIf you\'re up for exploring this - I\'m happy to contribute my time. I\'d also like to rev the admin site to using something a bit more current like Ember or Angular. This would help scale that lovely thing - but I\'ll pop this into another PR if you\'re game.\r\n\r\nMany thanks again for all your work.\r\n\r\n\r\n'
