1382,'','Page Type Rather Than Boolean\nAlthough the Ghost core needs to be as simplistic as possible, I do think future proofing is required regarding post types.\r\n\r\nI am planning to write a plugin for custom post types so I looked in to how pages are currently defined. It is simply a field called page that is true or false. This is fine but I think it would be much better to have type and page as a string, before static pages are released and turning back will be much harder.'
1381,'',"'.../built/scripts/vendor.js/?v=x' not found\nI built Ghost using the source code and followed the instructions from `CONTRIBUTING.md`.\r\n\r\nBut when I try accessing `localhost:2368/ghost/signup`, I get this:\r\n![screenshot 2013-11-01 17 42 18](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/760500/1458180/c89b3b22-4357-11e3-8535-17849e6605bb.png)\r\n\r\nThe console logs that the server returns a 404 for `http://localhost:2368/built/scripts/vendor.js/?v=0.3.3`."
1380,'','Difficulty scrolling past iframes in admin (iOS)\nI added an Instagram image and a YouTube video to a post using their embed code. I did this on a desktop and the post publishes and displays ok.\r\n\r\nWhen previewing a post in the admin on iOS though trying to scroll past an iframe can cause the entire canvas to be dragged upwards, rather than the page scrolling down.\r\n\r\nThis was in Safari for iOS 7 on an iPad Mini.\r\n\r\n![ghost-admin](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/540527/1454930/6031d622-4311-11e3-8e0a-f51de681812e.jpg)'
1379,'','Upgrade validator to 2.*.*\nFirst we need to do #1378 and implement whatever the intended solution is.\r\n\r\nThen we need to upgrade validator from 1.4.0 to the latest version.'
1378,'sebgie',"Investigate XSS filtering \nAt the moment Ghost uses node-validator's xss filter.\r\n\r\nHowever this has at least one known issue (#1328) in Ghost and has been removed from node-validator 2.0.0.\r\n\r\nWe need to investigate a better way to add a layer of XSS filtering to fields like titles.  Additionally, we should consider the need to add some level of (potentially configurable) filtering to the markdown -> html conversion we use for post content.\r\n\r\nMain questions to answer here is:\r\nIs [Google Caja](https://code.google.com/p/google-caja/) sanitizer the best solution?  Is it flexible / configurable / extensible?\r\nIf not what else is there?  \r\nIf it is, which npm wrapper is best (i think [this one](https://npmjs.org/package/sanitizer))?\r\n"
1377,'',"Upgrade fs-extra & resolve issues\nGhost depends on fs-extra 0.6.3, latest version of fs-extra is 0.8.1\r\n\r\nCurrently, switching versions causes uploads to fail, so there is obviously a breaking change (not surprising it's a pretty big jump).\r\n\r\nAt some point in 0.4 we need to investigate what the breaking change is, resolve it, and upgrade the dependency."
1376,'',"[Suggestion] Define uploaded image filename (Or an automatic name like permalink)\nToday, if we upload an image to Ghost the image is saved with the name of the file. Sometimes this is very bad for SEO.\r\n\r\n\r\nMaybe we could define image names, or generate a name by the articles permalink.\r\n\r\nThis would be a improvement in Ghost's SEO."
