1365,'','jslint unused parameters \nI think unused parameter detection in jslint is worth keeping.  It helps keep function definitions minimal and clean.\r\n\r\nI assume unused parameter detection is disabled because of this case:\r\n```javascript\r\nfunction (v, k) {\r\n    return k + " is the key";\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut that can be remedied by adding a jslint override line:\r\n```javascript\r\nfunction (v, k) {\r\n    /*jslint unparam:true*/\r\n    return k + " is the key";\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat override directive only applies in the scope of the function, so it\'s a nice way to deal with that case while still getting the benefits of unused paramater detection.\r\n\r\nWould you accept a PR that removes unparam:true from Gruntfile.js and adds the override where necessary?'
