1303,'','Set a sensible default sort order for post management admin\nCurrently the manage posts screen lists posts in order of "most recently updated" - this is a very useful sort order to have, but it\'s a very confusing default. Particularly after running a large content import, which effectively leaves you with a list of hundreds of posts in order of oldest=>newest.\r\n\r\n## Task: Set a new default sort order.\r\n\r\nAll unpublished posts (drafts) should be listed at the top. These should be sorted in order of \'updated_at\' time (most recently updated draft at the top, oldest draft at the bottom)\r\n\r\nAfter unpublished posts, all published posts should be listed. These should be sorted by newest (top) => oldest (bottom), by published_at time.'
