1292,'','Invalid pagination value on Heroku\nI recently installed Ghost on Heroku to give it a shot. On a brand new installation using `NODE_ENV=production` and Heroku\'s PostgreSQL offering, I found that the `paginationHelper` function in `/core/server/helpers/index.js` was throwing the following error:\r\n\r\n    Invalid value, check page, pages, limit and total are numbers\r\n\r\nAfter doing a bit of debugging, I found that the value of `this.pagination.total` was actually the *string* `"1"` instead of a number. The function is throwing an error because it\'s checking to see that this value is a number.'
1291,'','forever crashes ghost\nHey,\r\nwhen running this command ```forever /var/www/domain.com/blog/index.js``` It always restarts ghost even when I run it from inside the correct folder.\r\n\r\nThis is what it puts onto the console\r\n```\r\nERROR: Could not locate a configuration file.\r\n/\r\nPlease check your deployment for config.js or config.example.js.\r\n\r\nError: Could not locate a configuration file.\r\n    at checkTemplate (/var/www/mathixx.de/blog/core/config-loader.js:16:36)\r\n    at Object.cb [as oncomplete] (fs.js:168:19) \r\n\r\nForever detected script exited with code: 0\r\nForever restarting script for 9 time\r\n```'
