1181,'','jQuery CDN+fallback in ghost_foot\nI\'m trying to adapt <a href="http://github.com/h5bp/html5-boilerplate/">html5-boilerplate</a> as a bare-bones theme for Ghost.\r\nh5bp loads jQuery from a CDN with a local fallback as following:\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<script src="//ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.10.2/jquery.min.js"></script>\r\n<script>window.jQuery || document.write(\'<script src="js/vendor/jquery-1.10.2.min.js"><\\/script>\')</script>\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs far as I can tell, it\'s impossible to do this with the current implementation of `ghost_foot`. I understand that `ghost_foot` needs to remain in the theme as a future hook, but a proper port of h5bp would require implementing all of the best-practices that come along with it. I\'m not sure if that would mean creating a flag within the Ghost theme engine that could disable the default jQuery implementation while retaining the hook, or if the CDN+fallback solution is something that could be implemented into Ghost natively.\r\n\r\nThoughts?'
1180,'jgillich','Convert Docs from HTML to Markdown\nOur docs on the /gh-pages/ branch are using Jekyll, which supports both HTML and Markdown inputs. Currently we use HTML. It would be awesome + make a lot of sense + make translations much easier.... if we used Markdown.\r\n\r\nThis task is to convert our current /gh-pages/ implementation to be markdown based rather than HTML based - keeping all the same styles and functionality.\r\n\r\nThis is an open issue to anyone who wants to pick up / submit a PR.'
