1173,'','Remove special characters from CSS files\nThe errors.css file contains the following line, a utf-8 encoded character:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/blob/master/core/client/assets/sass/layouts/errors.scss#L98\r\n\r\n(content: "↪︎";)\r\n\r\nThis gives me a grunt compile error:\r\n```\r\nRunning "sass:compress" (sass) task\r\nSyntax error: Invalid US-ASCII character "\\xE2"\r\n        on line 98 of ./core/client/assets/sass/layouts/errors.scss\r\n        from line 43 of ./core/client/assets/sass/screen.scss\r\n```\r\n\r\nBased on the SASS [documentation here](http://sass-lang.com/documentation/file.SASS_REFERENCE.html), the implied character encoding of the file is based on the OS settings (which for many/most people is utf-8). However apparently that is not the case for my OS.\r\n\r\nI\'m running Ubuntu 10.04.4 LTS with Ruby 2.0.0p247\r\n\r\nThe fix would be an "@charset "utf-8";" declaration at the very top of the file.'
