1171,'','Display H1-H6 in a sidebar map mode / outline mode\nAs a power user it would be useful to see a "mini map" view of my document that is built dynamically while I\'m editing. It could be created directly off the H1-H6 tags I\'m using to organize my document. When clicked on any of the headers would jump me to that part of the document.\r\n\r\nThis is similar in approach to the map mode f or Sublime Text, but would actually be useful for navigating.'
1170,'',"While in edit mode, overwrite existing images by dragging new image in it's place\nAs a power user I'd like the default behavior of editing to be as follows:\r\n\r\n* Create an image placeholder in my article by pressing Shift + Ctrl + L.\r\n* Drag image onto the placeholder in the preview panel\r\n* Image is uploaded and displays properly\r\n* I can put a new image in it's place by simply dragging another image on top of the existing page.\r\n\r\n*Current behaviour*\r\n* When a new image is dragged on top of an existing image, the entire page is replaced in the browser window with the mew image. This can result in a loss of content, and confidence."
1169,'',"Double click blog post title in left nav to open edit pane.\nAs a power user I'd like to be able to click a blog post title within the left nav list of the Ghost admin panel to open that article up in edit mode.\r\n\r\n* Log in to Ghost admin panel\r\n* Click the Content button in the top left corner\r\n* View list of existing posts\r\n* Double click one to open it in edit mode"
