1155,'','Resetting passwords may be insecure\nPasswords are encrypted in the DB, which is great. But when you reset your password, the new password is sent to you by email. If Ghost mail settings are configured without SSL/TLS, then the email will be sent in clear text, which can be intercepted.\r\n\r\nThis is leaving aside the issue of email security in general.\r\n\r\nInstead of sending an email with the new password, Ghost should send an email with a link to a "password reset" page. From there, the user can set their new password themselves. The link should also auto-expire after a certain period of time to ensure that it can\'t be reused at a later time.\r\n\r\nAlso, I noticed the email template is a bit vague. It would be great if the template can be customised, or at least provide more details and context.\r\n\r\nThanks!'
