1146,'','Separate strings out into separate language file\nAfter looking through some of the server code, I have found that there are a lot of strings that don\'t mutate.\r\n\r\nFor example: \r\n\r\n        GhostBookshelf.validator.check(this.get(\'email\'), "Please enter a valid email address. That one looks a bit dodgy.").isEmail();\r\n\r\nIs it worth refactoring all these strings out into separate language files. \r\n\r\nFor example, a module could have a file:\r\n\r\n=> language/english/strings.js\r\n     \r\n       string[\'valid_email_message\'] = \'Please enter a valid email address....\';\r\n\r\nThis gives the ability to easily support multiple language in the future:\r\n\r\n=> language/australian/strings.js\r\n       \r\n       string[\'valid_email_message\'] = \'Enter a bloody valid email address ya bastard....\';\r\n\r\netc.\r\n\r\n\r\n'
