1059,'',"Feature Request: Support for content storage in s3\nHello!\r\nOne of the most common ways someone will host a nodejs application is with a service like heroku, openshift, or nodejitsu. Right now, you *can* deploy Ghost on these platforms, but it is a bad idea, as these services have a limited amount of volatile memory. The recommended way to work with this is to store your data in a service like s3. \r\n\r\nAs a node developer, I could probably hack in s3 support for my app, however I would be much nicer if you offered support for a services like s3 from the base up. \r\n\r\nIt wouldn't be too difficult, as the only file that really has to be moved would be the sqllite db files. It would also be nice to offer some really easy photo upload method and be able to alias the images to your website(www.my-ghost-blog.com/content/images/2013/oct/image.png instead of mybucket.s3.amazonaws.com/content/images/2013/oct/image.png)\r\n\r\nI would be happy to work on implementing this, but I would like to hear responses on whether or not this should be part of the ghost core.\r\n\r\n"
