1013,'','Allow ghost to work with both HTTP and HTTPS via config.js\nGhost currently requires a scheme (e.g. `url: \'http://example.com\'`) for the site URL in the config.js. Ghost should be updated to support a no-scheme URL (e.g. `url: \'//example.com\'` without the **http:**).\r\n\r\nNot requiring the scheme would allow guests to read the blog over HTTP, but the blog user/admin to login and make edits over HTTPS, enhancing blog security and preventing the admin password from being sent in plaintext over the internet.\r\n\r\nThis change is already supported by Nodejs [url.parse()](http://nodejs.org/docs/latest/api/url.html) by adding two additional arguments of `, false, true` properly get the hostname.\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nurl.parse(this.ghost.config().url, false, true).hostname\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis change would be necessary for anywhere the config url is parsed, this is done in two places in the source:\r\n- [ ] core/config-loader.js\r\n- [x] core/server/mail.js\r\n\r\nAdditionally, to prevent a mixed content warning, the hardcoded HTTP link for the google font API should also be changed to remove the scheme in:\r\n- [x] core/server/views/default.hbs\r\n- [ ] core/server/views/user-error.hbs\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<link rel="stylesheet" type=\'text/css\' href=\'//fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans:400,300,700\'>\r\n```'
