875,'','Update express to 3.4.x to help support Azure\nThere seems to be an issue with showing the default/custom error page. \r\n\r\nFrom a friend of ghost on twitter (paraphrased): \r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\nFor example, if you look at the `renderErrorInt` function within `/core/server/errorHandling.js` you\'ll see that it does a `res.render` and passes in a view to render. Unfortunately, as it stands, Express pukes up an error "Failed to lookup view [name]".\r\n\r\nAfter digging thru the Express code, I believe this is the reason: https://github.com/visionmedia/express/commit/9e406dfee22f172c084c900e235e1ac7e9497a24\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\nHe tested and updating seems to be working for him, I have yet to run the functional tests against an install of ghost with the latest version of express though.'
