868,'','[Service AWS] Ghost EC2 Config needs updating\nI\'m posting this here, just incase there I did something wrong when deploying, as I don\'t want to potentially break something which is already working. \r\n\r\nWhen running 0.3.0 on AWS, I was getting;\r\n```\r\n/var/www/core/config-loader.js:14\r\n            throw new Error(\'Could not locate a configuration file. Please che\r\n                  ^\r\nError: Could not locate a configuration file. Please check your deployment for config.js or config.example.js.\r\n    at checkTemplate (/var/www/core/config-loader.js:14:19)\r\n    at Object.cb [as oncomplete] (fs.js:168:19)\r\n```\r\n\r\nI found that this was because we were running the following in Upstart;\r\n```\r\n/usr/bin/node /var/www/index.js\r\n```\r\nMy guess this is breaking the `config.js` find file code.\r\nThe fix for me was to change the Upstart section in https://gist.github.com/ErisDS/3d7b5e2731f56f8617f8, to;\r\n\r\n```\r\n#!upstart\r\ndescription "Ghost Blog"\r\nauthor      "Ghost Foundation"\r\n\r\nstart on runlevel [2345]\r\nstop on runlevel [016]\r\n\r\nscript\r\n    export HOME="/root"\r\n\r\n    echo 1340 > /var/run/ghost.pid\r\n\tcd /var/www/\r\n    exec sudo -u ubuntu sh -c "/usr/bin/node index.js"\r\nend script\r\n\r\npre-stop script\r\n    rm /var/run/ghost.pid\r\nend script\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf this is a problem for everyone and not just me, I\'ll update the script.'
