824,'',"Possible Security Issue Using express.bodyParser\nI was alerted to a possible security issue with using `express.bodyParser` last night and did a bit of checking this morning. The basic premise is that with bodyParser turned on, one could actually throw files at any express route and temp files would be created regardless of if the route actually handles uploads. I don't see an explicit fix, but the suggestion is to split out the `express.multipart` middleware to only be registered on the actual upload route: https://github.com/visionmedia/express/issues/1673"
