646,'','Display keyboard shortcut appropriate to OS\nCloses #348\r\n\r\n* Changed markdown.hbs so that all keyboard shortcuts are written in Windows format (e.g. Ctrl + B)\r\n* Changed markdown.hbs to use Ctrl/Cmd + Shift + K for `code` shortcut. This is a change for Mac functionality from previous shortcut of Cmd + K\r\n* Added afterRender callback to the Markdown modal that replaces instances of Ctrl with ⌘'
645,'','New cmd+enter shortcut to go to a new paragraph without modifying the current line\nNew kb shortcut: cmd+enter \r\n\r\nAction: moves the cursor down 2 new lines without changing the current line. Eg.\r\n\r\nFrom here\r\n\r\n![image](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/120485/1101181/8c24f22e-17af-11e3-8684-864ac107f43c.png)\r\n\r\nTo here\r\n\r\n![image](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/120485/1101184/a60a4e6e-17af-11e3-8be7-cfc57380eeea.png)'
644,'','Markdown output jumps around like a monkey on crack when writing in italics\nExpected behaviour: Preview remains in italics, even when typing a space between italics tags.\r\n\r\nActual behaviour:\r\n![italicbug](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/120485/1101169/752f507e-17ae-11e3-83b9-90fbdb4d3180.gif)\r\n'
643,'',"Keyboard shortcut for italic inserts _ instead of *\nI realise that both `_italic_` and `*italic*` are supported in Markdown, but I'd prefer to keep us to the simpler defaults of `*italic*` and `**bold**` at least for keyboard shortcuts.\r\n\r\nCurrently on the editor when you press `cmd+i` it generates underscores, this should be changed to asterisks."
642,'','Tags automatically get converted to lowercase\nReproduce:\r\n\r\nEnter a new tag: About Ghost\r\n\r\nPress enter\r\n\r\nExpected result: Tag is created as `About Ghost`\r\n\r\nActual result: Tag is created as `about ghost`\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nTags should maintain the capitalisation which they were originally given.\r\n\r\nEg.\r\n\r\nIf a tag is entered for the first time as "Ghost" and later in another post, the user enters "ghost" - it should autocorrect to "Ghost".\r\n\r\nObviously we don\'t want duplicate tags, so we want to check if a tag already exists (regardless of capitalisation) - and match it if it does.\r\n\r\n/cc @skattyadz - I know this issue has been around since before you were working on tags. But you\'re probably most familiar with this area, and might have some ideas!'
