615,'','Post with image markdown displays broken HTML\nSummary of Issue \r\n------------------------------- \r\n\r\nPost with image markdown `![](http://)` displays nothing in preview, but shows broken HTML on the frontend\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce \r\n------------------------------- \r\n\r\n- create a new post\r\n- add image markdown\r\n- publish the post\r\n- view the post (not in /ghost/content/ but on the homepage)\r\n\r\nObserved result \r\n------------------------------- \r\n\r\nbroken html is displayed\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2013-09-02 at 3 05 26 pm](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/4643742/1069478/5ee1b324-141c-11e3-85fa-1a6e63f738c0.png)\r\n\r\nAdditional Information \r\n-------------------------------\r\n\r\nClient OS: Mac OS X 10.8.4\r\nServer OS: CentOS 6.4\r\nNode Version: 0.10.16\r\nGhost Build Number: 0.2.1\r\nLatest Commit: 13646f9ef6a5ac6100f3b4286e2efabd6a4bf436\r\nBrowser: Chrome 29.0.1547.62'
