573,'',"Ghost 'global' data - refactor / rethink\nRelated to #482 (migrations being a PITA) and #360 (BIG FAT refactor) and the separation of settings from fixtures #567 and the potential of binding data: #550\r\n\r\nGhost has several sources of what I am probably incorrectly referring to as 'global' data. \r\n- config.js\r\n- settings model\r\n- loaded state (such as the available themes)\r\n\r\nThis data is currently accessed in various ways, and is only available to the server, when in fact much of it is required on the admin client\r\n\r\nWe also have a very old issue open about dividing settings up into groups: #172 \r\n\r\nI'd like to make it easier to access this sort of data. I'd like to make it much clearer what data is and isn't available.\r\n\r\nWe also need a simple way of providing a reduced/filtered version of the data to themes via helpers. At the moment it is done through res.locals, which is nice but means if you're inside a post, getting to the url (currently in settings but being moved to config) requires you to do {{../settings.url}} when what we really want is something like {{blog.url}}.\r\n\r\nI'm not 100% sure how to go about achieving all of this in a sensible way and am very much interested in suggestions."
572,'ErisDS','Move url from settings to env config\nThere is currently a URL setting in the fixtures, but no way to edit this. We want to remove the URL from there and instead have it defined as part of the environment config.\r\n\r\nThis allows people to specify the correct URL for their blog in various environments.\r\n\r\nIt should be set to the same as the host and port number for each environment by default.'
