564,'',"Add post tagging functionality\ncloses #367\r\ncloses #368\r\ncloses #369\r\n\r\n- Adds Tag model with a many-to-many relationship with Post\r\n- Adds Tag API to retrieve all previously used Tags (needed for suggestions)\r\n- Allows setting and retrieval of Tags for a Post through the Post's existing API endpoints.\r\n- Hooks up the editor's Tag suggestion box to the Ghost install's previously used Tags\r\n- Tidies the client code for adding Tags, and encapsulates the functionality into a Backbone view\r\n- Replace any mention of 'categories' with 'tags'\r\n\r\nServer-side code should have full unit test coverage. Haven't done any integration tests.\r\n\r\n### Tags in the API:\r\n\r\nTags can be accessed through a Post. They appear in the JSON like this http://c.skatty.me/QzDx\r\n![screen shot 2013-08-23 at 17 22 01](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/91115/1052142/0cb4f54e-10d8-11e3-8109-6964cae9ef83.png)\r\n\r\nYou can set the Tags on a Post as part of the existing Post update call using a 'tags' parameter. It looks like this:\r\n![screen shot 2013-08-23 at 17 27 57](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/91115/1052141/05f9cf68-10d8-11e3-91f2-9ad4fdcdf8a9.png)\r\n\r\nThe tags array is optional, but if it is provided in an update, any added/removed Tags will be unlinked from the Post model in the database. Tags are referenced by ID; if a Tag is submitted without an ID it is assumed that a new Tag should be created with those attributes.\r\n\r\n### Considerations:\r\n\r\n- Haven't put any thought into smaller screens. It doesn't wrap nicely or do anything clever\r\n- Haven't tested in IE (I'm on crappy 3G connection right now)"
