523,'','Validation improvements\nThis PR is a combination of some work I have been doing to improve consistency of validation and an additional fix I have done for #517\r\n\r\nBoth of these fixes are similar in that they move validation onto the models themselves. Models should, in my opinion, be able to properly validate their state so that no matter what gets sent to them via the public API they are always OK.\r\n\r\nThe stripping of the properties is pretty aggressive, but I think this is the best plan.\r\n\r\nThis PR requires a lot more testing and additionally some more casper tests to ensure that the validation works correctly across the UI. However, I wanted to get it out there so hopefully some other eyes can take a look.'
