459,'',"Adding Github Flavored Markdown support\nI've been using a markdown file in the Ghost editor with a tonne of test cases in it. About to convert that into some proper unit tests (and possibly casperJS tests as well). Meanwhile, I thought I'd get some eyes on this.\r\n\r\nIt is a mixture of copy-pasta from here: https://gist.github.com/jorilallo/1283095#file-showdown-js-L158\r\nAnd a port of the ruby code from here: https://help.github.com/articles/github-flavored-markdown#gist118964\r\n\r\n`core/shared/vendor/showdown/extensions/github.js` is the custom / interesting file\r\n\r\ncloses #422\r\n\r\n- Upgraded codemirror to 3.15\r\n- Added GFM mode to codemirror\r\n- Took the github.js extension for Showdown and added all useful behaviour\r\n- Now supports strikethrough, auto linking urls & email, line breaking and multiple underscores\r\n\r\nTODO: unit tests\r\n"
