411,'',"Add 404 page\nA very simple 404 page styled with the current theme (added some padding\r\nbut that's it). Sent as a static file instead of a view to prevent us\r\nhaving to duplicate it on the theme and the admin side for now.\r\n\r\nCloses #409."
410,'',"Implement e-mail sending.\nImplements the behaviour described in https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/issues/53#issuecomment-22374025.\r\n\r\nFor the tests, I decided to mock the `ghost` object itself, so they run in a few ms and never touch disk or the database, except for require calls.\r\n\r\nThere is a `ghost.mail.sendWelcomeMessage` method, as suggested by @jgable (I think). It should be called during the first run, not sure where that would go.\r\n\r\nSuggestions appreciated, I'll continue updating this PR as needed."
409,'',"Handling non-existent content\nDo this:\r\n* create a post\r\n* be on the front end for the post with its permalink, don't navigate away\r\n* delete the post\r\n* refresh the page on the front end\r\n\r\nExpected behaviour:\r\n* a 404 page informing me that there's no such content\r\n\r\nActual behaviour:\r\n* chrome is still spinning, it will probably time out"
408,'',"Add LiveReload Grunt Dev Task\nAdds the ability to run a new task via `grunt dev` that will watch our\r\nsass, templates and javascript files for changes and reload them in the browser.\r\n\r\nAlso, refactored the Gruntfile to auto load all grunt-* tasks to remove\r\nsome code.\r\n\r\nI tested this by [installing the livereload chrome extension](http://feedback.livereload.com/knowledgebase/articles/86242-how-do-i-install-and-use-the-browser-extensions-) and running the `grunt dev` task locally.  It won't work on the VM right now because the livereload extension looks specifically for a localhost:[port] address for the livereload server."
407,'','Post Permissions\nAdded permissions checks around the main Post API methods.  Some notable changes are:\r\n\r\n- Added 003 migration that sets **all users** to admins who may have previously been created.\r\n- Added an "apiContext" scope to use as the `this` value in the `requestHandler`; didn\'t know whether to just pass a user id or not.\r\n- In the course of testing the update, fixed the way we are showing error messages from the API.  Added a base view helper method to do this because I couldn\'t see a utils lib anywhere.'
406,'','Markdown toolbar on mobile\n[From the forums](http://vip.tryghost.org/feedback/topic/markdown-toolbar/#post-419):\r\n\r\n> I think one really awesome feature of Ghost is that you can write from your mobile devices and I also like the idea of writing with markdown instead of a WYSIWYG editor, . . but . . writing markdown from a mobile device is a painful task!, that’s why I think a markdown toolbar is a good idea :).\r\n\r\n'
405,'',"MySQL Support\nMySQL Support\r\n\r\nCloses #364\r\n- Confirmed integration with local mysql installation works.\r\n- Updated fixtures and migration with appropriate schema-conforming values.\r\n- Updated schema with appropriate defaults and nullable columns.\r\n- Updated fixDates function on model base to appropriately deserialize\r\nvalues coming from SQLite now that dates are stored as actual DateTime\r\nobjects/ISO strings.\r\n- Updated default language to be 'en_US'.\r\n\r\nSample MySQL Connection (to be inserted in `config.js`):\r\n```javascript\r\ndatabase: {\r\n\tclient: 'mysql',\r\n\tconnection: {\r\n\t\thost: 'localhost',\r\n\t\tuser: 'root',\r\n\t\tpassword: 'Sl1m3r',\r\n\t\tdatabase: 'ghost-dev',\r\n\t\tcharset: 'utf8'\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n[How to install MySQL on Ubuntu](https://help.ubuntu.com/lts/serverguide/mysql.html)"
404,'',"Mobile interactions\nThis is simply a commit which improves the mobile interactions. This does not fix missing UI problems on mobiles / tablets, see #149.\r\n\r\n**New interactions;**\r\n\r\nMenu\r\n* Swipe right on header to show sidebar\r\n* Swipe left on sidebar to hide\r\n\r\n![gesture1](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/367517/975857/09c5e462-0681-11e3-81b5-7b72eb38964c.gif)\r\n\r\nContent\r\n* Tap / Swipe left on item to show preview\r\n* Swipe right to show content list\r\n\r\n![gesture2](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/367517/975866/375cb1ee-0681-11e3-9d75-ca58025001e3.gif)\r\n\r\nSettings\r\n* Tap / Swipe left on link to show settings\r\n* Swipe right on settings to show links\r\n\r\n![gesture3](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/367517/975925/5bd88a9c-0682-11e3-8e14-287372fe4d7e.gif)\r\n\r\n\r\n**Added specific designs on mobile;**\r\n\r\n* Content / Settings panels now slide when relative 'link' is clicked.\r\n* 1x1 Widgets now fill screen width (widgets that are 2x width still breaks the layout, this needs a nice solution)\r\n\r\n**Other points;**\r\n* New CasperJS test has been added to test the widgets can be moved\r\n* Hammer.js has had it's 'drag' events disabled due to a collision of event names between it and jQueryUI Draggable"
403,'',"CasperJS tests for mobile interactions and views\nI think we should add some CasperJS tests to make sure mobile versions of Ghost are working correctly. I'll update this issue with possible tests to include.\r\n\r\nDesigns: https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/issues/149\r\n\r\n##\xa0Header / Sidebar\r\n* [ ] Sidebar is hidden and not visible\r\n* [ ] Header button slides in sidebar on tap\r\n* [ ] Links in sidebar are correctly titled\r\n\r\n##\xa0Dashboard\r\n* [ ] Widgets are correct sizes and do not break layout (currently broken)\r\n\r\n## Content\r\n* [ ] Preview is hidden\r\n* [ ] Default view is post links\r\n* [ ] Tapping on post links slide in previews\r\n\r\n##\xa0New Post\r\n* [ ] Default panel is 'Markdown'\r\n* [ ] Preview panel is hidden\r\n* [ ] There is a 'Preview' panel header\r\n* [ ] 'Preview' panel header when tapped displays the preview\r\n\r\n## Settings\r\n* [ ] Settings options are hidden\r\n* [ ] Default view is settings sections links\r\n* [ ] Tapping on settings section slides in right settings options page"
402,'ericterpstra',"Post Settings Menu: published date\nThis is related to / semi-dependent on #370 - in fact either can be done first.\r\n\r\nUser story: https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/wiki/Write-Post#changing-post-settings\r\n\r\nAdd a new item to the post settings menu which allows users to edit the published date on a published post.\r\n\r\nThe label should say 'Published date'. The input should be a text input in the format:\r\ntext input [12 Jul 13] [calendar-icon]\r\n\r\nThe calendar icon is already present as: $i-calendar\r\n\r\nClicking on the calendar icon should open a date picker.\r\n\r\nFor the time being the field should be disabled if the post is not yet published, and the date picker should not allow the user to select dates in the future. This is to prevent confusion as we do not yet have scheduling available."
401,'','Ghostdown should match an image src and prepopulate the dropzone\nCurrently, the Ghostdown image regex captures any image which has a URL, and  shows the upload form disregarding the image that is present.\r\n\r\nThe expected behaviour is that the markup output by ghostdown should have an image tag prepopulated with the src if there is one available.\r\n\r\nThe uploader is built to work with prepopulated images & so this should only require a change to ghostdown.'
400,'','Make Ghostdown image regex is a bit too greedy\nCurrently, the Ghostdown image regex captures any image which has a URL, and therefore shows the upload form. \r\n\r\nThe expected behaviour is that if the user provides a url inside the parens, that the form/dropzone would not be shown, and the image markdown would behave as normal.'
399,'',"If Google fonts are not available for some reason, texts don't render\nTo reproduce:\r\n\r\n* be on a bad connection or temporarily disable access to http://themes.googleusercontent.com/static/fonts\r\n* try to view any of the pages (try to recreate it when the request to the above is pending, and not 404 or anything else\r\n\r\nSuggestion:\r\n* have a backup font locally that is being used before google fonts arrive\r\n\r\nOn a slightly offtopic, what's the screencapture to animated gif thing everyone uses?"
