89,'','Publishing by drafts, fetched by type, defaulting to published\nRe: the issues mentioned in #83:\r\n\r\n1. Should be taken care of.\r\n\r\n2. Also should be taken care of by 1, though a lot of the interaction around this will fall on the client side, so i\'m going to let that go until discussing #87\r\n\r\n3. Same as 2, all that should happen is to change the values in the put request for the model\'s properties and save, don\'t want to try to do that in the UI yet without further discussion\r\n\r\n4. Also UI related\r\n\r\n5 & 6. Done pretty simply on the `findPage` method, only shows "published" by default, allows passing \'all\' as an option well as any other conditions - though this feels sort of hacked together and the entire model/api layer should probably be discussed pretty in-depth to standardize the query structure, especially given the different potential permissions/caching/relation loading requirements and how these should be specified and returned in different api requests'
