4508,'',"About Page: Functional Tests\nLet's add some functional tests to cover the about screen in the settings panel.\r\n\r\nThis screen outputs some dynamic data which changes over time, but it would be nice to verify that each item has a valid value:\r\n\r\n- The version number should be a number\r\n- The database should be one of sqlite3, MySQL or PostGres.\r\n- There should be 20 contributors\r\n\r\nAnd so on and so forth.\r\n\r\nThis just ensures that refactors don't impact on that page rendering as it's something we don't tend to look at very often.\r\n\r\nI recommend that these are added to a new `settings_about_test.js` file or similar and not bundled in with the existing settings test."
