4424,'','Don\'t output meta tags with blank content\nIf a user doesn\'t enter anything for their post\'s meta description, the meta description tag is still output but with an empty content, like: `<meta name="description" content="">`\r\n\r\nIf the content is empty, the tag should never be output in the first place.\r\n\r\n\r\nRef [this comment](https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/issues/4413#issuecomment-62363069)'
4421,'','Summary downsize update\nIntroduces downsize v 0.0.8 and uses its contextual tags api to provide a round="true" (up)rounding feature to the content helper.\r\n\r\nI\'ve elected to implement this for the {{content}} helper first; the {{excerpt}} helper currently strips html before passing it to downsize. I want to think a bit about how smart we can be with that interaction, and I\'d love to land this first.\r\n\r\n###ce3e7b2\r\n- downsize 0.0.5 -> 0.0.8\r\n- downsize is now better at punctuation, update {{content}} and {{excerpt}} tests appropriately.\r\n###16c38bf\r\n- Passthrough to Downsize \'contextual tags\' functionality.\r\n- Allows for awaiting a markdown segment level closing tag before truncating content.\r\n- Includes tests.\r\n\r\nrelates to https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/issues/4017\r\n\r\n@ErisDS \r\n\r\n'
4409,'',"Ghost Labs\nWe're starting to develop certain features behind config flags, like tags, and perhaps soon OAuth / public API, custom permalinks, code injection, apps and maybe even search or i18n.\r\n\r\nAs we roll these out people are going to want to play with them, and we ***want*** people playing with these new features in advance, finding bugs, discovering usability issues etc.\r\n\r\nSo how about, as well as having a config flag, we make a 'Ghost Labs' page that provides the ability to turn on these options. The Ghost Labs page would be a hidden page a lot like our Ugly Debug Tools, that would simply live at `/ghost/labs/` with no internal link.\r\n\r\nWe can add a 'labs' setting to the settings DB that stores a JSON object with a boolean value for each feature we add to the page and whether it's on or off - which overrides the config value.\r\n\r\nThis might be a teeny bit fiddly to implement, but I think it could be a lot of fun, and a great way to get more feedback on features whilst they are in development. It would give us a space to try things out that we aren't sure about, or provide different potential solutions and experiment a little bit with what works best in practice. \r\n"
