4350,'',"Make /settings/user adapter hit /api/users/:slug to fetch a user\nFrom `core/client/routes/settings/users/user.js`\r\n```js\r\n// TODO: Make custom user adapter that uses /api/users/:slug endpoint\r\n// return this.store.find('user', { slug: params.slug });\r\n\r\n//What we're doing instead is..\r\n // get all the users and then manually find by slug\r\n return this.store.find('user').then(function (result) {\r\n     var user = result.findBy('slug', params.slug);\r\n     return user;\r\n }\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd actually, if you have a large number of users and haven't loaded all of them when you go to users/user, default pagination (15?) means that this perhaps won't find the user? Is this a bug waiting to happen?"
