3973,'',"[WIP] Post Filter Menu\ncloses #2640\r\n- Adds post filter\r\n- Adds gh-popup to show filter menu\r\n- Implements more filters on posts.api\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nThis PR implements the post filter menu. A live example can be seen in the screencast below (styles would need adjusting - they are inherited from `class='content-list'`). There's a bug with URL handling so that when you refresh the page with a query param active, it will append a trailing slash and screw up a ton of stuff. Not sure if it's us doing the trailing slash or queryParams not handling the our trailing slash correctly. I haven't yet looked into proper pagination, but it should be fairly simple to resolve.\r\n\r\n![post-menu](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/176576/4173659/1f69bf32-3560-11e4-84a2-00ffba881254.gif)\r\n\r\nI realise the issue is in the 0.6 milestone - no hard feelings if this isn't going to get merged, this can easily serve as a PoC. Working on this helped me get a better understanding in the whole Ember magic.\r\n"
3964,'',"Accessibility Testing of Content Editor Page Results \nHiya Chaps,\r\n\r\nI promised Paul a while ago i would take a look at ghost in voiceover to see how it faired. I took a look this evening and it did alright but not too great. I would say its possible to use Ghost in VO (once you figure out the patterns at play) but its not easy. \r\n\r\nI have brain dumped my findings for the content editing page below, i have also done a review of the ghost site account page where you name your account etc.  ~~Where would you like to put those notes?~~ i have emailed those notes directly to Paul.\r\n\r\nI'm happy to help fix some of the issues below. Many of them can be fixed with a bit of rejigging and  offscreen text for extra context. If you let me know which issues you want help with, then I will use the time I have to help you tackle those (possibly making a pull request if i can).\r\n\r\nPages:  https://accessibility-test.ghost.io/ghost/editor/1/\r\n\r\n- Navigation does not indicate current selected page, so page has not obvious title\r\n- Menu on left if Read as “Avatar {Username}” no indication its an menu for account settings. \r\n- Focus works correctly when menu is opened, however menu interaction is non obvious. Consider adding ARIA states. \r\n- Leaving menu into main content does not indicate that editing panel is open. However edit input is read. so the functionality can be guessed at. Consider labelling the the input and hiding the label offscreen.\r\n- “MARKDOWN” text needs more context. Consider writing an off screen introduction to the editor layout / usage. (or a link to a guide which only appears on focus)\r\n- Tags and Post Setting are read correctly and interaction works well.\r\n- Menu on the “Update post” button is not being picked up by voiceover. I'm not entirely sure why, could do with more poking!\r\n\r\nThe notes above are far from complete, they are just the big things i noticed during about a 30 minute test. I can spend longer looking if you need more input. \r\n\r\nHope that helps,\r\n\r\nCheers,\r\n\r\nJamie + Lion"
3961,'',"Change the `{{url}}`helper to be synchronous\nI'm not 100% on what the options for doing this are, but I *think* we can achieve it if we're a bit clever.\r\n\r\nThe main reason why the helper is async, is due to the need to fetch the permalink setting. However, settings are cached meaning that this is normally a synchronous operation anyway. Further still, there should be no need to do this more than one per render of a view, so I'm thinking we could perhaps cache the setting either against the helpers or against express with `app.set` as part of the setup middleware.\r\n\r\nIt'd probably be good to do something like this with settings & config that affect rendering: url, permalink, activeTheme, postsPerPage etc. URL can only change on a server restart, and the others require settings to be changed, so we could refresh the caches for these object either based on events (something we've talked about elsewhere) or only change the values if they're not set, or if the current request is an admin request.\r\n\r\nJust throwing around some thoughts, but the goal remains simple: make `{{url}}` a normal helper, rather than an async helper. \r\n\r\nRemoving the need for async helpers at all is a secondary goal as they're unlikely to ever be supported properly."
3959,'',"[Discussion] Make Ghost's Markdown parser adhere to CommonMark\nWe know that markdown is ambiguous. Let's unambiguate it as per ~~http://standardmarkdown.com/~~ http://commonmark.org and implement the syntax in our markdown parser.\r\n\r\nRef: http://blog.codinghorror.com/standard-flavored-markdown/"
3930,'PaulAdamDavis','App UI\n<a href="https://github.com/ErisDS"><img src="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/101513?v=2" align="left" width="96" height="96" hspace="10"></img></a> **Issue by [ErisDS](https://github.com/ErisDS)**\n_Saturday Aug 16, 2014 at 14:29 GMT_\n_Originally opened as https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost-UI/issues/96_\n\n----\n\nNot sure what happened to these, but they are outstanding and belong on this repo. It would be nice to have this UI available to us at some point soon so that we can work on all the app screens and get a very basic (and config enabled) version of the App platform out there in a release some time soon.\r\n\r\nEverything after the break is copied straight from https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost/issues/2065\r\n---\r\n\r\nThe item is currently a draft because the UI designs are still a work in progress. \r\n\r\nHere they are so far, for your viewing pleasure.\r\n\r\n![desktop](http://f.cl.ly/items/0h1b1Z101F3V0M1m3Y2O/Apps.png)\r\n![tablet](http://f.cl.ly/items/101n3v1p130v3t0y3o1C/Apps%20-%20Tablet.png)\r\n![mobile](http://f.cl.ly/items/1c09220x2e10402t422Q/Apps%20-%20Mobile.png)\r\n![delete](http://f.cl.ly/items/1X1S450v3K38081Q0S0k/Apps-delete.png)\r\n![manage](http://f.cl.ly/items/3W183M170s0j2Z1a0G12/Apps-bulkmanage.png)\n'
3928,'','Implement button:loading style\n<a href="https://github.com/JohnONolan"><img src="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/120485?v=2" align="left" width="96" height="96" hspace="10"></img></a> **Issue by [JohnONolan](https://github.com/JohnONolan)**\n_Thursday Jul 17, 2014 at 09:29 GMT_\n_Originally opened as https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost-UI/issues/71_\n\n----\n\nLet\'s get rid of the - pardon me - fucking horrendous button style that exists right now when an action is pending. (Where the button goes dim + inactive, but still has a hover state, but doesn\'t do anything)\r\n\r\nCan we bring over the button-loading spinner from ghost.org and use that instead?\n'
3927,'PaulAdamDavis','First pass on new importer UI\n<a href="https://github.com/JohnONolan"><img src="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/120485?v=2" align="left" width="96" height="96" hspace="10"></img></a> **Issue by [JohnONolan](https://github.com/JohnONolan)**\n_Wednesday Jun 25, 2014 at 10:39 GMT_\n_Originally opened as https://github.com/TryGhost/Ghost-UI/issues/47_\n\n----\n\nThis probably needs more discussion / spec. Just a starting point for the UI.\r\n\r\nSketch3 file - http://cl.ly/WFFg\r\n\r\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/120485/3384127/a9d2e9d6-fc54-11e3-81b1-867aee9de41e.png)\r\n\r\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/120485/3384132/b333fae2-fc54-11e3-9e68-005aa3db6e7c.png)\r\n\r\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/120485/3384136/c04693c0-fc54-11e3-92b3-0177572800ec.png)\r\n\r\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/120485/3384144/d286cde8-fc54-11e3-95dc-8c94b2cbe4db.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\n'
